v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

196 return v8_Default_embedded_blob_code_;
197}
198uint32_t DefaultEmbeddedBlobCodeSize() {
199 return v8_Default_embedded_blob_code_size_;
200}
201const uint8_t* DefaultEmbeddedBlobData() {

208namespace {
209// These variables provide access to the current embedded blob without requiring
210// an isolate instance. This is needed e.g. by
211// InstructionStream::InstructionStart, which may not have access to an isolate
212// but still needs to access the embedded blob. The variables are initialized by
213// each isolate in Init(). Writes and reads are relaxed since we can guarantee
214// that the current thread has initialized these variables before accessing
215// them. Different threads may race, but this is fine since they all attempt to
216// set the same values of the blob pointer and size.
217
218std::atomic<const uint8_t*> current_embedded_blob_code_(nullptr);
219std::atomic<uint32_t> current_embedded_blob_code_size_(0);
220std::atomic<const uint8_t*> current_embedded_blob_data_(nullptr);
221std::atomic<uint32_t> current_embedded_blob_data_size_(0);
222
223// The various workflows around embedded snapshots are fairly complex. We need
224// to support plain old snapshot builds, nosnap builds, and the requirements of
225// subtly different serialization tests. There's two related knobs to twiddle:
226//
227// - The default embedded blob may be overridden by setting the sticky embedded
228// blob. This is set automatically whenever we create a new embedded blob.
229//
230// - Lifecycle management can be either manual or set to refcounting.
231//
232// A few situations to demonstrate their use:
233//
234// - A plain old snapshot build neither overrides the default blob nor
235// refcounts.
236//
237// - mksnapshot sets the sticky blob and manually frees the embedded
238// blob once done.
239//
240// - Most serializer tests do the same.
241//
242// - Nosnapshot builds set the sticky blob and enable refcounting.
243
244// This mutex protects access to the following variables:
245// - sticky_embedded_blob_code_
246// - sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_
247// - sticky_embedded_blob_data_
248// - sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_
249// - enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_
250// - current_embedded_blob_refs_
251base::LazySpinningMutex current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_ =
252 LAZY_SELFISH_MUTEX_INITIALIZER;
253
254const uint8_t* sticky_embedded_blob_code_ = nullptr;
255uint32_t sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_ = 0;
256const uint8_t* sticky_embedded_blob_data_ = nullptr;
257uint32_t sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_ = 0;
258
259bool enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_ = true;
260int current_embedded_blob_refs_ = 0;
261
262const uint8_t* StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() { return sticky_embedded_blob_code_; }
263uint32_t StickyEmbeddedBlobCodeSize() {
264 return sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_;
265}
266const uint8_t* StickyEmbeddedBlobData() { return sticky_embedded_blob_data_; }
267uint32_t StickyEmbeddedBlobDataSize() {
268 return sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_;
269}
270
271void SetStickyEmbeddedBlob(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t code_size,
272 const uint8_t* data, uint32_t data_size) {
273 sticky_embedded_blob_code_ = code;
274 sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_ = code_size;
275 sticky_embedded_blob_data_ = data;
276 sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_ = data_size;
277}
278
279} // namespace
280
281void DisableEmbeddedBlobRefcounting() {
282 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(
283 current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
284 enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_ = false;
285}
286
287void FreeCurrentEmbeddedBlob() {
288 CHECK(!enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_);
289 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(
290 current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
291
292 if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() == nullptr) return;
293
294 CHECK_EQ(StickyEmbeddedBlobCode(), Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode());
295 CHECK_EQ(StickyEmbeddedBlobData(), Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobData());
296
297 OffHeapInstructionStream::FreeOffHeapOffHeapInstructionStream(
298 const_cast<uint8_t*>(Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode()),
299 Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobCodeSize(),
300 const_cast<uint8_t*>(Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobData()),
301 Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobDataSize());
302
303 current_embedded_blob_code_.store(nullptr, std::memory_order_relaxed);
304 current_embedded_blob_code_size_.store(0, std::memory_order_relaxed);
305 current_embedded_blob_data_.store(nullptr, std::memory_order_relaxed);
306 current_embedded_blob_data_size_.store(0, std::memory_order_relaxed);
307 sticky_embedded_blob_code_ = nullptr;
308 sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_ = 0;
309 sticky_embedded_blob_data_ = nullptr;
310 sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_ = 0;
311}
312
313// static
314bool Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobIsBinaryEmbedded() {
315 // In some situations, we must be able to rely on the embedded blob being
316 // immortal immovable. This is the case if the blob is binary-embedded.
317 // See blob lifecycle controls above for descriptions of when the current
318 // embedded blob may change (e.g. in tests or mksnapshot). If the blob is
319 // binary-embedded, it is immortal immovable.
320 const uint8_t* code =
321 current_embedded_blob_code_.load(std::memory_order_relaxed);
322 if (code == nullptr) return false;
323 return code == DefaultEmbeddedBlobCode();
324}
325
326void Isolate::SetEmbeddedBlob(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t code_size,
327 const uint8_t* data, uint32_t data_size) {
328 CHECK_NOT_NULL(code);
329 CHECK_NOT_NULL(data);
330
331 embedded_blob_code_ = code;
332 embedded_blob_code_size_ = code_size;
333 embedded_blob_data_ = data;
334 embedded_blob_data_size_ = data_size;
335 current_embedded_blob_code_.store(code, std::memory_order_relaxed);
336 current_embedded_blob_code_size_.store(code_size, std::memory_order_relaxed);
337 current_embedded_blob_data_.store(data, std::memory_order_relaxed);
338 current_embedded_blob_data_size_.store(data_size, std::memory_order_relaxed);
339
340#ifdef DEBUG
341 // Verify that the contents of the embedded blob are unchanged from
342 // serialization-time, just to ensure the compiler isn't messing with us.
343 EmbeddedData d = EmbeddedData::FromBlob();
344 if (d.EmbeddedBlobDataHash() != d.CreateEmbeddedBlobDataHash()) {
345 FATAL(
346 "Embedded blob data section checksum verification failed. This "
347 "indicates that the embedded blob has been modified since compilation "
348 "time.");
349 }
350 if (v8_flags.text_is_readable) {
351 if (d.EmbeddedBlobCodeHash() != d.CreateEmbeddedBlobCodeHash()) {
352 FATAL(
353 "Embedded blob code section checksum verification failed. This "
354 "indicates that the embedded blob has been modified since "
355 "compilation time. A common cause is a debugging breakpoint set "
356 "within builtin code.");
357 }
358 }
359#endif // DEBUG
360}
361
362void Isolate::ClearEmbeddedBlob() {
363 CHECK(enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_);
364 CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_code_, CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode());
365 CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_code_, StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
366 CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_data_, CurrentEmbeddedBlobData());
367 CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_data_, StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
368
369 embedded_blob_code_ = nullptr;
370 embedded_blob_code_size_ = 0;
371 embedded_blob_data_ = nullptr;
372 embedded_blob_data_size_ = 0;
373 current_embedded_blob_code_.store(nullptr, std::memory_order_relaxed);
374 current_embedded_blob_code_size_.store(0, std::memory_order_relaxed);
375 current_embedded_blob_data_.store(nullptr, std::memory_order_relaxed);
376 current_embedded_blob_data_size_.store(0, std::memory_order_relaxed);
377 sticky_embedded_blob_code_ = nullptr;
378 sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_ = 0;
379 sticky_embedded_blob_data_ = nullptr;
380 sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_ = 0;
381}

416// static
417base::AddressRegion Isolate::GetShortBuiltinsCallRegion() {
418 // Update calculations below if the assert fails.
419 static_assert(kMaxPCRelativeCodeRangeInMB <= 4096);
420 if (kMaxPCRelativeCodeRangeInMB == 0) {
421 // Return empty region if pc-relative calls/jumps are not supported.
422 return base::AddressRegion(kNullAddress, 0);
423 }
424 constexpr size_t max_size = std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max();
425 if (uint64_t{kMaxPCRelativeCodeRangeInMB} * MB > max_size) {
426 // The whole addressable space is reachable with pc-relative calls/jumps.
427 return base::AddressRegion(kNullAddress, max_size);
428 }
429 constexpr size_t radius = kMaxPCRelativeCodeRangeInMB * MB;
430
431 DCHECK_LT(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCodeSize(), radius);
432 Address embedded_blob_code_start =
433 reinterpret_cast<Address>(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode());
434 if (embedded_blob_code_start == kNullAddress) {
435 // Return empty region if there's no embedded blob.
436 return base::AddressRegion(kNullAddress, 0);
437 }
438 Address embedded_blob_code_end =
439 embedded_blob_code_start + CurrentEmbeddedBlobCodeSize();
440 Address region_start =
441 (embedded_blob_code_end > radius) ? (embedded_blob_code_end - radius) : 0;
442 Address region_end = embedded_blob_code_start + radius;
443 if (region_end < embedded_blob_code_start) {
444 region_end = static_cast<Address>(-1);
445 }
446 return base::AddressRegion(region_start, region_end - region_start);
447}
448
449size_t Isolate::HashIsolateForEmbeddedBlob() {
450 DCHECK(builtins_.is_initialized());
451 DCHECK(Builtins::AllBuiltinsAreIsolateIndependent());
452
453 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
454
455 static constexpr size_t kSeed = 0;
456 size_t hash = kSeed;
457
458 // Hash static entries of the roots table.
459 hash = base::hash_combine(hash, V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL);
460#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
461 hash = base::hash_combine(hash,
462 static_cast<int>(RootIndex::kReadOnlyRootsCount));
463 RootIndex i = RootIndex::kFirstReadOnlyRoot;
464 for (auto ptr : StaticReadOnlyRootsPointerTable) {
465 hash = base::hash_combine(ptr, hash);
466 ++i;
467 }
468#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
469
470 // Hash data sections of builtin code objects.
471 for (Builtin builtin = Builtins::kFirst; builtin <= Builtins::kLast;
472 ++builtin) {
473 Tagged<Code> code = builtins()->code(builtin);
474
475 DCHECK(Internals::HasHeapObjectTag(code.ptr()));
476 uint8_t* const code_ptr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(code.address());
477
478 // These static asserts ensure we don't miss relevant fields. We don't hash
479 // instruction_start, but other data fields must remain the same.
480 static_assert(Code::kEndOfStrongFieldsOffset ==
481 Code::kInstructionStartOffset);
482#ifndef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
483 static_assert(
484 Code::kInstructionStartOffsetEnd + 1 +
485 (V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL ? kJSDispatchHandleSize : 0) ==
486 Code::kFlagsOffset);
487#endif
488 static_assert(Code::kFlagsOffsetEnd + 1 == Code::kInstructionSizeOffset);
489 static_assert(Code::kInstructionSizeOffsetEnd + 1 ==
490 Code::kMetadataSizeOffset);
491 static_assert(Code::kMetadataSizeOffsetEnd + 1 ==
492 Code::kInlinedBytecodeSizeOffset);
493 static_assert(Code::kInlinedBytecodeSizeOffsetEnd + 1 ==
494 Code::kOsrOffsetOffset);
495 static_assert(Code::kOsrOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
496 Code::kHandlerTableOffsetOffset);
497 static_assert(Code::kHandlerTableOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
498 Code::kUnwindingInfoOffsetOffset);
499 static_assert(Code::kUnwindingInfoOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
500 Code::kConstantPoolOffsetOffset);
501 static_assert(Code::kConstantPoolOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
502 Code::kCodeCommentsOffsetOffset);
503 static_assert(Code::kCodeCommentsOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
504 Code::kBuiltinJumpTableInfoOffsetOffset);
505 static_assert(Code::kBuiltinJumpTableInfoOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
506 Code::kParameterCountOffset);
507 static_assert(Code::kParameterCountOffsetEnd + 1 == Code::kBuiltinIdOffset);
508 static_assert(Code::kBuiltinIdOffsetEnd + 1 == Code::kUnalignedSize);
509 static constexpr int kStartOffset = Code::kFlagsOffset;
510
511 for (int j = kStartOffset; j < Code::kUnalignedSize; j++) {
512 hash = base::hash_combine(hash, size_t{code_ptr[j]});
513 }
514 }
515
516 // The builtins constants table is also tightly tied to embedded builtins.
517 hash = base::hash_combine(
518 hash, static_cast<size_t>(heap_.builtins_constants_table()->length()));
519
520 return hash;
521}

524 V8_CONSTINIT = nullptr;
525thread_local Isolate* g_current_isolate_ V8_CONSTINIT = nullptr;

527V8_TLS_DEFINE_GETTER(Isolate::TryGetCurrent, Isolate*, g_current_isolate_)

532namespace {
533// A global counter for all generated Isolates, might overflow.
534std::atomic<int> isolate_counter{0};
535} // namespace
536
537Isolate::PerIsolateThreadData*
538Isolate::FindOrAllocatePerThreadDataForThisThread() {
539 ThreadId thread_id = ThreadId::Current();
540 PerIsolateThreadData* per_thread = nullptr;
541 {
542 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&thread_data_table_mutex_);
543 per_thread = thread_data_table_.Lookup(thread_id);
544 if (per_thread == nullptr) {
545 if (v8_flags.adjust_os_scheduling_parameters) {
546 base::OS::AdjustSchedulingParams();
547 }
548 per_thread = new PerIsolateThreadData(this, thread_id);
549 thread_data_table_.Insert(per_thread);
550 }
551 DCHECK(thread_data_table_.Lookup(thread_id) == per_thread);
552 }
553 return per_thread;
554}
555
556void Isolate::DiscardPerThreadDataForThisThread() {
557 ThreadId thread_id = ThreadId::TryGetCurrent();
558 if (thread_id.IsValid()) {
559 DCHECK_NE(thread_manager_->mutex_owner_.load(std::memory_order_relaxed),
560 thread_id);
561 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&thread_data_table_mutex_);
562 PerIsolateThreadData* per_thread = thread_data_table_.Lookup(thread_id);
563 if (per_thread) {
564 DCHECK(!per_thread->thread_state_);
565 thread_data_table_.Remove(per_thread);
566 }
567 }
568}

570Isolate::PerIsolateThreadData* Isolate::FindPerThreadDataForThisThread() {
571 ThreadId thread_id = ThreadId::Current();
572 return FindPerThreadDataForThread(thread_id);
573}
574
575Isolate::PerIsolateThreadData* Isolate::FindPerThreadDataForThread(
576 ThreadId thread_id) {
577 PerIsolateThreadData* per_thread = nullptr;
578 {
579 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&thread_data_table_mutex_);
580 per_thread = thread_data_table_.Lookup(thread_id);
581 }
582 return per_thread;
583}

585void Isolate::InitializeOncePerProcess() { Heap::InitializeOncePerProcess(); }
586
587Address Isolate::get_address_from_id(IsolateAddressId id) {
588 return isolate_addresses_[id];
589}
590
591char* Isolate::Iterate(RootVisitor* v, char* thread_storage) {
592 ThreadLocalTop* thread = reinterpret_cast<ThreadLocalTop*>(thread_storage);
593 Iterate(v, thread);
594 // Normally, ThreadLocalTop::topmost_script_having_context_ is visited weakly
595 // but in order to simplify handling of frozen threads we just clear it.
596 // Otherwise, we'd need to traverse the thread_storage again just to find this
597 // one field.
598 thread->topmost_script_having_context_ = Context();
599 return thread_storage + sizeof(ThreadLocalTop);
600}
601
602void Isolate::IterateThread(ThreadVisitor* v, char* t) {
603 ThreadLocalTop* thread = reinterpret_cast<ThreadLocalTop*>(t);
604 v->VisitThread(this, thread);
605}
606
607void Isolate::Iterate(RootVisitor* v, ThreadLocalTop* thread) {
608 // Visit the roots from the top for a given thread.
609 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
610 FullObjectSlot(&thread->exception_));
611 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
612 FullObjectSlot(&thread->pending_message_));
613 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
614 FullObjectSlot(&thread->context_));
615
616 for (v8::TryCatch* block = thread->try_catch_handler_; block != nullptr;
617 block = block->next_) {
618 // TODO(3770): Make TryCatch::exception_ an Address (and message_obj_ too).
619 v->VisitRootPointer(
620 Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
621 FullObjectSlot(reinterpret_cast<Address>(&(block->exception_))));
622 v->VisitRootPointer(
623 Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
624 FullObjectSlot(reinterpret_cast<Address>(&(block->message_obj_))));
625 }
626
627 v->VisitRootPointer(
628 Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
629 FullObjectSlot(continuation_preserved_embedder_data_address()));
630
631 // Iterate over pointers on native execution stack.
632#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
633 wasm::WasmCodeRefScope wasm_code_ref_scope;
634
635 for (const std::unique_ptr<wasm::StackMemory>& stack : wasm_stacks_) {
636 if (stack->IsActive()) {
637 continue;
638 }
639 for (StackFrameIterator it(this, stack.get()); !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
640 it.frame()->Iterate(v);
641 }
642 }
643 StackFrameIterator it(this, thread, StackFrameIterator::FirstStackOnly{});
644#else
645 StackFrameIterator it(this, thread);
646#endif
647 for (; !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
648 it.frame()->Iterate(v);
649 }
650}
651
652void Isolate::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) {
653 ThreadLocalTop* current_t = thread_local_top();
654 Iterate(v, current_t);
655}
656
657void Isolate::RegisterTryCatchHandler(v8::TryCatch* that) {
658 thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_ = that;
659}
660
661void Isolate::UnregisterTryCatchHandler(v8::TryCatch* that) {
662 DCHECK_EQ(thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_, that);
663 thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_ = that->next_;
664 SimulatorStack::UnregisterJSStackComparableAddress(this);
665}
666
667Handle<String> Isolate::StackTraceString() {
668 if (stack_trace_nesting_level_ == 0) {
669 stack_trace_nesting_level_++;
670 HeapStringAllocator allocator;
671 StringStream::ClearMentionedObjectCache(this);
672 StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
673 incomplete_message_ = &accumulator;
674 PrintStack(&accumulator);
675 Handle<String> stack_trace = accumulator.ToString(this);
676 incomplete_message_ = nullptr;
677 stack_trace_nesting_level_ = 0;
678 return stack_trace;
679 } else if (stack_trace_nesting_level_ == 1) {
680 stack_trace_nesting_level_++;
681 base::OS::PrintError(
682 "\n\nAttempt to print stack while printing stack (double fault)\n");
683 base::OS::PrintError(
684 "If you are lucky you may find a partial stack dump on stdout.\n\n");
685 incomplete_message_->OutputToStdOut();
686 return factory()->empty_string();
687 } else {
688 base::OS::Abort();
689 }
690}
691
692void Isolate::PushStackTraceAndDie(void* ptr1, void* ptr2, void* ptr3,
693 void* ptr4, void* ptr5, void* ptr6) {
694 StackTraceFailureMessage message(this,
695 StackTraceFailureMessage::kIncludeStackTrace,
696 ptr1, ptr2, ptr3, ptr4, ptr5, ptr6);
697 message.Print();
698 base::OS::Abort();
699}

701void Isolate::PushParamsAndDie(void* ptr1, void* ptr2, void* ptr3, void* ptr4,
702 void* ptr5, void* ptr6) {
703 StackTraceFailureMessage message(
704 this, StackTraceFailureMessage::kDontIncludeStackTrace, ptr1, ptr2, ptr3,
705 ptr4, ptr5, ptr6);
706 message.Print();
707 base::OS::Abort();
708}

710void Isolate::PushStackTraceAndContinue(void* ptr1, void* ptr2, void* ptr3,
711 void* ptr4, void* ptr5, void* ptr6) {
712 StackTraceFailureMessage message(this,
713 StackTraceFailureMessage::kIncludeStackTrace,
714 ptr1, ptr2, ptr3, ptr4, ptr5, ptr6);
715 message.Print();
716 V8::GetCurrentPlatform()->DumpWithoutCrashing();
717}
718
719void Isolate::PushParamsAndContinue(void* ptr1, void* ptr2, void* ptr3,
720 void* ptr4, void* ptr5, void* ptr6) {
721 StackTraceFailureMessage message(
722 this, StackTraceFailureMessage::kDontIncludeStackTrace, ptr1, ptr2, ptr3,
723 ptr4, ptr5, ptr6);
724 message.Print();
725 V8::GetCurrentPlatform()->DumpWithoutCrashing();
726}
727
728void StackTraceFailureMessage::Print() volatile {
729 // Print the details of this failure message object, including its own address
730 // to force stack allocation.
731 base::OS::PrintError(
732 "Stacktrace:\n ptr1=%p\n ptr2=%p\n ptr3=%p\n ptr4=%p\n "
733 "ptr5=%p\n ptr6=%p\n failure_message_object=%p\n%s",
734 ptr1_, ptr2_, ptr3_, ptr4_, ptr5_, ptr6_, this, &js_stack_trace_[0]);
735}
736
737StackTraceFailureMessage::StackTraceFailureMessage(
738 Isolate* isolate, StackTraceFailureMessage::StackTraceMode mode, void* ptr1,
739 void* ptr2, void* ptr3, void* ptr4, void* ptr5, void* ptr6) {
740 isolate_ = isolate;
741 ptr1_ = ptr1;
742 ptr2_ = ptr2;
743 ptr3_ = ptr3;
744 ptr4_ = ptr4;
745 ptr5_ = ptr5;
746 ptr6_ = ptr6;
747 // Write a stracktrace into the {js_stack_trace_} buffer.
748 const size_t buffer_length = arraysize(js_stack_trace_);
749 memset(&js_stack_trace_, 0, buffer_length);
750 memset(&code_objects_, 0, sizeof(code_objects_));
751 if (mode == kIncludeStackTrace) {
752 FixedStringAllocator fixed(&js_stack_trace_[0], buffer_length - 1);
753 StringStream accumulator(&fixed, StringStream::kPrintObjectConcise);
754 isolate->PrintStack(&accumulator, Isolate::kPrintStackVerbose);
755 // Keeping a reference to the last code objects to increase likelihood that
756 // they get included in the minidump.
757 const size_t code_objects_length = arraysize(code_objects_);
758 size_t i = 0;
759 StackFrameIterator it(isolate);
760 for (; !it.done() && i < code_objects_length; it.Advance()) {
761 code_objects_[i++] =
762 reinterpret_cast<void*>(it.frame()->unchecked_code().ptr());
763 }
764 }
765}
766
767bool NoExtension(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>&) { return false; }
768
769namespace {
770
771bool IsBuiltinFunction(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<HeapObject> object,
772 Builtin builtin) {
773 if (!IsJSFunction(object)) return false;
774 Tagged<JSFunction> const function = Cast<JSFunction>(object);
775 // Currently we have to use full pointer comparison here as builtin Code
776 // objects are still inside the sandbox while runtime-generated Code objects
777 // are in trusted space.
778 static_assert(!kAllCodeObjectsLiveInTrustedSpace);
779 return function->code(isolate).SafeEquals(isolate->builtins()->code(builtin));
780}
781
782// Check if the function is one of the known async function or
783// async generator fulfill handlers.
784bool IsBuiltinAsyncFulfillHandler(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
785 return IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
786 Builtin::kAsyncFunctionAwaitResolveClosure) ||
787 IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
788 Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorAwaitResolveClosure) ||
789 IsBuiltinFunction(
790 isolate, object,
791 Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorYieldWithAwaitResolveClosure);
792}
793
794// Check if the function is one of the known async function or
795// async generator fulfill handlers.
796bool IsBuiltinAsyncRejectHandler(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
797 return IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
798 Builtin::kAsyncFunctionAwaitRejectClosure) ||
799 IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
800 Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorAwaitRejectClosure);
801}
802
803// Check if the function is one of the known builtin rejection handlers that
804// rethrows the exception instead of catching it.
805bool IsBuiltinForwardingRejectHandler(Isolate* isolate,
806 Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
807 return IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object, Builtin::kPromiseCatchFinally) ||
808 IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
809 Builtin::kAsyncFromSyncIteratorCloseSyncAndRethrow);
810}
811
812MaybeHandle<JSGeneratorObject> TryGetAsyncGenerator(
813 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<PromiseReaction> reaction) {
814 // Check if the {reaction} has one of the known async function or
815 // async generator continuations as its fulfill handler.
816 if (IsBuiltinAsyncFulfillHandler(isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler())) {
817 // Now peek into the handlers' AwaitContext to get to
818 // the JSGeneratorObject for the async function.
819 DirectHandle<Context> context(
820 Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler())->context(), isolate);
821 Handle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object(
822 Cast<JSGeneratorObject>(context->extension()), isolate);
823 return generator_object;
824 }
825 return MaybeHandle<JSGeneratorObject>();
826}
827
828#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
829MaybeHandle<WasmSuspenderObject> TryGetWasmSuspender(
830 Isolate* isolate, Tagged<HeapObject> handler) {
831 // Check if the {handler} is WasmResume.
832 if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, handler, Builtin::kWasmResume)) {
833 // Now peek into the handlers' AwaitContext to get to
834 // the JSGeneratorObject for the async function.
835 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = Cast<JSFunction>(handler)->shared();
836 if (shared->HasWasmResumeData()) {
837 return handle(shared->wasm_resume_data()->suspender(), isolate);
838 }
839 }
840 return MaybeHandle<WasmSuspenderObject>();
841}
842#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
843
844int GetGeneratorBytecodeOffset(
845 DirectHandle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object) {
846 // The stored bytecode offset is relative to a different base than what
847 // is used in the source position table, hence the subtraction.
848 return Smi::ToInt(generator_object->input_or_debug_pos()) -
849 (BytecodeArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag);
850}
851
852class CallSiteBuilder {
853 public:
854 CallSiteBuilder(Isolate* isolate, FrameSkipMode mode, int limit,
855 Handle<Object> caller)
856 : isolate_(isolate),
857 mode_(mode),
858 limit_(limit),
859 caller_(caller),
860 skip_next_frame_(mode != SKIP_NONE) {
861 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode_ == SKIP_UNTIL_SEEN, IsJSFunction(*caller_));
862 // Modern web applications are usually built with multiple layers of
863 // framework and library code, and stack depth tends to be more than
864 // a dozen frames, so we over-allocate a bit here to avoid growing
865 // the elements array in the common case.
866 elements_ = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(std::min(64, limit));
867 }
868
869 void SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall() {
870 if (skipped_prev_frame_) return;
871 DCHECK_GT(index_, 0);
872 Tagged<CallSiteInfo> info =
873 Tagged<CallSiteInfo>::cast(elements_->get(index_ - 1));
874 info->set_flags(info->flags() | CallSiteInfo::kIsConstructor);
875 }
876
877 bool Visit(FrameSummary const& summary) {
878 if (Full()) return false;
879#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
880#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
881 if (summary.IsWasmInterpreted()) {
882 AppendWasmInterpretedFrame(summary.AsWasmInterpreted());
883 return true;
884 // FrameSummary::IsWasm() should be renamed FrameSummary::IsWasmCompiled
885 // to be more precise, but we'll leave it as it is to try to reduce merge
886 // churn.
887 } else {
888#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
889 if (summary.IsWasm()) {
890 AppendWasmFrame(summary.AsWasm());
891 return true;
892 }
893#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
894 }
895#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
896 if (summary.IsWasmInlined()) {
897 AppendWasmInlinedFrame(summary.AsWasmInlined());
898 return true;
899 }
900 if (summary.IsBuiltin()) {
901 AppendBuiltinFrame(summary.AsBuiltin());
902 return true;
903 }
904#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
905 AppendJavaScriptFrame(summary.AsJavaScript());
906 return true;
907 }
908
909 void AppendAsyncFrame(DirectHandle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object) {
910 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(generator_object->function(), isolate_);
911 if (!IsVisibleInStackTrace(function)) {
912 skipped_prev_frame_ = true;
913 return;
914 }
915 int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsAsync;
916 if (IsStrictFrame(function)) flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsStrict;
917
918 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver(generator_object->receiver(), isolate_);
919 DirectHandle<BytecodeArray> code(
920 function->shared()->GetBytecodeArray(isolate_), isolate_);
921 int offset = GetGeneratorBytecodeOffset(generator_object);
922
923 DirectHandle<FixedArray> parameters =
924 isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
925 if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.detailed_error_stack_trace)) {
926 parameters = isolate_->factory()->CopyFixedArrayUpTo(
927 direct_handle(generator_object->parameters_and_registers(), isolate_),
928 function->shared()
929 ->internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver());
930 }
931
932 AppendFrame(receiver, function, code, offset, flags, parameters);
933 }
934
935 void AppendPromiseCombinatorFrame(DirectHandle<JSFunction> element_function,
936 DirectHandle<JSFunction> combinator) {
937 if (!IsVisibleInStackTrace(combinator)) {
938 skipped_prev_frame_ = true;
939 return;
940 }
941 int flags =
942 CallSiteInfo::kIsAsync | CallSiteInfo::kIsSourcePositionComputed;
943
944 DirectHandle<JSFunction> receiver(
945 combinator->native_context()->promise_function(), isolate_);
946 DirectHandle<Code> code(combinator->code(isolate_), isolate_);
947
948 // TODO(mmarchini) save Promises list from the Promise combinator
949 DirectHandle<FixedArray> parameters =
950 isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
951
952 // We store the offset of the promise into the element function's
953 // hash field for element callbacks.
954 int promise_index = Smi::ToInt(element_function->GetIdentityHash()) - 1;
955
956 AppendFrame(receiver, combinator, code, promise_index, flags, parameters);
957 }
958
959 void AppendJavaScriptFrame(
960 FrameSummary::JavaScriptFrameSummary const& summary) {
961 // Filter out internal frames that we do not want to show.
962 if (!IsVisibleInStackTrace(summary.function())) {
963 skipped_prev_frame_ = true;
964 return;
965 }
966
967 int flags = 0;
968 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = summary.function();
969 if (IsStrictFrame(function)) flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsStrict;
970 if (summary.is_constructor()) flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsConstructor;
971
972 AppendFrame(Cast<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>>(summary.receiver()), function,
973 summary.abstract_code(), summary.code_offset(), flags,
974 summary.parameters());
975 }
976
977#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
978 void AppendWasmFrame(FrameSummary::WasmFrameSummary const& summary) {
979 if (summary.code()->kind() != wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFunction) return;
980 DirectHandle<WasmInstanceObject> instance = summary.wasm_instance();
981 int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsWasm;
982 if (instance->module_object()->is_asm_js()) {
983 flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsAsmJsWasm;
984 if (summary.at_to_number_conversion()) {
985 flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsAsmJsAtNumberConversion;
986 }
987 }
988
989 DirectHandle<HeapObject> code = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
990 AppendFrame(instance,
991 direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(summary.function_index()), isolate_),
992 code, summary.code_offset(), flags,
993 isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
994 }
995
996#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
997 void AppendWasmInterpretedFrame(
998 FrameSummary::WasmInterpretedFrameSummary const& summary) {
999 Handle<WasmInstanceObject> instance = summary.wasm_instance();
1000 int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsWasm | CallSiteInfo::kIsWasmInterpretedFrame;
1001 DCHECK(!instance->module_object()->is_asm_js());
1002 // We don't have any code object in the interpreter, so we pass 'undefined'.
1003 auto code = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
1004 AppendFrame(instance,
1005 handle(Smi::FromInt(summary.function_index()), isolate_), code,
1006 summary.byte_offset(), flags,
1007 isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1008 }
1009#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1010
1011 void AppendWasmInlinedFrame(
1012 FrameSummary::WasmInlinedFrameSummary const& summary) {
1013 DirectHandle<HeapObject> code = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
1014 int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsWasm;
1015 AppendFrame(summary.wasm_instance(),
1016 direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(summary.function_index()), isolate_),
1017 code, summary.code_offset(), flags,
1018 isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1019 }
1020
1021 void AppendBuiltinFrame(FrameSummary::BuiltinFrameSummary const& summary) {
1022 Builtin builtin = summary.builtin();
1023 DirectHandle<Code> code = isolate_->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
1024 DirectHandle<Smi> function(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(builtin)),
1025 isolate_);
1026 int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsBuiltin;
1027 AppendFrame(Cast<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>>(summary.receiver()), function, code,
1028 summary.code_offset(), flags,
1029 isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1030 }
1031#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1032
1033 bool Full() { return index_ >= limit_; }
1034
1035 Handle<FixedArray> Build() {
1036 return FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate_, elements_, index_);
1037 }
1038
1039 private:
1040 // Poison stack frames below the first strict mode frame.
1041 // The stack trace API should not expose receivers and function
1042 // objects on frames deeper than the top-most one with a strict mode
1043 // function.
1044 bool IsStrictFrame(DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
1045 if (!encountered_strict_function_) {
1046 encountered_strict_function_ =
1047 is_strict(function->shared()->language_mode());
1048 }
1049 return encountered_strict_function_;
1050 }
1051
1052 // Determines whether the given stack frame should be displayed in a stack
1053 // trace.
1054 bool IsVisibleInStackTrace(DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
1055 return ShouldIncludeFrame(function) && IsNotHidden(function);
1056 }
1057
1058 // This mechanism excludes a number of uninteresting frames from the stack
1059 // trace. This can be be the first frame (which will be a builtin-exit frame
1060 // for the error constructor builtin) or every frame until encountering a
1061 // user-specified function.
1062 bool ShouldIncludeFrame(DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
1063 switch (mode_) {
1064 case SKIP_NONE:
1065 return true;
1066 case SKIP_FIRST:
1067 if (!skip_next_frame_) return true;
1068 skip_next_frame_ = false;
1069 return false;
1070 case SKIP_UNTIL_SEEN:
1071 if (skip_next_frame_ && (*function == *caller_)) {
1072 skip_next_frame_ = false;
1073 return false;
1074 }
1075 return !skip_next_frame_;
1076 }
1077 UNREACHABLE();
1078 }
1079
1080 bool IsNotHidden(DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
1081 // TODO(szuend): Remove this check once the flag is enabled
1082 // by default.
1083 if (!v8_flags.experimental_stack_trace_frames &&
1084 function->shared()->IsApiFunction()) {
1085 return false;
1086 }
1087 // Functions defined not in user scripts are not visible unless directly
1088 // exposed, in which case the native flag is set.
1089 // The --builtins-in-stack-traces command line flag allows including
1090 // internal call sites in the stack trace for debugging purposes.
1091 if (!v8_flags.builtins_in_stack_traces &&
1092 !function->shared()->IsUserJavaScript()) {
1093 return function->shared()->native() ||
1094 function->shared()->IsApiFunction();
1095 }
1096 return true;
1097 }
1098
1099 void AppendFrame(DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>> receiver_or_instance,
1100 DirectHandle<UnionOf<Smi, JSFunction>> function,
1101 DirectHandle<HeapObject> code, int offset, int flags,
1102 DirectHandle<FixedArray> parameters) {
1103 if (IsTheHole(*receiver_or_instance, isolate_)) {
1104 // TODO(jgruber): Fix all cases in which frames give us a hole value
1105 // (e.g. the receiver in RegExp constructor frames).
1106 receiver_or_instance = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
1107 }
1108 auto info = isolate_->factory()->NewCallSiteInfo(
1109 Cast<JSAny>(receiver_or_instance), function, code, offset, flags,
1110 parameters);
1111 elements_ = FixedArray::SetAndGrow(isolate_, elements_, index_++, info);
1112 skipped_prev_frame_ = false;
1113 }
1114
1115 Isolate* isolate_;
1116 const FrameSkipMode mode_;
1117 int index_ = 0;
1118 const int limit_;
1119 const Handle<Object> caller_;
1120 bool skip_next_frame_;
1121 bool skipped_prev_frame_ = false;
1122 bool encountered_strict_function_ = false;
1123 Handle<FixedArray> elements_;
1124};
1125
1126void CaptureAsyncStackTrace(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
1127 CallSiteBuilder* builder) {
1128 while (!builder->Full()) {
1129 // Check that the {promise} is not settled.
1130 if (promise->status() != Promise::kPending) return;
1131
1132 // Check that we have exactly one PromiseReaction on the {promise}.
1133 if (!IsPromiseReaction(promise->reactions())) return;
1134 DirectHandle<PromiseReaction> reaction(
1135 Cast<PromiseReaction>(promise->reactions()), isolate);
1136 if (!IsSmi(reaction->next())) return;
1137
1138 Handle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object;
1139
1140 if (TryGetAsyncGenerator(isolate, reaction).ToHandle(&generator_object)) {
1141 CHECK(generator_object->is_suspended());
1142
1143 // Append async frame corresponding to the {generator_object}.
1144 builder->AppendAsyncFrame(generator_object);
1145
1146 // Try to continue from here.
1147 if (IsJSAsyncFunctionObject(*generator_object)) {
1148 auto async_function_object =
1149 Cast<JSAsyncFunctionObject>(generator_object);
1150 promise = direct_handle(async_function_object->promise(), isolate);
1151 } else {
1152 auto async_generator_object =
1153 Cast<JSAsyncGeneratorObject>(generator_object);
1154 if (IsUndefined(async_generator_object->queue(), isolate)) return;
1155 DirectHandle<AsyncGeneratorRequest> async_generator_request(
1156 Cast<AsyncGeneratorRequest>(async_generator_object->queue()),
1157 isolate);
1158 promise = direct_handle(
1159 Cast<JSPromise>(async_generator_request->promise()), isolate);
1160 }
1161 } else if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler(),
1162 Builtin::kPromiseAllResolveElementClosure)) {
1163 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(
1164 Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler()), isolate);
1165 DirectHandle<Context> context(function->context(), isolate);
1166 DirectHandle<JSFunction> combinator(
1167 context->native_context()->promise_all(), isolate);
1168 builder->AppendPromiseCombinatorFrame(function, combinator);
1169
1170 if (IsNativeContext(*context)) {
1171 // NativeContext is used as a marker that the closure was already
1172 // called. We can't access the reject element context any more.
1173 return;
1174 }
1175
1176 // Now peek into the Promise.all() resolve element context to
1177 // find the promise capability that's being resolved when all
1178 // the concurrent promises resolve.
1179 int const index =
1180 PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseAllResolveElementCapabilitySlot;
1181 DirectHandle<PromiseCapability> capability(
1182 Cast<PromiseCapability>(context->get(index)), isolate);
1183 if (!IsJSPromise(capability->promise())) return;
1184 promise = direct_handle(Cast<JSPromise>(capability->promise()), isolate);
1185 } else if (IsBuiltinFunction(
1186 isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler(),
1187 Builtin::kPromiseAllSettledResolveElementClosure)) {
1188 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(
1189 Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler()), isolate);
1190 DirectHandle<Context> context(function->context(), isolate);
1191 DirectHandle<JSFunction> combinator(
1192 context->native_context()->promise_all_settled(), isolate);
1193 builder->AppendPromiseCombinatorFrame(function, combinator);
1194
1195 if (IsNativeContext(*context)) {
1196 // NativeContext is used as a marker that the closure was already
1197 // called. We can't access the reject element context any more.
1198 return;
1199 }
1200
1201 // Now peek into the Promise.allSettled() resolve element context to
1202 // find the promise capability that's being resolved when all
1203 // the concurrent promises resolve.
1204 int const index =
1205 PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseAllResolveElementCapabilitySlot;
1206 DirectHandle<PromiseCapability> capability(
1207 Cast<PromiseCapability>(context->get(index)), isolate);
1208 if (!IsJSPromise(capability->promise())) return;
1209 promise = direct_handle(Cast<JSPromise>(capability->promise()), isolate);
1210 } else if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, reaction->reject_handler(),
1211 Builtin::kPromiseAnyRejectElementClosure)) {
1212 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(
1213 Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->reject_handler()), isolate);
1214 DirectHandle<Context> context(function->context(), isolate);
1215 DirectHandle<JSFunction> combinator(
1216 context->native_context()->promise_any(), isolate);
1217 builder->AppendPromiseCombinatorFrame(function, combinator);
1218
1219 if (IsNativeContext(*context)) {
1220 // NativeContext is used as a marker that the closure was already
1221 // called. We can't access the reject element context any more.
1222 return;
1223 }
1224
1225 // Now peek into the Promise.any() reject element context to
1226 // find the promise capability that's being resolved when any of
1227 // the concurrent promises resolve.
1228 int const index = PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseAnyRejectElementCapabilitySlot;
1229 DirectHandle<PromiseCapability> capability(
1230 Cast<PromiseCapability>(context->get(index)), isolate);
1231 if (!IsJSPromise(capability->promise())) return;
1232 promise = direct_handle(Cast<JSPromise>(capability->promise()), isolate);
1233 } else if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler(),
1234 Builtin::kPromiseCapabilityDefaultResolve)) {
1235 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(
1236 Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler()), isolate);
1237 DirectHandle<Context> context(function->context(), isolate);
1238 promise = direct_handle(
1239 Cast<JSPromise>(context->get(PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseSlot)),
1240 isolate);
1241 } else {
1242 // We have some generic promise chain here, so try to
1243 // continue with the chained promise on the reaction
1244 // (only works for native promise chains).
1245 Handle<HeapObject> promise_or_capability(
1246 reaction->promise_or_capability(), isolate);
1247 if (IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
1248 promise = Cast<JSPromise>(promise_or_capability);
1249 } else if (IsPromiseCapability(*promise_or_capability)) {
1250 auto capability = Cast<PromiseCapability>(promise_or_capability);
1251 if (!IsJSPromise(capability->promise())) return;
1252 promise =
1253 direct_handle(Cast<JSPromise>(capability->promise()), isolate);
1254 } else {
1255 // Otherwise the {promise_or_capability} must be undefined here.
1256 CHECK(IsUndefined(*promise_or_capability, isolate));
1257 return;
1258 }
1259 }
1260 }
1261}
1262
1263MaybeHandle<JSPromise> TryGetCurrentTaskPromise(Isolate* isolate) {
1264 Handle<Object> current_microtask = isolate->factory()->current_microtask();
1265 if (IsPromiseReactionJobTask(*current_microtask)) {
1266 auto promise_reaction_job_task =
1267 Cast<PromiseReactionJobTask>(current_microtask);
1268 // Check if the {reaction} has one of the known async function or
1269 // async generator continuations as its fulfill handler.
1270 if (IsBuiltinAsyncFulfillHandler(isolate,
1271 promise_reaction_job_task->handler()) ||
1272 IsBuiltinAsyncRejectHandler(isolate,
1273 promise_reaction_job_task->handler())) {
1274 // Now peek into the handlers' AwaitContext to get to
1275 // the JSGeneratorObject for the async function.
1276 DirectHandle<Context> context(
1277 Cast<JSFunction>(promise_reaction_job_task->handler())->context(),
1278 isolate);
1279 Handle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object(
1280 Cast<JSGeneratorObject>(context->extension()), isolate);
1281 if (generator_object->is_executing()) {
1282 if (IsJSAsyncFunctionObject(*generator_object)) {
1283 auto async_function_object =
1284 Cast<JSAsyncFunctionObject>(generator_object);
1285 Handle<JSPromise> promise(async_function_object->promise(), isolate);
1286 return promise;
1287 } else {
1288 auto async_generator_object =
1289 Cast<JSAsyncGeneratorObject>(generator_object);
1290 DirectHandle<Object> queue(async_generator_object->queue(), isolate);
1291 if (!IsUndefined(*queue, isolate)) {
1292 auto async_generator_request = Cast<AsyncGeneratorRequest>(queue);
1293 Handle<JSPromise> promise(
1294 Cast<JSPromise>(async_generator_request->promise()), isolate);
1295 return promise;
1296 }
1297 }
1298 }
1299 } else {
1300#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1301 DirectHandle<WasmSuspenderObject> suspender;
1302 if (TryGetWasmSuspender(isolate, promise_reaction_job_task->handler())
1303 .ToHandle(&suspender)) {
1304 // The {promise_reaction_job_task} belongs to a suspended Wasm stack
1305 return handle(suspender->promise(), isolate);
1306 }
1307#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1308
1309 // The {promise_reaction_job_task} doesn't belong to an await (or
1310 // yield inside an async generator) or a suspended Wasm stack,
1311 // but we might still be able to find an async frame if we follow
1312 // along the chain of promises on the {promise_reaction_job_task}.
1313 Handle<HeapObject> promise_or_capability(
1314 promise_reaction_job_task->promise_or_capability(), isolate);
1315 if (IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
1316 Handle<JSPromise> promise = Cast<JSPromise>(promise_or_capability);
1317 return promise;
1318 }
1319 }
1320 }
1321 return MaybeHandle<JSPromise>();
1322}
1323
1324void CaptureAsyncStackTrace(Isolate* isolate, CallSiteBuilder* builder) {
1325 DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise;
1326 if (TryGetCurrentTaskPromise(isolate).ToHandle(&promise)) {
1327 CaptureAsyncStackTrace(isolate, promise, builder);
1328 }
1329}
1330
1331template <typename Visitor>
1332void VisitStack(Isolate* isolate, Visitor* visitor,
1333 StackTrace::StackTraceOptions options = StackTrace::kDetailed) {
1334 DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
1335 // Keep track if we visited a stack frame, but did not visit any summarized
1336 // frames. Either because the stack frame didn't create any summarized frames
1337 // or due to security origin.
1338 bool skipped_last_frame = true;
1339 for (StackFrameIterator it(isolate); !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
1340 StackFrame* frame = it.frame();
1341 switch (frame->type()) {
1342 case StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT:
1343 case StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT:
1344 case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION:
1345 case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_WITH_CATCH:
1346 case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS:
1347 case StackFrame::MAGLEV:
1348 case StackFrame::INTERPRETED:
1349 case StackFrame::BASELINE:
1350 case StackFrame::BUILTIN:
1351#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1352 case StackFrame::STUB:
1353 case StackFrame::WASM:
1354 case StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START:
1355#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1356 case StackFrame::WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY:
1357#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1358#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1359 {
1360 // A standard frame may include many summarized frames (due to
1361 // inlining).
1362 FrameSummaries summaries = CommonFrame::cast(frame)->Summarize();
1363 if (summaries.top_frame_is_construct_call && !skipped_last_frame) {
1364 visitor->SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall();
1365 }
1366 skipped_last_frame = true;
1367 for (auto summary = summaries.frames.rbegin();
1368 summary != summaries.frames.rend(); ++summary) {
1369 // Skip frames from other origins when asked to do so.
1370 if (!(options & StackTrace::kExposeFramesAcrossSecurityOrigins) &&
1371 !summary->native_context()->HasSameSecurityTokenAs(
1372 isolate->context())) {
1373 continue;
1374 }
1375 if (!visitor->Visit(*summary)) return;
1376 skipped_last_frame = false;
1377 }
1378 break;
1379 }
1380
1381 default:
1382 break;
1383 }
1384 }
1385}
1386
1387Handle<FixedArray> CaptureSimpleStackTrace(Isolate* isolate, int limit,
1388 FrameSkipMode mode,
1389 Handle<Object> caller) {
1390 TRACE_EVENT_BEGIN1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__,
1391 "maxFrameCount", limit);
1392
1393#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1394 wasm::WasmCodeRefScope code_ref_scope;
1395#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1396
1397 CallSiteBuilder builder(isolate, mode, limit, caller);
1398 VisitStack(isolate, &builder);
1399
1400 // If --async-stack-traces are enabled and the "current microtask" is a
1401 // PromiseReactionJobTask, we try to enrich the stack trace with async
1402 // frames.
1403 if (v8_flags.async_stack_traces) {
1404 CaptureAsyncStackTrace(isolate, &builder);
1405 }
1406
1407 Handle<FixedArray> stack_trace = builder.Build();
1408 TRACE_EVENT_END1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__,
1409 "frameCount", stack_trace->length());
1410 return stack_trace;
1411}
1412
1413Handle<StackTraceInfo> GetDetailedStackTraceFromCallSiteInfos(
1414 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<FixedArray> call_site_infos, int limit) {
1415 auto frames = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1416 std::min(limit, call_site_infos->length()));
1417 int index = 0;
1418 for (int i = 0; i < call_site_infos->length() && index < limit; ++i) {
1419 DirectHandle<CallSiteInfo> call_site_info(
1420 Cast<CallSiteInfo>(call_site_infos->get(i)), isolate);
1421 if (call_site_info->IsAsync()) {
1422 break;
1423 }
1424 DirectHandle<Script> script;
1425 if (!CallSiteInfo::GetScript(isolate, call_site_info).ToHandle(&script) ||
1426 !script->IsSubjectToDebugging()) {
1427 continue;
1428 }
1429 DirectHandle<StackFrameInfo> stack_frame_info =
1430 isolate->factory()->NewStackFrameInfo(
1431 script, CallSiteInfo::GetSourcePosition(call_site_info),
1432 CallSiteInfo::GetFunctionDebugName(call_site_info),
1433 IsConstructor(*call_site_info));
1434 frames->set(index++, *stack_frame_info);
1435 }
1436 frames = FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, frames, index);
1437 return isolate->factory()->NewStackTraceInfo(frames);
1438}
1439
1440} // namespace
1441
1442MaybeHandle<JSObject> Isolate::CaptureAndSetErrorStack(
1443 Handle<JSObject> error_object, FrameSkipMode mode, Handle<Object> caller) {
1444 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__);
1445 Handle<UnionOf<Undefined, FixedArray>> call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack =
1446 factory()->undefined_value();
1447
1448 // Capture the "simple stack trace" for the error.stack property,
1449 // which can be disabled by setting Error.stackTraceLimit to a non
1450 // number value or simply deleting the property. If the inspector
1451 // is active, and requests more stack frames than the JavaScript
1452 // program itself, we collect up to the maximum.
1453 int stack_trace_limit = 0;
1454 if (GetStackTraceLimit(this, &stack_trace_limit)) {
1455 int limit = stack_trace_limit;
1456 if (capture_stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_ &&
1457 !(stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_options_ &
1458 StackTrace::kExposeFramesAcrossSecurityOrigins)) {
1459 // Collect up to the maximum of what the JavaScript program and
1460 // the inspector want. There's a special case here where the API
1461 // can ask the stack traces to also include cross-origin frames,
1462 // in which case we collect a separate trace below. Note that
1463 // the inspector doesn't use this option, so we could as well
1464 // just deprecate this in the future.
1465 if (limit < stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_) {
1466 limit = stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_;
1467 }
1468 }
1469 call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack =
1470 CaptureSimpleStackTrace(this, limit, mode, caller);
1471 }
1472 DirectHandle<Object> error_stack = call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack;
1473
1474 // Next is the inspector part: Depending on whether we got a "simple
1475 // stack trace" above and whether that's usable (meaning the API
1476 // didn't request to include cross-origin frames), we remember the
1477 // cap for the stack trace (either a positive limit indicating that
1478 // the Error.stackTraceLimit value was below what was requested via
1479 // the API, or a negative limit to indicate the opposite), or we
1480 // collect a "detailed stack trace" eagerly and stash that away.
1481 if (capture_stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_) {
1482 DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace;
1483 if (IsUndefined(*call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack, this) ||
1484 (stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_options_ &
1485 StackTrace::kExposeFramesAcrossSecurityOrigins)) {
1486 stack_trace = CaptureDetailedStackTrace(
1487 stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_,
1488 stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_options_);
1489 } else {
1490 auto call_site_infos =
1491 Cast<FixedArray>(call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack);
1492 stack_trace = GetDetailedStackTraceFromCallSiteInfos(
1493 this, call_site_infos,
1494 stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_);
1495 if (stack_trace_limit < call_site_infos->length()) {
1496 call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack = FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(
1497 this, call_site_infos, stack_trace_limit);
1498 }
1499 // Notify the debugger.
1500 OnStackTraceCaptured(stack_trace);
1501 }
1502 error_stack = factory()->NewErrorStackData(
1503 call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack, stack_trace);
1504 }
1505
1506 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1507 this,
1508 Object::SetProperty(this, error_object, factory()->error_stack_symbol(),
1509 error_stack, StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
1510 Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError)));
1511 return error_object;
1512}
1513
1514Handle<StackTraceInfo> Isolate::GetDetailedStackTrace(
1515 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> maybe_error_object) {
1516 ErrorUtils::StackPropertyLookupResult lookup =
1517 ErrorUtils::GetErrorStackProperty(this, maybe_error_object);
1518 if (!IsErrorStackData(*lookup.error_stack)) return {};
1519 return handle(Cast<ErrorStackData>(lookup.error_stack)->stack_trace(), this);
1520}
1521
1522Handle<FixedArray> Isolate::GetSimpleStackTrace(
1523 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> maybe_error_object) {
1524 ErrorUtils::StackPropertyLookupResult lookup =
1525 ErrorUtils::GetErrorStackProperty(this, maybe_error_object);
1526
1527 if (IsFixedArray(*lookup.error_stack)) {
1528 return Cast<FixedArray>(lookup.error_stack);
1529 }
1530 if (!IsErrorStackData(*lookup.error_stack)) {
1531 return factory()->empty_fixed_array();
1532 }
1533 auto error_stack_data = Cast<ErrorStackData>(lookup.error_stack);
1534 if (!error_stack_data->HasCallSiteInfos()) {
1535 return factory()->empty_fixed_array();
1536 }
1537 return handle(error_stack_data->call_site_infos(), this);
1538}
1539
1540Address Isolate::GetAbstractPC(int* line, int* column) {
1541 JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(this);
1542
1543 if (it.done()) {
1544 *line = -1;
1545 *column = -1;
1546 return kNullAddress;
1547 }
1548 JavaScriptFrame* frame = it.frame();
1549 DCHECK(!frame->is_builtin());
1550
1551 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(frame->function()->shared(), this);
1552 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(this, shared);
1553 int position = frame->position();
1554
1555 Tagged<Object> maybe_script = frame->function()->shared()->script();
1556 if (IsScript(maybe_script)) {
1557 DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(maybe_script), this);
1558 Script::PositionInfo info;
1559 Script::GetPositionInfo(script, position, &info);
1560 *line = info.line + 1;
1561 *column = info.column + 1;
1562 } else {
1563 *line = position;
1564 *column = -1;
1565 }
1566
1567 if (frame->is_unoptimized()) {
1568 UnoptimizedJSFrame* iframe = static_cast<UnoptimizedJSFrame*>(frame);
1569 Address bytecode_start =
1570 iframe->GetBytecodeArray()->GetFirstBytecodeAddress();
1571 return bytecode_start + iframe->GetBytecodeOffset();
1572 }
1573
1574 return frame->pc();
1575}
1576
1577namespace {
1578
1579class StackFrameBuilder {
1580 public:
1581 StackFrameBuilder(Isolate* isolate, int limit)
1582 : isolate_(isolate),
1583 frames_(isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array()),
1584 index_(0),
1585 limit_(limit) {}
1586
1587 void SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall() {
1588 // Nothing to do.
1589 }
1590
1591 bool Visit(FrameSummary& summary) {
1592 // Check if we have enough capacity left.
1593 if (index_ >= limit_) return false;
1594 // Skip frames that aren't subject to debugging.
1595 if (!summary.is_subject_to_debugging()) return true;
1596 DirectHandle<StackFrameInfo> frame = summary.CreateStackFrameInfo();
1597 frames_ = FixedArray::SetAndGrow(isolate_, frames_, index_++, frame);
1598 return true;
1599 }
1600
1601 Handle<FixedArray> Build() {
1602 return FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate_, frames_, index_);
1603 }
1604
1605 private:
1606 Isolate* isolate_;
1607 Handle<FixedArray> frames_;
1608 int index_;
1609 int limit_;
1610};
1611
1612} // namespace
1613
1614Handle<StackTraceInfo> Isolate::CaptureDetailedStackTrace(
1615 int limit, StackTrace::StackTraceOptions options) {
1616 TRACE_EVENT_BEGIN1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__,
1617 "maxFrameCount", limit);
1618 StackFrameBuilder builder(this, limit);
1619 VisitStack(this, &builder, options);
1620 auto frames = builder.Build();
1621 TRACE_EVENT_END1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__,
1622 "frameCount", frames->length());
1623 auto stack_trace = factory()->NewStackTraceInfo(frames);
1624 OnStackTraceCaptured(stack_trace);
1625 return stack_trace;
1626}
1627
1628namespace {
1629
1630class CurrentScriptNameStackVisitor {
1631 public:
1632 explicit CurrentScriptNameStackVisitor(Isolate* isolate)
1633 : isolate_(isolate) {}
1634
1635 void SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall() {
1636 // Nothing to do.
1637 }
1638
1639 bool Visit(FrameSummary& summary) {
1640 // Skip frames that aren't subject to debugging. Keep this in sync with
1641 // StackFrameBuilder::Visit so both visitors visit the same frames.
1642 if (!summary.is_subject_to_debugging()) return true;
1643
1644 // Frames that are subject to debugging always have a valid script object.
1645 auto script = Cast<Script>(summary.script());
1646 Handle<Object> name_or_url_obj(script->GetNameOrSourceURL(), isolate_);
1647 if (!IsString(*name_or_url_obj)) return true;
1648
1649 auto name_or_url = Cast<String>(name_or_url_obj);
1650 if (!name_or_url->length()) return true;
1651
1652 name_or_url_ = name_or_url;
1653 return false;
1654 }
1655
1656 Handle<String> CurrentScriptNameOrSourceURL() const { return name_or_url_; }
1657
1658 private:
1659 Isolate* const isolate_;
1660 Handle<String> name_or_url_;
1661};
1662
1663class CurrentScriptStackVisitor {
1664 public:
1665 void SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall() {
1666 // Nothing to do.
1667 }
1668
1669 bool Visit(FrameSummary& summary) {
1670 // Skip frames that aren't subject to debugging. Keep this in sync with
1671 // StackFrameBuilder::Visit so both visitors visit the same frames.
1672 if (!summary.is_subject_to_debugging()) return true;
1673
1674 // Frames that are subject to debugging always have a valid script object.
1675 current_script_ = Cast<Script>(summary.script());
1676 return false;
1677 }
1678
1679 MaybeHandle<Script> CurrentScript() const { return current_script_; }
1680
1681 private:
1682 MaybeHandle<Script> current_script_;
1683};
1684
1685} // namespace
1686
1687Handle<String> Isolate::CurrentScriptNameOrSourceURL() {
1688 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__);
1689 CurrentScriptNameStackVisitor visitor(this);
1690 VisitStack(this, &visitor);
1691 return visitor.CurrentScriptNameOrSourceURL();
1692}
1693
1694MaybeHandle<Script> Isolate::CurrentReferrerScript() {
1695 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__);
1696 CurrentScriptStackVisitor visitor{};
1697 VisitStack(this, &visitor);
1698 DirectHandle<Script> script;
1699 if (!visitor.CurrentScript().ToHandle(&script)) {
1700 return MaybeHandle<Script>();
1701 }
1702 return handle(script->GetEvalOrigin(), this);
1703}
1704
1705bool Isolate::GetStackTraceLimit(Isolate* isolate, int* result) {
1706 if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) return false;
1707 DirectHandle<JSObject> error = isolate->error_function();
1708
1709 DirectHandle<String> key = isolate->factory()->stackTraceLimit_string();
1710 DirectHandle<Object> stack_trace_limit =
1711 JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(isolate, error, key);
1712 if (!IsNumber(*stack_trace_limit)) return false;
1713
1714 // Ensure that limit is not negative.
1715 *result = std::max(
1716 FastD2IChecked(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*stack_trace_limit))), 0);
1717
1718 if (*result != v8_flags.stack_trace_limit) {
1719 isolate->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kErrorStackTraceLimit);
1720 }
1721
1722 return true;
1723}
1724
1725void Isolate::PrintStack(FILE* out, PrintStackMode mode) {
1726 if (stack_trace_nesting_level_ == 0) {
1727 stack_trace_nesting_level_++;
1728 StringStream::ClearMentionedObjectCache(this);
1729 HeapStringAllocator allocator;
1730 StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
1731 incomplete_message_ = &accumulator;
1732 PrintStack(&accumulator, mode);
1733 accumulator.OutputToFile(out);
1734 InitializeLoggingAndCounters();
1735 accumulator.Log(this);
1736 incomplete_message_ = nullptr;
1737 stack_trace_nesting_level_ = 0;
1738 } else if (stack_trace_nesting_level_ == 1) {
1739 stack_trace_nesting_level_++;
1740 base::OS::PrintError(
1741 "\n\nAttempt to print stack while printing stack (double fault)\n");
1742 base::OS::PrintError(
1743 "If you are lucky you may find a partial stack dump on stdout.\n\n");
1744 incomplete_message_->OutputToFile(out);
1745 }
1746}
1747
1748static void PrintFrames(Isolate* isolate, StringStream* accumulator,
1749 StackFrame::PrintMode mode) {
1750 StackFrameIterator it(isolate);
1751 for (int i = 0; !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
1752 it.frame()->Print(accumulator, mode, i++);
1753 }
1754}
1755
1756void Isolate::PrintStack(StringStream* accumulator, PrintStackMode mode) {
1757 HandleScope scope(this);
1758 DCHECK(accumulator->IsMentionedObjectCacheClear(this));
1759
1760 // Avoid printing anything if there are no frames.
1761 if (c_entry_fp(thread_local_top()) == 0) return;
1762
1763 accumulator->Add(
1764 "\n==== JS stack trace =========================================\n\n");
1765 PrintFrames(this, accumulator, StackFrame::OVERVIEW);
1766 if (mode == kPrintStackVerbose) {
1767 accumulator->Add(
1768 "\n==== Details ================================================\n\n");
1769 PrintFrames(this, accumulator, StackFrame::DETAILS);
1770 accumulator->PrintMentionedObjectCache(this);
1771 }
1772 accumulator->Add("=====================\n\n");
1773}
1774
1775void Isolate::SetFailedAccessCheckCallback(
1776 v8::FailedAccessCheckCallback callback) {
1777 thread_local_top()->failed_access_check_callback_ = callback;
1778}
1779
1780MaybeHandle<Object> Isolate::ReportFailedAccessCheck(
1781 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver) {
1782 if (!thread_local_top()->failed_access_check_callback_) {
1783 THROW_NEW_ERROR(this, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNoAccess));
1784 }
1785
1786 DCHECK(IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver));
1787 DCHECK(!context().is_null());
1788
1789 // Get the data object from access check info.
1790 HandleScope scope(this);
1791 DirectHandle<Object> data;
1792 {
1793 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1794 Tagged<AccessCheckInfo> access_check_info =
1795 AccessCheckInfo::Get(this, receiver);
1796 if (access_check_info.is_null()) {
1797 no_gc.Release();
1798 THROW_NEW_ERROR(this, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNoAccess));
1799 }
1800 data = direct_handle(access_check_info->data(), this);
1801 }
1802
1803 {
1804 // Leaving JavaScript.
1805 VMState<EXTERNAL> state(this);
1806 thread_local_top()->failed_access_check_callback_(
1807 v8::Utils::ToLocal(receiver), v8::ACCESS_HAS, v8::Utils::ToLocal(data));
1808 }
1809 RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION(this, {});
1810 // Throw exception even the callback forgot to do so.
1811 THROW_NEW_ERROR(this, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNoAccess));
1812}
1813
1814bool Isolate::MayAccess(DirectHandle<NativeContext> accessing_context,
1815 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver) {
1816 DCHECK(IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver) || IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver));
1817
1818 // Check for compatibility between the security tokens in the
1819 // current lexical context and the accessed object.
1820
1821 // During bootstrapping, callback functions are not enabled yet.
1822 if (bootstrapper()->IsActive()) return true;
1823 {
1824 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1825
1826 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver)) {
1827 std::optional<Tagged<Object>> receiver_context =
1828 Cast<JSGlobalProxy>(*receiver)->GetCreationContext();
1829 if (!receiver_context) return false;
1830
1831 if (*receiver_context == *accessing_context) return true;
1832
1833 if (Cast<Context>(*receiver_context)->security_token() ==
1834 accessing_context->security_token())
1835 return true;
1836 }
1837 }
1838
1839 HandleScope scope(this);
1840 DirectHandle<Object> data;
1841 v8::AccessCheckCallback callback = nullptr;
1842 {
1843 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1844 Tagged<AccessCheckInfo> access_check_info =
1845 AccessCheckInfo::Get(this, receiver);
1846 if (access_check_info.is_null()) return false;
1847 Tagged<Object> fun_obj = access_check_info->callback();
1848 callback = v8::ToCData<v8::AccessCheckCallback, kApiAccessCheckCallbackTag>(
1849 this, fun_obj);
1850 data = direct_handle(access_check_info->data(), this);
1851 }
1852
1853 {
1854 // Leaving JavaScript.
1855 VMState<EXTERNAL> state(this);
1856 return callback(v8::Utils::ToLocal(accessing_context),
1857 v8::Utils::ToLocal(receiver), v8::Utils::ToLocal(data));
1858 }
1859}
1860
1861Tagged<Object> Isolate::StackOverflow() {
1862 // Whoever calls this method should not have overflown the stack limit by too
1863 // much. Otherwise we risk actually running out of stack space.
1864 // We allow for up to 8kB overflow, because we typically allow up to 4KB
1865 // overflow per frame in generated code, but might call through more smaller
1866 // frames until we reach this method.
1867 // If this DCHECK fails, one of the frames on the stack should be augmented by
1868 // an additional stack check.
1869#if defined(V8_USE_ADDRESS_SANITIZER) || defined(MEMORY_SANITIZER)
1870 // Allow for a bit more overflow in sanitizer builds, because C++ frames take
1871 // significantly more space there.
1872 DCHECK_GE(GetCurrentStackPosition(), stack_guard()->real_climit() - 64 * KB);
1873#elif (defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32)) && \
1874 defined(USE_SIMULATOR)
1875 // Allow for more overflow on riscv simulator, because C++ frames take more
1876 // there.
1877 DCHECK_GE(GetCurrentStackPosition(), stack_guard()->real_climit() - 12 * KB);
1878#else
1879 DCHECK_GE(GetCurrentStackPosition(), stack_guard()->real_climit() - 8 * KB);
1880#endif
1881
1882 if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
1883 FATAL("Aborting on stack overflow");
1884 }
1885
1886 DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(this);
1887 HandleScope scope(this);
1888
1889 DirectHandle<JSFunction> fun = range_error_function();
1890 DirectHandle<Object> msg = factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
1891 MessageFormatter::TemplateString(MessageTemplate::kStackOverflow));
1892 DirectHandle<Object> options = factory()->undefined_value();
1893 DirectHandle<Object> no_caller;
1894 DirectHandle<JSObject> exception;
1895 ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(
1896 this, exception,
1897 ErrorUtils::Construct(this, fun, fun, msg, options, SKIP_NONE, no_caller,
1898 ErrorUtils::StackTraceCollection::kEnabled));
1899 JSObject::AddProperty(this, exception, factory()->wasm_uncatchable_symbol(),
1900 factory()->true_value(), NONE);
1901
1902 Throw(*exception);
1903
1904#ifdef VERIFY_HEAP
1905 if (v8_flags.verify_heap && v8_flags.stress_compaction) {
1906 heap()->CollectAllGarbage(GCFlag::kNoFlags,
1907 GarbageCollectionReason::kTesting);
1908 }
1909#endif // VERIFY_HEAP
1910
1911 return ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).exception();
1912}
1913
1914Tagged<Object> Isolate::ThrowAt(DirectHandle<JSObject> exception,
1915 MessageLocation* location) {
1916 DirectHandle<Name> key_start_pos = factory()->error_start_pos_symbol();
1917 Object::SetProperty(this, exception, key_start_pos,
1918 direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(location->start_pos()), this),
1919 StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
1920 Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
1921 .Check();
1922
1923 DirectHandle<Name> key_end_pos = factory()->error_end_pos_symbol();
1924 Object::SetProperty(this, exception, key_end_pos,
1925 direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(location->end_pos()), this),
1926 StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
1927 Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
1928 .Check();
1929
1930 DirectHandle<Name> key_script = factory()->error_script_symbol();
1931 Object::SetProperty(this, exception, key_script, location->script(),
1932 StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
1933 Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
1934 .Check();
1935
1936 return Throw(*exception, location);
1937}
1938
1939Tagged<Object> Isolate::TerminateExecution() {
1940 return Throw(ReadOnlyRoots(this).termination_exception());
1941}
1942
1943void Isolate::CancelTerminateExecution() {
1944 if (!is_execution_terminating()) return;
1945 clear_internal_exception();
1946 if (try_catch_handler()) try_catch_handler()->ResetInternal();
1947}
1948
1949void Isolate::RequestInterrupt(InterruptCallback callback, void* data) {
1950 ExecutionAccess access(this);
1951 api_interrupts_queue_.push(InterruptEntry(callback, data));
1952 stack_guard()->RequestApiInterrupt();
1953}
1954
1955void Isolate::InvokeApiInterruptCallbacks() {
1956 RCS_SCOPE(this, RuntimeCallCounterId::kInvokeApiInterruptCallbacks);
1957 // Note: callback below should be called outside of execution access lock.
1958 while (true) {
1959 InterruptEntry entry;
1960 {
1961 ExecutionAccess access(this);
1962 if (api_interrupts_queue_.empty()) return;
1963 entry = api_interrupts_queue_.front();
1964 api_interrupts_queue_.pop();
1965 }
1966 VMState<EXTERNAL> state(this);
1967 HandleScope handle_scope(this);
1968 entry.first(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this), entry.second);
1969 }
1970}
1971
1972void Isolate::RequestInvalidateNoProfilingProtector() {
1973 // This request might be triggered from arbitrary thread but protector
1974 // invalidation must happen on the main thread, so use Api interrupt
1975 // to achieve that.
1976 RequestInterrupt(
1977 [](v8::Isolate* isolate, void*) {
1978 Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(isolate);
1979 if (Protectors::IsNoProfilingIntact(i_isolate)) {
1980 Protectors::InvalidateNoProfiling(i_isolate);
1981 }
1982 },
1983 nullptr);
1984}
