1986namespace {
1987
1988void ReportBootstrappingException(DirectHandle<Object> exception,
1989 MessageLocation* location) {
1990 base::OS::PrintError("Exception thrown during bootstrapping\n");
1991 if (location == nullptr || location->script().is_null()) return;
1992 // We are bootstrapping and caught an error where the location is set
1993 // and we have a script for the location.
1994 // In this case we could have an extension (or an internal error
1995 // somewhere) and we print out the line number at which the error occurred
1996 // to the console for easier debugging.
1997 int line_number =
1998 location->script()->GetLineNumber(location->start_pos()) + 1;
1999 if (IsString(*exception) && IsString(location->script()->name())) {
2000 base::OS::PrintError(
2001 "Extension or internal compilation error: %s in %s at line %d.\n",
2002 Cast<String>(*exception)->ToCString().get(),
2003 Cast<String>(location->script()->name())->ToCString().get(),
2004 line_number);
2005 } else if (IsString(location->script()->name())) {
2006 base::OS::PrintError(
2007 "Extension or internal compilation error in %s at line %d.\n",
2008 Cast<String>(location->script()->name())->ToCString().get(),
2009 line_number);
2010 } else if (IsString(*exception)) {
2011 base::OS::PrintError("Extension or internal compilation error: %s.\n",
2012 Cast<String>(*exception)->ToCString().get());
2013 } else {
2014 base::OS::PrintError("Extension or internal compilation error.\n");
2015 }
2016#ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
2017 // Since comments and empty lines have been stripped from the source of
2018 // builtins, print the actual source here so that line numbers match.
2019 if (IsString(location->script()->source())) {
2020 DirectHandle<String> src(Cast<String>(location->script()->source()),
2021 location->script()->GetIsolate());
2022 PrintF("Failing script:");
2023 int len = src->length();
2024 if (len == 0) {
2025 PrintF(" <not available>\n");
2026 } else {
2027 PrintF("\n");
2028 line_number = 1;
2029 PrintF("%5d: ", line_number);
2030 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
2031 uint16_t character = src->Get(i);
2032 PrintF("%c", character);
2033 if (character == '\n' && i < len - 2) {
2034 PrintF("%5d: ", ++line_number);
2035 }
2036 }
2037 PrintF("\n");
2038 }
2039 }
2040#endif
2041}
2042
2043} // anonymous namespace
2044
2045Handle<JSMessageObject> Isolate::CreateMessageOrAbort(
2046 DirectHandle<Object> exception, MessageLocation* location) {
2047 Handle<JSMessageObject> message_obj = CreateMessage(exception, location);
2048
2049 // If the abort-on-uncaught-exception flag is specified, and if the
2050 // embedder didn't specify a custom uncaught exception callback,
2051 // or if the custom callback determined that V8 should abort, then
2052 // abort.
2053 // Cache the flag on a static so that we can modify the value looked up below
2054 // in the presence of read-only flags.
2055 static bool abort_on_uncaught_exception =
2056 v8_flags.abort_on_uncaught_exception;
2057 if (abort_on_uncaught_exception) {
2058 CatchType prediction = PredictExceptionCatcher();
2059 if ((prediction == NOT_CAUGHT || prediction == CAUGHT_BY_EXTERNAL) &&
2060 (!abort_on_uncaught_exception_callback_ ||
2061 abort_on_uncaught_exception_callback_(
2062 reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this)))) {
2063 // Prevent endless recursion.
2064 abort_on_uncaught_exception = false;
2065 // This flag is intended for use by JavaScript developers, so
2066 // print a user-friendly stack trace (not an internal one).
2067 PrintF(stderr, "%s\n\nFROM\n",
2068 MessageHandler::GetLocalizedMessage(this, message_obj).get());
2069 std::ostringstream stack_trace_stream;
2070 PrintCurrentStackTrace(stack_trace_stream);
2071 PrintF(stderr, "%s", stack_trace_stream.str().c_str());
2072 base::OS::Abort();
2073 }
2074 }
2075
2076 return message_obj;
2077}
2078
2079Tagged<Object> Isolate::Throw(Tagged<Object> raw_exception,
2080 MessageLocation* location) {
2081 DCHECK(!has_exception());
2082 DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsHole(raw_exception),
2083 raw_exception == ReadOnlyRoots{this}.termination_exception());
2084#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2085 trap_handler::AssertThreadNotInWasm();
2086#endif
2087
2088 HandleScope scope(this);
2089 DirectHandle<Object> exception(raw_exception, this);
2090
2091 if (v8_flags.print_all_exceptions) {
2092 PrintF("=========================================================\n");
2093 PrintF("Exception thrown:\n");
2094 if (location) {
2095 DirectHandle<Script> script = location->script();
2096 DirectHandle<Object> name(script->GetNameOrSourceURL(), this);
2097 PrintF("at ");
2098 if (IsString(*name) && Cast<String>(*name)->length() > 0) {
2099 Cast<String>(*name)->PrintOn(stdout);
2100 } else {
2101 PrintF("<anonymous>");
2102 }
2103// Script::GetLineNumber and Script::GetColumnNumber can allocate on the heap to
2104// initialize the line_ends array, so be careful when calling them.
2105#ifdef DEBUG
2106 if (AllowGarbageCollection::IsAllowed()) {
2107#else
2108 if ((false)) {
2109#endif
2110 Script::PositionInfo start_pos;
2111 Script::PositionInfo end_pos;
2112 Script::GetPositionInfo(script, location->start_pos(), &start_pos);
2113 Script::GetPositionInfo(script, location->end_pos(), &end_pos);
2114 PrintF(", %d:%d - %d:%d\n", start_pos.line + 1, start_pos.column + 1,
2115 end_pos.line + 1, end_pos.column + 1);
2116 } else {
2117 PrintF(", line %d\n", script->GetLineNumber(location->start_pos()) + 1);
2118 }
2119 }
2120 Print(*exception);
2121 PrintF("Stack Trace:\n");
2122 PrintStack(stdout);
2123 PrintF("=========================================================\n");
2124 }
2125
2126 // Determine whether a message needs to be created for the given exception
2127 // depending on the following criteria:
2128 // 1) External v8::TryCatch missing: Always create a message because any
2129 // JavaScript handler for a finally-block might re-throw to top-level.
2130 // 2) External v8::TryCatch exists: Only create a message if the handler
2131 // captures messages or is verbose (which reports despite the catch).
2132 // 3) ReThrow from v8::TryCatch: The message from a previous throw still
2133 // exists and we preserve it instead of creating a new message.
2134 bool requires_message = try_catch_handler() == nullptr ||
2135 try_catch_handler()->is_verbose_ ||
2136 try_catch_handler()->capture_message_;
2137 bool rethrowing_message = thread_local_top()->rethrowing_message_;
2138
2139 thread_local_top()->rethrowing_message_ = false;
2140
2141 // Notify debugger of exception.
2142 if (is_catchable_by_javascript(*exception)) {
2143 std::optional<Tagged<Object>> maybe_exception = debug()->OnThrow(exception);
2144 if (maybe_exception.has_value()) {
2145 return *maybe_exception;
2146 }
2147 }
2148
2149 // Generate the message if required.
2150 if (requires_message && !rethrowing_message) {
2151 MessageLocation computed_location;
2152 // If no location was specified we try to use a computed one instead.
2153 if (location == nullptr && ComputeLocation(&computed_location)) {
2154 location = &computed_location;
2155 }
2156 if (bootstrapper()->IsActive()) {
2157 // It's not safe to try to make message objects or collect stack traces
2158 // while the bootstrapper is active since the infrastructure may not have
2159 // been properly initialized.
2160 ReportBootstrappingException(exception, location);
2161 } else {
2162 DirectHandle<Object> message_obj =
2163 CreateMessageOrAbort(exception, location);
2164 set_pending_message(*message_obj);
2165 }
2166 }
2167
2168 // Set the exception being thrown.
2169 set_exception(*exception);
2170 PropagateExceptionToExternalTryCatch(TopExceptionHandlerType(*exception));
2171
2172 if (v8_flags.experimental_report_exceptions_from_callbacks &&
2173 exception_propagation_callback_ && !rethrowing_message &&
2174 !preprocessing_exception_) {
2175 // Don't preprocess exceptions that might happen inside
2176 // |exception_propagation_callback_|.
2177 preprocessing_exception_ = true;
2178 NotifyExceptionPropagationCallback();
2179 preprocessing_exception_ = false;
2180 }
2181 return ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).exception();
2182}
2183
2184Tagged<Object> Isolate::ReThrow(Tagged<Object> exception) {
2185 DCHECK(!has_exception());
2186
2187 // Set the exception being re-thrown.
2188 set_exception(exception);
2189 return ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).exception();
2190}
2191
2192Tagged<Object> Isolate::ReThrow(Tagged<Object> exception,
2193 Tagged<Object> message) {
2194 DCHECK(!has_exception());
2195 DCHECK(!has_pending_message());
2196
2197 set_pending_message(message);
2198 return ReThrow(exception);
2199}
2200
2201namespace {
2202#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2203// This scope will set the thread-in-wasm flag after the execution of all
2204// destructors. The thread-in-wasm flag is only set when the scope gets enabled.
2205class SetThreadInWasmFlagScope {
2206 public:
2207 SetThreadInWasmFlagScope() { trap_handler::AssertThreadNotInWasm(); }
2208
2209 ~SetThreadInWasmFlagScope() {
2210 if (enabled_) trap_handler::SetThreadInWasm();
2211 }
2212
2213 void Enable() { enabled_ = true; }
2214
2215 private:
2216 bool enabled_ = false;
2217};
2218#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2219} // namespace
2220
2221Tagged<Object> Isolate::UnwindAndFindHandler() {
2222 // TODO(v8:12676): Fix gcmole failures in this function.
2223 DisableGCMole no_gcmole;
2224 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2225
2226 // The topmost_script_having_context value becomes outdated after frames
2227 // unwinding.
2228 clear_topmost_script_having_context();
2229
2230#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2231 // Create the {SetThreadInWasmFlagScope} first in this function so that its
2232 // destructor gets called after all the other destructors. It is important
2233 // that the destructor sets the thread-in-wasm flag after all other
2234 // destructors. The other destructors may cause exceptions, e.g. ASan on
2235 // Windows, which would invalidate the thread-in-wasm flag when the wasm trap
2236 // handler handles such non-wasm exceptions.
2237 SetThreadInWasmFlagScope set_thread_in_wasm_flag_scope;
2238#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2239 Tagged<Object> exception = this->exception();
2240
2241 auto FoundHandler = [&](Tagged<Context> context, Address instruction_start,
2242 intptr_t handler_offset,
2243 Address constant_pool_address, Address handler_sp,
2244 Address handler_fp, int num_frames_above_handler) {
2245 // Store information to be consumed by the CEntry.
2246 thread_local_top()->pending_handler_context_ = context;
2247 thread_local_top()->pending_handler_entrypoint_ =
2248 instruction_start + handler_offset;
2249 thread_local_top()->pending_handler_constant_pool_ = constant_pool_address;
2250 thread_local_top()->pending_handler_fp_ = handler_fp;
2251 thread_local_top()->pending_handler_sp_ = handler_sp;
2252 thread_local_top()->num_frames_above_pending_handler_ =
2253 num_frames_above_handler;
2254
2255 // Return and clear exception. The contract is that:
2256 // (1) the exception is stored in one place (no duplication), and
2257 // (2) within generated-code land, that one place is the return register.
2258 // If/when we unwind back into C++ (returning to the JSEntry stub,
2259 // or to Execution::CallWasm), the returned exception will be sent
2260 // back to isolate->set_exception(...).
2261 clear_internal_exception();
2262 return exception;
2263 };
2264
2265#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2266 auto HandleStackSwitch = [&](StackFrameIterator& iter) {
2267 if (iter.wasm_stack() == nullptr) return;
2268 auto& switch_info = iter.wasm_stack()->stack_switch_info();
2269 if (!switch_info.has_value()) return;
2270 Tagged<Object> suspender_obj = root(RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
2271 if (!IsUndefined(suspender_obj)) {
2272 // If the wasm-to-js wrapper was on a secondary stack and switched
2273 // to the central stack, handle the implicit switch back.
2274 if (switch_info.source_fp == iter.frame()->fp()) {
2275 thread_local_top()->is_on_central_stack_flag_ = false;
2276 uintptr_t limit =
2277 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(iter.wasm_stack()->jslimit());
2278 stack_guard()->SetStackLimitForStackSwitching(limit);
2279#if USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL && V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
2280 Simulator::current(this)->SetStackLimit(limit);
2281#endif
2282 iter.wasm_stack()->clear_stack_switch_info();
2283 }
2284 }
2285 };
2286#endif
2287
2288 // Special handling of termination exceptions, uncatchable by JavaScript and
2289 // Wasm code, we unwind the handlers until the top ENTRY handler is found.
2290 bool catchable_by_js = is_catchable_by_javascript(exception);
2291 if (!catchable_by_js && !context().is_null()) {
2292 // Because the array join stack will not pop the elements when throwing the
2293 // uncatchable terminate exception, we need to clear the array join stack to
2294 // avoid leaving the stack in an invalid state.
2295 // See also CycleProtectedArrayJoin.
2296 raw_native_context()->set_array_join_stack(
2297 ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
2298 }
2299
2300 // Compute handler and stack unwinding information by performing a full walk
2301 // over the stack and dispatching according to the frame type.
2302 int visited_frames = 0;
2303 for (StackFrameIterator iter(this, thread_local_top(),
2304 StackFrameIterator::NoHandles{});
2305 ; iter.Advance(), visited_frames++) {
2306#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2307 if (iter.frame()->type() == StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH) {
2308 if (catchable_by_js && iter.frame()->LookupCode()->builtin_id() !=
2309 Builtin::kJSToWasmStressSwitchStacksAsm) {
2310 Tagged<Code> code =
2311 builtins()->code(Builtin::kWasmReturnPromiseOnSuspendAsm);
2312 HandlerTable table(code);
2313 Address instruction_start =
2314 code->InstructionStart(this, iter.frame()->pc());
2315 int handler_offset = table.LookupReturn(0);
2316 return FoundHandler(Context(), instruction_start, handler_offset,
2317 kNullAddress, iter.frame()->sp(),
2318 iter.frame()->fp(), visited_frames);
2319 } else {
2320 // We reached the base of the wasm stack. Follow the chain of
2321 // continuations to find the parent stack and reset the iterator.
2322 wasm::StackMemory* stack =
2323 reinterpret_cast<wasm::StackMemory*>(iter.continuation()->stack());
2324 RetireWasmStack(stack);
2325 iter.Advance();
2326 wasm::StackMemory* parent =
2327 reinterpret_cast<wasm::StackMemory*>(iter.continuation()->stack());
2328 parent->jmpbuf()->state = wasm::JumpBuffer::Active;
2329 roots_table()
2330 .slot(RootIndex::kActiveContinuation)
2331 .store(iter.continuation());
2332 SyncStackLimit();
2333#if USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL && V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
2334 Simulator::current(this)->SetStackLimit(
2335 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(parent->jslimit()));
2336#endif
2337 continue;
2338 }
2339 }
2340#endif
2341 // Handler must exist.
2342 DCHECK(!iter.done());
2343
2344 StackFrame* frame = iter.frame();
2345
2346 // The debugger implements the "restart frame" feature by throwing a
2347 // terminate exception. Check and if we need to restart `frame`,
2348 // jump into the `RestartFrameTrampoline` builtin instead of
2349 // a catch handler.
2350 // Optimized frames take a detour via the deoptimizer before also jumping
2351 // to the `RestartFrameTrampoline` builtin.
2352 if (debug()->ShouldRestartFrame(frame->id())) {
2353 CancelTerminateExecution();
2354 CHECK(!catchable_by_js);
2355 CHECK(frame->is_javascript());
2356
2357 if (frame->is_optimized_js()) {
2358 Tagged<Code> code = frame->LookupCode();
2359 // The debugger triggers lazy deopt for the "to-be-restarted" frame
2360 // immediately when the CDP event arrives while paused.
2361 CHECK(code->marked_for_deoptimization());
2362 set_deoptimizer_lazy_throw(true);
2363
2364 // Jump directly to the optimized frames return, to immediately fall
2365 // into the deoptimizer.
2366 const int offset =
2367 static_cast<int>(frame->pc() - code->instruction_start());
2368
2369 // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2370 // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2371 // Note: Needed by the deoptimizer to rematerialize frames.
2372 Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2373 StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2374 code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize;
2375 return FoundHandler(Context(), code->instruction_start(), offset,
2376 code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2377 visited_frames);
2378 }
2379
2380 debug()->clear_restart_frame();
2381 Tagged<Code> code = *BUILTIN_CODE(this, RestartFrameTrampoline);
2382 return FoundHandler(Context(), code->instruction_start(), 0,
2383 code->constant_pool(), kNullAddress, frame->fp(),
2384 visited_frames);
2385 }
2386
2387 switch (frame->type()) {
2388 case StackFrame::ENTRY:
2389 case StackFrame::CONSTRUCT_ENTRY: {
2390 // For JSEntry frames we always have a handler.
2391 StackHandler* handler = frame->top_handler();
2392
2393 // Restore the next handler.
2394 thread_local_top()->handler_ = handler->next_address();
2395
2396 // Gather information from the handler.
2397 Tagged<Code> code = frame->LookupCode();
2398 HandlerTable table(code);
2399 return FoundHandler(Context(),
2400 code->InstructionStart(this, frame->pc()),
2401 table.LookupReturn(0), code->constant_pool(),
2402 handler->address() + StackHandlerConstants::kSize,
2403 0, visited_frames);
2404 }
2405
2406#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2407 case StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY: {
2408#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2409 if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
2410 StackHandler* handler = frame->top_handler();
2411 thread_local_top()->handler_ = handler->next_address();
2412 Tagged<Code> code =
2413 frame->LookupCode(); // WasmInterpreterCWasmEntry.
2414
2415 HandlerTable table(code);
2416 Address instruction_start = code->InstructionStart(this, frame->pc());
2417 // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2418 // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2419 Address return_sp = *reinterpret_cast<Address*>(
2420 frame->fp() + WasmInterpreterCWasmEntryConstants::kSPFPOffset);
2421 const int handler_offset = table.LookupReturn(0);
2422 if (trap_handler::IsThreadInWasm()) {
2423 trap_handler::ClearThreadInWasm();
2424 }
2425 return FoundHandler(Context(), instruction_start, handler_offset,
2426 code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2427 visited_frames);
2428 }
2429#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2430
2431 StackHandler* handler = frame->top_handler();
2432 thread_local_top()->handler_ = handler->next_address();
2433 Tagged<Code> code = frame->LookupCode();
2434 HandlerTable table(code);
2435 Address instruction_start = code->instruction_start();
2436 int return_offset = static_cast<int>(frame->pc() - instruction_start);
2437 int handler_offset = table.LookupReturn(return_offset);
2438 DCHECK_NE(-1, handler_offset);
2439 // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2440 // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2441 Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2442 StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2443 code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize;
2444 return FoundHandler(Context(), instruction_start, handler_offset,
2445 code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2446 visited_frames);
2447 }
2448
2449#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2450 case StackFrame::WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY: {
2451 if (trap_handler::IsThreadInWasm()) {
2452 trap_handler::ClearThreadInWasm();
2453 }
2454 } break;
2455#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2456
2457 case StackFrame::WASM:
2458 case StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START: {
2459 if (!is_catchable_by_wasm(exception)) break;
2460
2461 WasmFrame* wasm_frame = static_cast<WasmFrame*>(frame);
2462 wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code =
2463 wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(this, frame->pc());
2464 int offset = wasm_frame->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable();
2465 if (offset < 0) break;
2466 // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2467 // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2468 // The stack slot count needs to be adjusted for Liftoff frames. It has
2469 // two components: the fixed frame slots, and the maximum number of
2470 // registers pushed on top of the frame in out-of-line code. We know
2471 // that we are not currently in an OOL call, because OOL calls don't
2472 // have exception handlers. So we subtract the OOL spill count from the
2473 // total stack slot count to compute the actual frame size:
2474 int stack_slots = wasm_code->stack_slots() - wasm_code->ool_spills();
2475 Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2476 StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2477 stack_slots * kSystemPointerSize;
2478
2479#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2480 // Transitioning from JS To Wasm.
2481 if (v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms &&
2482 v8_flags.slow_histograms && !v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
2483 // Start measuring the time spent running Wasm for jitted Wasm.
2484 wasm_execution_timer()->Start();
2485 }
2486#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2487
2488 // This is going to be handled by WebAssembly, so we need to set the TLS
2489 // flag. The {SetThreadInWasmFlagScope} will set the flag after all
2490 // destructors have been executed.
2491 set_thread_in_wasm_flag_scope.Enable();
2492 return FoundHandler(Context(), wasm_code->instruction_start(), offset,
2493 wasm_code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2494 visited_frames);
2495 }
2496
2497 case StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP: {
2498 // The WasmLiftoffFrameSetup builtin doesn't throw, and doesn't call
2499 // out to user code that could throw.
2500 UNREACHABLE();
2501 }
2502 case StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS:
2503 case StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION: {
2504 HandleStackSwitch(iter);
2505 break;
2506 }
2507#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2508
2509 case StackFrame::MAGLEV:
2510 case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS: {
2511 // For optimized frames we perform a lookup in the handler table.
2512 if (!catchable_by_js) break;
2513 OptimizedJSFrame* opt_frame = static_cast<OptimizedJSFrame*>(frame);
2514 int offset = opt_frame->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(nullptr, nullptr);
2515 if (offset < 0) break;
2516 // The code might be an optimized code or a turbofanned builtin.
2517 Tagged<Code> code = frame->LookupCode();
2518 // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures
2519 // that argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2520 Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2521 StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2522 code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize;
2523
2524 // TODO(bmeurer): Turbofanned BUILTIN frames appear as TURBOFAN_JS,
2525 // but do not have a code kind of TURBOFAN_JS.
2526 if (CodeKindCanDeoptimize(code->kind()) &&
2527 code->marked_for_deoptimization()) {
2528 // If the target code is lazy deoptimized, we jump to the original
2529 // return address, but we make a note that we are throwing, so
2530 // that the deoptimizer can do the right thing.
2531 offset = static_cast<int>(frame->pc() - code->instruction_start());
2532 set_deoptimizer_lazy_throw(true);
2533 }
2534
2535 return FoundHandler(
2536 Context(), code->InstructionStart(this, frame->pc()), offset,
2537 code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(), visited_frames);
2538 }
2539
2540 case StackFrame::STUB: {
2541#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2542 HandleStackSwitch(iter);
2543#endif
2544 // Some stubs are able to handle exceptions.
2545 if (!catchable_by_js) break;
2546 StubFrame* stub_frame = static_cast<StubFrame*>(frame);
2547#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2548 DCHECK_NULL(wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(this, frame->pc()));
2549#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2550
2551 // The code might be a dynamically generated stub or a turbofanned
2552 // embedded builtin.
2553 Tagged<Code> code = stub_frame->LookupCode();
2554 if (!code->is_turbofanned() || !code->has_handler_table()) {
2555 break;
2556 }
2557
2558 int offset = stub_frame->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable();
2559 if (offset < 0) break;
2560
2561 // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures
2562 // that argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2563 Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2564 StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2565 code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize;
2566
2567 return FoundHandler(
2568 Context(), code->InstructionStart(this, frame->pc()), offset,
2569 code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(), visited_frames);
2570 }
2571
2572 case StackFrame::INTERPRETED:
2573 case StackFrame::BASELINE: {
2574 // For interpreted frame we perform a range lookup in the handler table.
2575 if (!catchable_by_js) break;
2576 UnoptimizedJSFrame* js_frame = UnoptimizedJSFrame::cast(frame);
2577 int register_slots = UnoptimizedFrameConstants::RegisterStackSlotCount(
2578 js_frame->GetBytecodeArray()->register_count());
2579 int context_reg = 0; // Will contain register index holding context.
2580 int offset =
2581 js_frame->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(&context_reg, nullptr);
2582 if (offset < 0) break;
2583 // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2584 // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2585 // Note: This is only needed for interpreted frames that have been
2586 // materialized by the deoptimizer. If there is a handler frame
2587 // in between then {frame->sp()} would already be correct.
2588 Address return_sp = frame->fp() -
2589 InterpreterFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp -
2590 register_slots * kSystemPointerSize;
2591
2592 // Patch the bytecode offset in the interpreted frame to reflect the
2593 // position of the exception handler. The special builtin below will
2594 // take care of continuing to dispatch at that position. Also restore
2595 // the correct context for the handler from the interpreter register.
2596 Tagged<Context> context =
2597 Cast<Context>(js_frame->ReadInterpreterRegister(context_reg));
2598 DCHECK(IsContext(context));
2599
2600 if (frame->is_baseline()) {
2601 BaselineFrame* sp_frame = BaselineFrame::cast(js_frame);
2602 Tagged<Code> code = sp_frame->LookupCode();
2603 intptr_t pc_offset = sp_frame->GetPCForBytecodeOffset(offset);
2604 // Patch the context register directly on the frame, so that we don't
2605 // need to have a context read + write in the baseline code.
2606 sp_frame->PatchContext(context);
2607 return FoundHandler(Context(), code->instruction_start(), pc_offset,
2608 code->constant_pool(), return_sp, sp_frame->fp(),
2609 visited_frames);
2610 } else {
2611 InterpretedFrame::cast(js_frame)->PatchBytecodeOffset(
2612 static_cast<int>(offset));
2613
2614 Tagged<Code> code = *BUILTIN_CODE(this, InterpreterEnterAtBytecode);
2615 // We subtract a frame from visited_frames because otherwise the
2616 // shadow stack will drop the underlying interpreter entry trampoline
2617 // in which the handler runs.
2618 //
2619 // An interpreted frame cannot be the first frame we look at
2620 // because at a minimum, an exit frame into C++ has to separate
2621 // it and the context in which this C++ code runs.
2622 CHECK_GE(visited_frames, 1);
2623 return FoundHandler(context, code->instruction_start(), 0,
2624 code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2625 visited_frames - 1);
2626 }
2627 }
2628
2629 case StackFrame::BUILTIN:
2630 // For builtin frames we are guaranteed not to find a handler.
2631 if (catchable_by_js) {
2632 CHECK_EQ(-1, BuiltinFrame::cast(frame)->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(
2633 nullptr, nullptr));
2634 }
2635 break;
2636
2637 case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_WITH_CATCH: {
2638 // Builtin continuation frames with catch can handle exceptions.
2639 if (!catchable_by_js) break;
2640 JavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatchFrame* js_frame =
2641 JavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatchFrame::cast(frame);
2642 js_frame->SetException(exception);
2643
2644 // Reconstruct the stack pointer from the frame pointer.
2645 Address return_sp = js_frame->fp() - js_frame->GetSPToFPDelta();
2646 Tagged<Code> code = js_frame->LookupCode();
2647 return FoundHandler(Context(), code->instruction_start(), 0,
2648 code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2649 visited_frames);
2650 }
2651
2652 default:
2653 // All other types can not handle exception.
2654 break;
2655 }
2656
2657 if (frame->is_optimized_js()) {
2658 // Remove per-frame stored materialized objects.
2659 bool removed = materialized_object_store_->Remove(frame->fp());
2660 USE(removed);
2661 // If there were any materialized objects, the code should be
2662 // marked for deopt.
2663 DCHECK_IMPLIES(removed, frame->LookupCode()->marked_for_deoptimization());
2664 }
2665 }
2666
2667 UNREACHABLE();
2668} // namespace internal
2669
2670namespace {
2671
2672class StackFrameSummaryIterator {
2673 public:
2674 explicit StackFrameSummaryIterator(Isolate* isolate)
2675 : stack_iterator_(isolate), summaries_(), index_(0) {
2676 InitSummaries();
2677 }
2678 void Advance() {
2679 if (index_ == 0) {
2680 summaries_.frames.clear();
2681 stack_iterator_.Advance();
2682 InitSummaries();
2683 } else {
2684 index_--;
2685 }
2686 }
2687 bool done() const { return stack_iterator_.done(); }
2688 StackFrame* frame() const { return stack_iterator_.frame(); }
2689 bool has_frame_summary() const { return index_ < summaries_.size(); }
2690 const FrameSummary& frame_summary() const {
2691 DCHECK(has_frame_summary());
2692 return summaries_.frames[index_];
2693 }
2694 Isolate* isolate() const { return stack_iterator_.isolate(); }
2695
2696 private:
2697 void InitSummaries() {
2698 if (!done() && frame()->is_javascript()) {
2699 summaries_ = JavaScriptFrame::cast(frame())->Summarize();
2700 DCHECK_GT(summaries_.size(), 0);
2701 index_ = summaries_.size() - 1;
2702 }
2703 }
2704 StackFrameIterator stack_iterator_;
2705 FrameSummaries summaries_;
2706 int index_;
2707};
2708
2709HandlerTable::CatchPrediction CatchPredictionFor(Builtin builtin_id) {
2710 switch (builtin_id) {
2711#define CASE(Name) \
2712 case Builtin::k##Name: \
2713 return HandlerTable::PROMISE;
2714 BUILTIN_PROMISE_REJECTION_PREDICTION_LIST(CASE)
2715#undef CASE
2716 default:
2717 return HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT;
2718 }
2719}
2720
2721HandlerTable::CatchPrediction PredictExceptionFromBytecode(
2722 Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecode, int code_offset) {
2723 HandlerTable table(bytecode);
2724 int handler_index = table.LookupHandlerIndexForRange(code_offset);
2725 if (handler_index < 0) return HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT;
2726 return table.GetRangePrediction(handler_index);
2727}
2728
2729HandlerTable::CatchPrediction PredictException(const FrameSummary& summary,
2730 Isolate* isolate) {
2731 if (!summary.IsJavaScript()) {
2732 // This can happen when WASM is inlined by TurboFan. For now we ignore
2733 // frames that are not JavaScript.
2734 // TODO(https://crbug.com/349588762): We should also check Wasm code
2735 // for exception handling.
2736 return HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT;
2737 }
2738 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate);
2739 DirectHandle<AbstractCode> code = summary.AsJavaScript().abstract_code();
2740 if (code->kind(cage_base) == CodeKind::BUILTIN) {
2741 return CatchPredictionFor(code->GetCode()->builtin_id());
2742 }
2743
2744 // Must have been constructed from a bytecode array.
2745 CHECK_EQ(CodeKind::INTERPRETED_FUNCTION, code->kind(cage_base));
2746 return PredictExceptionFromBytecode(code->GetBytecodeArray(),
2747 summary.code_offset());
2748}
2749
2750HandlerTable::CatchPrediction PredictExceptionFromGenerator(
2751 DirectHandle<JSGeneratorObject> generator, Isolate* isolate) {
2752 return PredictExceptionFromBytecode(
2753 generator->function()->shared()->GetBytecodeArray(isolate),
2754 GetGeneratorBytecodeOffset(generator));
2755}
2756
2757Isolate::CatchType ToCatchType(HandlerTable::CatchPrediction prediction) {
2758 switch (prediction) {
2759 case HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT:
2760 return Isolate::NOT_CAUGHT;
2761 case HandlerTable::CAUGHT:
2762 return Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_JAVASCRIPT;
2763 case HandlerTable::PROMISE:
2764 return Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_PROMISE;
2765 case HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT:
2766 case HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT:
2767 return Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_ASYNC_AWAIT;
2768 default:
2769 UNREACHABLE();
2770 }
2771}
2772
2773Isolate::CatchType PredictExceptionCatchAtFrame(
2774 const StackFrameSummaryIterator& iterator) {
2775 const StackFrame* frame = iterator.frame();
2776 switch (frame->type()) {
2777 case StackFrame::ENTRY:
2778 case StackFrame::CONSTRUCT_ENTRY: {
2779 Address external_handler =
2780 iterator.isolate()->thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_address();
2781 Address entry_handler = frame->top_handler()->next_address();
2782 // The exception has been externally caught if and only if there is an
2783 // external handler which is on top of the top-most JS_ENTRY handler.
2784 if (external_handler != kNullAddress &&
2785 !iterator.isolate()->try_catch_handler()->IsVerbose()) {
2786 if (entry_handler == kNullAddress || entry_handler > external_handler) {
2787 return Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_EXTERNAL;
2788 }
2789 }
2790 } break;
2791
2792 // For JavaScript frames we perform a lookup in the handler table.
2793 case StackFrame::INTERPRETED:
2794 case StackFrame::BASELINE:
2795 case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS:
2796 case StackFrame::MAGLEV:
2797 case StackFrame::BUILTIN: {
2798 DCHECK(iterator.has_frame_summary());
2799 return ToCatchType(
2800 PredictException(iterator.frame_summary(), iterator.isolate()));
2801 }
2802
2803 case StackFrame::STUB: {
2804 Tagged<Code> code = *frame->LookupCode();
2805 if (code->kind() != CodeKind::BUILTIN || !code->has_handler_table() ||
2806 !code->is_turbofanned()) {
2807 break;
2808 }
2809
2810 return ToCatchType(CatchPredictionFor(code->builtin_id()));
2811 }
2812
2813 case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_WITH_CATCH: {
2814 Tagged<Code> code = *frame->LookupCode();
2815 return ToCatchType(CatchPredictionFor(code->builtin_id()));
2816 }
2817
2818 default:
2819 // All other types can not handle exception.
2820 break;
2821 }
2822 return Isolate::NOT_CAUGHT;
2823}
2824} // anonymous namespace
2825
2826Isolate::CatchType Isolate::PredictExceptionCatcher() {
2827 if (TopExceptionHandlerType(Tagged<Object>()) ==
2828 ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch) {
2829 return CAUGHT_BY_EXTERNAL;
2830 }
2831
2832 // Search for an exception handler by performing a full walk over the stack.
2833 for (StackFrameSummaryIterator iter(this); !iter.done(); iter.Advance()) {
2834 Isolate::CatchType prediction = PredictExceptionCatchAtFrame(iter);
2835 if (prediction != NOT_CAUGHT) return prediction;
2836 }
2837
2838 // Handler not found.
2839 return NOT_CAUGHT;
2840}
2841
2842Tagged<Object> Isolate::ThrowIllegalOperation() {
2843 if (v8_flags.stack_trace_on_illegal) PrintStack(stdout);
2844 return Throw(ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).illegal_access_string());
2845}
2846
2847void Isolate::PrintCurrentStackTrace(std::ostream& out) {
2848 DirectHandle<FixedArray> frames = CaptureSimpleStackTrace(
2849 this, FixedArray::kMaxLength, SKIP_NONE, factory()->undefined_value());
2850
2851 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(this);
2852 for (int i = 0; i < frames->length(); ++i) {
2853 DirectHandle<CallSiteInfo> frame(Cast<CallSiteInfo>(frames->get(i)), this);
2854 SerializeCallSiteInfo(this, frame, &builder);
2855 if (i != frames->length() - 1) builder.AppendCharacter('\n');
2856 }
2857
2858 DirectHandle<String> stack_trace = builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
2859 stack_trace->PrintOn(out);
2860}
2861
2862bool Isolate::ComputeLocation(MessageLocation* target) {
2863 DebuggableStackFrameIterator it(this);
2864 if (it.done()) return false;
2865 // Compute the location from the function and the relocation info of the
2866 // baseline code. For optimized code this will use the deoptimization
2867 // information to get canonical location information.
2868#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2869 wasm::WasmCodeRefScope code_ref_scope;
2870#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2871 FrameSummary summary = it.GetTopValidFrame();
2872 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared;
2873 Handle<Object> script = summary.script();
2874 if (!IsScript(*script) ||
2875 IsUndefined(Cast<Script>(*script)->source(), this)) {
2876 return false;
2877 }
2878
2879 if (summary.IsJavaScript()) {
2880 shared = handle(summary.AsJavaScript().function()->shared(), this);
2881 }
2882 if (summary.AreSourcePositionsAvailable()) {
2883 int pos = summary.SourcePosition();
2884 *target = MessageLocation(Cast<Script>(script), pos, pos + 1, shared);
2885 } else {
2886 *target =
2887 MessageLocation(Cast<Script>(script), shared, summary.code_offset());
2888 }
2889 return true;
2890}
2891
2892bool Isolate::ComputeLocationFromException(MessageLocation* target,
2893 DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
2894 if (!IsJSObject(*exception)) return false;
2895
2896 DirectHandle<Name> start_pos_symbol = factory()->error_start_pos_symbol();
2897 DirectHandle<Object> start_pos = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
2898 this, Cast<JSObject>(exception), start_pos_symbol);
2899 if (!IsSmi(*start_pos)) return false;
2900 int start_pos_value = Cast<Smi>(*start_pos).value();
2901
2902 DirectHandle<Name> end_pos_symbol = factory()->error_end_pos_symbol();
2903 DirectHandle<Object> end_pos = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
2904 this, Cast<JSObject>(exception), end_pos_symbol);
2905 if (!IsSmi(*end_pos)) return false;
2906 int end_pos_value = Cast<Smi>(*end_pos).value();
2907
2908 DirectHandle<Name> script_symbol = factory()->error_script_symbol();
2909 DirectHandle<Object> script = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
2910 this, Cast<JSObject>(exception), script_symbol);
2911 if (!IsScript(*script)) return false;
2912
2913 Handle<Script> cast_script(Cast<Script>(*script), this);
2914 *target = MessageLocation(cast_script, start_pos_value, end_pos_value);
2915 return true;
2916}
2917
2918bool Isolate::ComputeLocationFromSimpleStackTrace(
2919 MessageLocation* target, DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
2920 if (!IsJSReceiver(*exception)) {
2921 return false;
2922 }
2923 DirectHandle<FixedArray> call_site_infos =
2924 GetSimpleStackTrace(Cast<JSReceiver>(exception));
2925 for (int i = 0; i < call_site_infos->length(); ++i) {
2926 DirectHandle<CallSiteInfo> call_site_info(
2927 Cast<CallSiteInfo>(call_site_infos->get(i)), this);
2928 if (CallSiteInfo::ComputeLocation(call_site_info, target)) {
2929 return true;
2930 }
2931 }
2932 return false;
2933}
2934
2935bool Isolate::ComputeLocationFromDetailedStackTrace(
2936 MessageLocation* target, DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
2937 if (!IsJSReceiver(*exception)) return false;
2938
2939 DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace =
2940 GetDetailedStackTrace(Cast<JSReceiver>(exception));
2941 if (stack_trace.is_null() || stack_trace->length() == 0) {
2942 return false;
2943 }
2944
2945 DirectHandle<StackFrameInfo> info(stack_trace->get(0), this);
2946 const int pos = StackFrameInfo::GetSourcePosition(info);
2947 *target = MessageLocation(handle(info->script(), this), pos, pos + 1);
2948 return true;
2949}
2950
2951Handle<JSMessageObject> Isolate::CreateMessage(DirectHandle<Object> exception,
2952 MessageLocation* location) {
2953 DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace;
2954 if (capture_stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_) {
2955 if (IsJSObject(*exception)) {
2956 // First, check whether a stack trace is already present on this object.
2957 // It maybe an Error, or the embedder may have stored a stack trace using
2958 // Exception::CaptureStackTrace().
2959 // If the lookup fails, we fall through and capture the stack trace
2960 // at this throw site.
2961 stack_trace = GetDetailedStackTrace(Cast<JSObject>(exception));
2962 }
2963 if (stack_trace.is_null()) {
2964 // Not an error object, we capture stack and location at throw site.
2965 stack_trace = CaptureDetailedStackTrace(
2966 stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_,
2967 stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_options_);
2968 }
2969 }
2970 MessageLocation computed_location;
2971 if (location == nullptr &&
2972 (ComputeLocationFromException(&computed_location, exception) ||
2973 ComputeLocationFromSimpleStackTrace(&computed_location, exception) ||
2974 ComputeLocation(&computed_location))) {
2975 location = &computed_location;
2976 }
2977
2978 return MessageHandler::MakeMessageObject(this,
2979 MessageTemplate::kUncaughtException,
2980 location, exception, stack_trace);
2981}
2982
2983Handle<JSMessageObject> Isolate::CreateMessageFromException(
2984 DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
2985 DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace;
2986 if (IsJSError(*exception)) {
2987 stack_trace = GetDetailedStackTrace(Cast<JSObject>(exception));
2988 }
2989
2990 MessageLocation* location = nullptr;
2991 MessageLocation computed_location;
2992 if (ComputeLocationFromException(&computed_location, exception) ||
2993 ComputeLocationFromDetailedStackTrace(&computed_location, exception)) {
2994 location = &computed_location;
2995 }
2996
2997 return MessageHandler::MakeMessageObject(this,
2998 MessageTemplate::kPlaceholderOnly,
2999 location, exception, stack_trace);
3000}
3001
3002Isolate::ExceptionHandlerType Isolate::TopExceptionHandlerType(
3003 Tagged<Object> exception) {
3004 DCHECK_NE(ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).the_hole_value(), exception);
3005
3006 Address js_handler = Isolate::handler(thread_local_top());
3007 Address external_handler = thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_address();
3008
3009 // A handler cannot be on top if it doesn't exist. For uncatchable exceptions,
3010 // the JavaScript handler cannot be on top.
3011 if (js_handler == kNullAddress || !is_catchable_by_javascript(exception)) {
3012 if (external_handler == kNullAddress) {
3013 return ExceptionHandlerType::kNone;
3014 }
3015 return ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch;
3016 }
3017
3018 if (external_handler == kNullAddress) {
3019 return ExceptionHandlerType::kJavaScriptHandler;
3020 }
3021
3022 // The exception has been externally caught if and only if there is an
3023 // external handler which is on top of the top-most JS_ENTRY handler.
3024 //
3025 // Note, that finally clauses would re-throw an exception unless it's aborted
3026 // by jumps in control flow (like return, break, etc.) and we'll have another
3027 // chance to set proper v8::TryCatch later.
3028 DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, external_handler);
3029 DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, js_handler);
3030 if (external_handler < js_handler) {
3031 return ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch;
3032 }
3033 return ExceptionHandlerType::kJavaScriptHandler;
3034}
3035
3036std::vector<MemoryRange>* Isolate::GetCodePages() const {
3037 return code_pages_.load(std::memory_order_acquire);
3038}
3039
3040void Isolate::SetCodePages(std::vector<MemoryRange>* new_code_pages) {
3041 code_pages_.store(new_code_pages, std::memory_order_release);
3042}
3043
3044void Isolate::ReportPendingMessages(bool report) {
3045 Tagged<Object> exception_obj = exception();
3046 ExceptionHandlerType top_handler = TopExceptionHandlerType(exception_obj);
3047
3048 // Try to propagate the exception to an external v8::TryCatch handler. If
3049 // propagation was unsuccessful, then we will get another chance at reporting
3050 // the pending message if the exception is re-thrown.
3051 bool has_been_propagated = PropagateExceptionToExternalTryCatch(top_handler);
3052 if (!has_been_propagated) return;
3053 if (!report) return;
3054
3055 DCHECK(AllowExceptions::IsAllowed(this));
3056
3057 // The embedder might run script in response to an exception.
3058 AllowJavascriptExecutionDebugOnly allow_script(this);
3059
3060 // Clear the pending message object early to avoid endless recursion.
3061 Tagged<Object> message_obj = pending_message();
3062 clear_pending_message();
3063
3064 // For uncatchable exceptions we do nothing. If needed, the exception and the
3065 // message have already been propagated to v8::TryCatch.
3066 if (!is_catchable_by_javascript(exception_obj)) return;
3067
3068 // Determine whether the message needs to be reported to all message handlers
3069 // depending on whether the topmost external v8::TryCatch is verbose. We know
3070 // there's no JavaScript handler on top; if there was, we would've returned
3071 // early.
3072 DCHECK_NE(ExceptionHandlerType::kJavaScriptHandler, top_handler);
3073
3074 bool should_report_exception;
3075 if (top_handler == ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch) {
3076 should_report_exception = try_catch_handler()->is_verbose_;
3077 } else {
3078 should_report_exception = true;
3079 }
3080
3081 // Actually report the pending message to all message handlers.
3082 if (!IsTheHole(message_obj, this) && should_report_exception) {
3083 HandleScope scope(this);
3084 DirectHandle<JSMessageObject> message(Cast<JSMessageObject>(message_obj),
3085 this);
3086 Handle<Script> script(message->script(), this);
3087 // Clear the exception and restore it afterwards, otherwise
3088 // CollectSourcePositions will abort.
3089 {
3090 ExceptionScope exception_scope(this);
3091 JSMessageObject::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(this, message);
3092 }
3093 int start_pos = message->GetStartPosition();
3094 int end_pos = message->GetEndPosition();
3095 MessageLocation location(script, start_pos, end_pos);
3096 MessageHandler::ReportMessage(this, &location, message);
3097 }
3098}
3099
3100namespace {
3101bool ReceiverIsForwardingHandler(Isolate* isolate,
3102 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler) {
3103 // Recurse to the forwarding Promise (e.g. return false) due to
3104 // - await reaction forwarding to the throwaway Promise, which has
3105 // a dependency edge to the outer Promise.
3106 // - PromiseIdResolveHandler forwarding to the output of .then
3107 // - Promise.all/Promise.race forwarding to a throwaway Promise, which
3108 // has a dependency edge to the generated outer Promise.
3109 // Otherwise, this is a real reject handler for the Promise.
3110 DirectHandle<Symbol> key =
3111 isolate->factory()->promise_forwarding_handler_symbol();
3112 DirectHandle<Object> forwarding_handler =
3113 JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(isolate, handler, key);
3114 return !IsUndefined(*forwarding_handler, isolate);
3115}
3116
3117bool WalkPromiseTreeInternal(
3118 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
3119 const std::function<void(Isolate::PromiseHandler)>& callback) {
3120 if (promise->status() != Promise::kPending) {
3121 // If a rejection reaches an exception that isn't pending, it will be
3122 // treated as caught.
3123 return true;
3124 }
3125
3126 bool any_caught = false;
3127 bool any_uncaught = false;
3128 DirectHandle<Object> current(promise->reactions(), isolate);
3129 while (!IsSmi(*current)) {
3130 auto reaction = Cast<PromiseReaction>(current);
3131 DirectHandle<HeapObject> promise_or_capability(
3132 reaction->promise_or_capability(), isolate);
3133 if (!IsUndefined(*promise_or_capability, isolate)) {
3134 if (!IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
3135 promise_or_capability = direct_handle(
3136 Cast<PromiseCapability>(promise_or_capability)->promise(), isolate);
3137 }
3138 if (IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
3139 DirectHandle<JSPromise> next_promise =
3140 Cast<JSPromise>(promise_or_capability);
3141 bool caught = false;
3142 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> reject_handler;
3143 if (!IsUndefined(reaction->reject_handler(), isolate)) {
3144 reject_handler = direct_handle(
3145 Cast<JSReceiver>(reaction->reject_handler()), isolate);
3146 if (!ReceiverIsForwardingHandler(isolate, reject_handler) &&
3147 !IsBuiltinForwardingRejectHandler(isolate, *reject_handler)) {
3148 caught = true;
3149 }
3150 }
3151 // Pass each handler to the callback
3152 DirectHandle<JSGeneratorObject> async_function;
3153 if (TryGetAsyncGenerator(isolate, reaction).ToHandle(&async_function)) {
3154 caught = caught ||
3155 PredictExceptionFromGenerator(async_function, isolate) ==
3156 HandlerTable::CAUGHT;
3157 // Look at the async function, not the individual handlers
3158 callback({async_function->function()->shared(), true});
3159 } else {
3160 // Not an async function, look at individual handlers
3161 if (!IsUndefined(reaction->fulfill_handler(), isolate)) {
3162 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fulfill_handler(
3163 Cast<JSReceiver>(reaction->fulfill_handler()), isolate);
3164 if (!ReceiverIsForwardingHandler(isolate, fulfill_handler)) {
3165 if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, *fulfill_handler,
3166 Builtin::kPromiseThenFinally)) {
3167 // If this is the finally handler, get the wrapped callback
3168 // from the context to use instead
3169 DirectHandle<Context> context(
3170 Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler())->context(),
3171 isolate);
3172 int const index =
3173 PromiseBuiltins::PromiseFinallyContextSlot::kOnFinallySlot;
3174 fulfill_handler = direct_handle(
3175 Cast<JSReceiver>(context->get(index)), isolate);
3176 }
3177 if (IsJSFunction(*fulfill_handler)) {
3178 callback({Cast<JSFunction>(fulfill_handler)->shared(), true});
3179 }
3180 }
3181 }
3182 if (caught) {
3183 // We've already checked that this isn't undefined or
3184 // a forwarding handler
3185 if (IsJSFunction(*reject_handler)) {
3186 callback({Cast<JSFunction>(reject_handler)->shared(), true});
3187 }
3188 }
3189 }
3190 caught =
3191 caught || WalkPromiseTreeInternal(isolate, next_promise, callback);
3192 any_caught = any_caught || caught;
3193 any_uncaught = any_uncaught || !caught;
3194 }
3195 } else {
3196#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3197 DirectHandle<WasmSuspenderObject> suspender;
3198 if (TryGetWasmSuspender(isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler())
3199 .ToHandle(&suspender)) {
3200 // If in the future we support Wasm exceptions or ignore listing in
3201 // Wasm, we will need to iterate through these frames. For now, we
3202 // only care about the resulting promise.
3203 DirectHandle<JSPromise> next_promise(suspender->promise(), isolate);
3204 bool caught = WalkPromiseTreeInternal(isolate, next_promise, callback);
3205 any_caught = any_caught || caught;
3206 any_uncaught = any_uncaught || !caught;
3207 }
3208#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3209 }
3210 current = direct_handle(reaction->next(), isolate);
3211 }
3212
3213 bool caught = any_caught && !any_uncaught;
3214
3215 if (!caught) {
3216 // If there is an outer promise, follow that to see if it is caught.
3217 DirectHandle<Symbol> key = isolate->factory()->promise_handled_by_symbol();
3218 DirectHandle<Object> outer_promise_obj =
3219 JSObject::GetDataProperty(isolate, promise, key);
3220 if (IsJSPromise(*outer_promise_obj)) {
3221 return WalkPromiseTreeInternal(
3222 isolate, Cast<JSPromise>(outer_promise_obj), callback);
3223 }
3224 }
3225 return caught;
3226}
3227
3228// Helper functions to scan for calls to .catch.
3229using interpreter::Bytecode;
3230using interpreter::Bytecodes;
3231
3232enum PromiseMethod { kThen, kCatch, kFinally, kInvalid };
3233
3234// Requires the iterator to be on a GetNamedProperty instruction
3235PromiseMethod GetPromiseMethod(
3236 Isolate* isolate, const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
3237 DirectHandle<Object> object = iterator.GetConstantForIndexOperand(1, isolate);
3238 if (!IsString(*object)) {
3239 return kInvalid;
3240 }
3241 auto str = Cast<String>(object);
3242 if (str->Equals(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).then_string())) {
3243 return kThen;
3244 } else if (str->IsEqualTo(base::StaticCharVector("catch"))) {
3245 return kCatch;
3246 } else if (str->IsEqualTo(base::StaticCharVector("finally"))) {
3247 return kFinally;
3248 } else {
3249 return kInvalid;
3250 }
3251}
3252
3253bool TouchesRegister(const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator,
3254 int index) {
3255 Bytecode bytecode = iterator.current_bytecode();
3256 int num_operands = Bytecodes::NumberOfOperands(bytecode);
3257 const interpreter::OperandType* operand_types =
3258 Bytecodes::GetOperandTypes(bytecode);
3259
3260 for (int i = 0; i < num_operands; ++i) {
3261 if (Bytecodes::IsRegisterOperandType(operand_types[i])) {
3262 int base_index = iterator.GetRegisterOperand(i).index();
3263 int num_registers;
3264 if (Bytecodes::IsRegisterListOperandType(operand_types[i])) {
3265 num_registers = iterator.GetRegisterCountOperand(++i);
3266 } else {
3267 num_registers =
3268 Bytecodes::GetNumberOfRegistersRepresentedBy(operand_types[i]);
3269 }
3270
3271 if (base_index <= index && index < base_index + num_registers) {
3272 return true;
3273 }
3274 }
3275 }
3276
3277 if (Bytecodes::WritesImplicitRegister(bytecode)) {
3278 return iterator.GetStarTargetRegister().index() == index;
3279 }
3280
3281 return false;
3282}
3283
3284bool CallsCatchMethod(Isolate* isolate, Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array,
3285 int offset) {
3286 interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator iterator(bytecode_array, offset);
3287
3288 while (!iterator.done()) {
3289 // We should be on a call instruction of some kind. While we could check
3290 // this, it may be difficult to create an exhaustive list of instructions
3291 // that could call, such as property getters, but at a minimum this
3292 // instruction should write to the accumulator.
3293 if (!Bytecodes::WritesAccumulator(iterator.current_bytecode())) {
3294 return false;
3295 }
3296
3297 iterator.Advance();
3298 // While usually the next instruction is a Star, sometimes we store and
3299 // reload from context first.
3300 if (iterator.done()) {
3301 return false;
3302 }
3303 if (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kStaCurrentContextSlot) {
3304 // Step over patterns like:
3305 // StaCurrentContextSlot [x]
3306 // LdaImmutableCurrentContextSlot [x]
3307 unsigned int slot = iterator.GetIndexOperand(0);
3308 iterator.Advance();
3309 if (!iterator.done() &&
3310 (iterator.current_bytecode() ==
3311 Bytecode::kLdaImmutableCurrentContextSlot ||
3312 iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kLdaCurrentContextSlot)) {
3313 if (iterator.GetIndexOperand(0) != slot) {
3314 return false;
3315 }
3316 iterator.Advance();
3317 }
3318 } else if (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kStaContextSlot) {
3319 // Step over patterns like:
3320 // StaContextSlot r_x [y] [z]
3321 // LdaContextSlot r_x [y] [z]
3322 int context = iterator.GetRegisterOperand(0).index();
3323 unsigned int slot = iterator.GetIndexOperand(1);
3324 unsigned int depth = iterator.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(2);
3325 iterator.Advance();
3326 if (!iterator.done() &&
3327 (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kLdaImmutableContextSlot ||
3328 iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kLdaContextSlot)) {
3329 if (iterator.GetRegisterOperand(0).index() != context ||
3330 iterator.GetIndexOperand(1) != slot ||
3331 iterator.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(2) != depth) {
3332 return false;
3333 }
3334 iterator.Advance();
3335 }
3336 } else if (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kStaLookupSlot) {
3337 // Step over patterns like:
3338 // StaLookupSlot [x] [_]
3339 // LdaLookupSlot [x]
3340 unsigned int slot = iterator.GetIndexOperand(0);
3341 iterator.Advance();
3342 if (!iterator.done() &&
3343 (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kLdaLookupSlot ||
3344 iterator.current_bytecode() ==
3345 Bytecode::kLdaLookupSlotInsideTypeof)) {
3346 if (iterator.GetIndexOperand(0) != slot) {
3347 return false;
3348 }
3349 iterator.Advance();
3350 }
3351 }
3352
3353 // Next instruction should be a Star (store accumulator to register)
3354 if (iterator.done() || !Bytecodes::IsAnyStar(iterator.current_bytecode())) {
3355 return false;
3356 }
3357 // The register it stores to will be assumed to be our promise
3358 int promise_register = iterator.GetStarTargetRegister().index();
3359
3360 // TODO(crbug/40283993): Should we loop over non-matching instructions here
3361 // to allow code like
3362 // `const promise = foo(); console.log(...); promise.catch(...);`?
3363
3364 iterator.Advance();
3365 // We should be on a GetNamedProperty instruction.
3366 if (iterator.done() ||
3367 iterator.current_bytecode() != Bytecode::kGetNamedProperty ||
3368 iterator.GetRegisterOperand(0).index() != promise_register) {
3369 return false;
3370 }
3371 PromiseMethod method = GetPromiseMethod(isolate, iterator);
3372 if (method == kInvalid) {
3373 return false;
3374 }
3375
3376 iterator.Advance();
3377 // Next instruction should be a Star (save immediate to register)
3378 if (iterator.done() || !Bytecodes::IsAnyStar(iterator.current_bytecode())) {
3379 return false;
3380 }
3381 // This register contains the method we will eventually invoke
3382 int method_register = iterator.GetStarTargetRegister().index();
3383 if (method_register == promise_register) {
3384 return false;
3385 }
3386
3387 // Now we step over multiple instructions creating the arguments for the
3388 // method.
3389 while (true) {
3390 iterator.Advance();
3391 if (iterator.done()) {
3392 return false;
3393 }
3394 Bytecode bytecode = iterator.current_bytecode();
3395 if (bytecode == Bytecode::kCallProperty1 ||
3396 bytecode == Bytecode::kCallProperty2) {
3397 // This is a call property call of the right size, but is it a call of
3398 // the method and on the promise?
3399 if (iterator.GetRegisterOperand(0).index() == method_register &&
3400 iterator.GetRegisterOperand(1).index() == promise_register) {
3401 // This is our method call, but does it catch?
3402 if (method == kCatch ||
3403 (method == kThen && bytecode == Bytecode::kCallProperty2)) {
3404 return true;
3405 }
3406 // Break out of the inner loop, continuing the outer loop. We
3407 // will use the same procedure to check for chained method calls.
3408 break;
3409 }
3410 }
3411
3412 // Check for some instructions that should make us give up scanning.
3413 if (Bytecodes::IsJump(bytecode) || Bytecodes::IsSwitch(bytecode) ||
3414 Bytecodes::Returns(bytecode) ||
3415 Bytecodes::UnconditionallyThrows(bytecode)) {
3416 // Stop scanning at control flow instructions that aren't calls
3417 return false;
3418 }
3419
3420 if (TouchesRegister(iterator, promise_register) ||
3421 TouchesRegister(iterator, method_register)) {
3422 // Stop scanning at instruction that unexpectedly interacts with one of
3423 // the registers we care about.
3424 return false;
3425 }
3426 }
3427 }
3428 return false;
3429}
3430
3431bool CallsCatchMethod(const StackFrameSummaryIterator& iterator) {
3432 if (!iterator.frame()->is_javascript()) {
3433 return false;
3434 }
3435 if (iterator.frame_summary().IsJavaScript()) {
3436 auto& js_summary = iterator.frame_summary().AsJavaScript();
3437 if (IsBytecodeArray(*js_summary.abstract_code())) {
3438 if (CallsCatchMethod(iterator.isolate(),
3439 Cast<BytecodeArray>(js_summary.abstract_code()),
3440 js_summary.code_offset())) {
3441 return true;
3442 }
3443 }
3444 }
3445 return false;
3446}
3447
3448} // namespace
3449
3450bool Isolate::WalkCallStackAndPromiseTree(
3451 MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise> rejected_promise,
3452 const std::function<void(PromiseHandler)>& callback) {
3453 bool is_promise_rejection = false;
3454
3455 DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise;
3456 if (rejected_promise.ToHandle(&promise)) {
3457 is_promise_rejection = true;
3458 // If the promise has reactions, follow them and assume we are done. If
3459 // it has no reactions, assume promise is returned up the call stack and
3460 // trace accordingly. If the promise is not pending, it has no reactions
3461 // and is probably the result of a call to Promise.reject().
3462 if (promise->status() != Promise::kPending) {
3463 // Ignore this promise; set to null
3464 rejected_promise = MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>();
3465 } else if (IsSmi(promise->reactions())) {
3466 // Also check that there is no outer promise
3467 DirectHandle<Symbol> key = factory()->promise_handled_by_symbol();
3468 if (!IsJSPromise(*JSObject::GetDataProperty(this, promise, key))) {
3469 // Ignore this promise; set to null
3470 rejected_promise = MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>();
3471 }
3472 }
3473 }
3474
3475 if (!is_promise_rejection && TopExceptionHandlerType(Tagged<Object>()) ==
3476 ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch) {
3477 return true; // caught by external
3478 }
3479
3480 // Search for an exception handler by performing a full walk over the stack.
3481 for (StackFrameSummaryIterator iter(this); !iter.done(); iter.Advance()) {
3482 Isolate::CatchType prediction = PredictExceptionCatchAtFrame(iter);
3483
3484 bool caught;
3485 if (rejected_promise.is_null()) {
3486 switch (prediction) {
3487 case NOT_CAUGHT:
3488 // Uncaught unless this is a promise rejection and the code will call
3489 // .catch()
3490 caught = is_promise_rejection && CallsCatchMethod(iter);
3491 break;
3492 case CAUGHT_BY_ASYNC_AWAIT:
3493 // Uncaught unless this is a promise rejection and the code will call
3494 // .catch()
3495 caught = is_promise_rejection && CallsCatchMethod(iter);
3496 // Exceptions turn into promise rejections here
3497 is_promise_rejection = true;
3498 break;
3499 case CAUGHT_BY_PROMISE:
3500 // Exceptions turn into promise rejections here
3501 // TODO(leese): Perhaps we can handle the case where the reject method
3502 // is called in the promise constructor and it is still on the stack
3503 // by ignoring all try/catches on the stack until we get to the right
3504 // CAUGHT_BY_PROMISE?
3505 is_promise_rejection = true;
3506 caught = false;
3507 break;
3508 case CAUGHT_BY_EXTERNAL:
3509 caught = !is_promise_rejection;
3510 break;
3511 case CAUGHT_BY_JAVASCRIPT:
3512 caught = true;
3513 // Unless this is a promise rejection and the function is not async...
3514 DCHECK(iter.has_frame_summary());
3515 const FrameSummary& summary = iter.frame_summary();
3516 if (is_promise_rejection && summary.IsJavaScript()) {
3517 // If the catch happens in an async function, assume it will
3518 // await this promise. Alternately, if the code will call .catch,
3519 // assume it is on this promise.
3520 caught = IsAsyncFunction(iter.frame_summary()
3521 .AsJavaScript()
3522 .function()
3523 ->shared()
3524 ->kind()) ||
3525 CallsCatchMethod(iter);
3526 }
3527 break;
3528 }
3529 } else {
3530 // The frame that calls the reject handler will not catch that promise
3531 // regardless of what else it does. We will trace where this rejection
3532 // goes according to its reaction callbacks, but we first need to handle
3533 // the topmost debuggable frame just to ensure there is a debuggable
3534 // frame and to permit ignore listing there.
3535 caught = false;
3536 }
3537
3538 if (iter.frame()->is_javascript()) {
3539 bool debuggable = false;
3540 DCHECK(iter.has_frame_summary());
3541 const FrameSummary& summary = iter.frame_summary();
3542 if (summary.IsJavaScript()) {
3543 const auto& info = summary.AsJavaScript().function()->shared();
3544 if (info->IsSubjectToDebugging()) {
3545 callback({*info, false});
3546 debuggable = true;
3547 }
3548 }
3549
3550 // Ignore the rest of the call stack if this is a rejection and the
3551 // promise has handlers; we will trace where the rejection goes instead
3552 // of where it came from.
3553 if (debuggable && !rejected_promise.is_null()) {
3554 break;
3555 }
3556 }
3557
3558 if (caught) {
3559 return true;
3560 }
3561 }
3562
3563 if (rejected_promise.is_null()) {
3564 // Now follow promises if this is a promise reaction job.
3565 rejected_promise = TryGetCurrentTaskPromise(this);
3566 }
3567
3568 if (rejected_promise.ToHandle(&promise)) {
3569 return WalkPromiseTreeInternal(this, promise, callback);
3570 }
3571 // Nothing caught.
3572 return false;
3573}

3591void Isolate::InstallConditionalFeatures(DirectHandle<NativeContext> context) {
3592 DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global =
3593 direct_handle(context->global_object(), this);
3594 // If some fuzzer decided to make the global object non-extensible, then
3595 // we can't install any features (and would CHECK-fail if we tried).
3596 if (!global->map()->is_extensible()) return;
3597 DirectHandle<String> sab_name = factory()->SharedArrayBuffer_string();
3598 if (IsSharedArrayBufferConstructorEnabled(context)) {
3599 if (!JSObject::HasRealNamedProperty(this, global, sab_name)
3600 .FromMaybe(true)) {
3601 JSObject::AddProperty(this, global, factory()->SharedArrayBuffer_string(),
3602 shared_array_buffer_fun(), DONT_ENUM);
3603 }
3604 }
3605}
3606
3607bool Isolate::IsSharedArrayBufferConstructorEnabled(
3608 DirectHandle<NativeContext> context) {
3609 if (!v8_flags.enable_sharedarraybuffer_per_context) return true;
3610
3611 if (sharedarraybuffer_constructor_enabled_callback()) {
3612 v8::Local<v8::Context> api_context = v8::Utils::ToLocal(context);
3613 return sharedarraybuffer_constructor_enabled_callback()(api_context);
3614 }
3615 return false;
3616}

3621 // stringref.

3623 wasm_imported_strings_enabled_callback();

3625 v8::Local<v8::Context> api_context = v8::Utils::ToLocal(context);
3626 if (callback_imported_strings(api_context)) return true;

3630#else
3631 return false;
3632#endif

3640 if (jspi_callback(api_context)) return true;
3641 }

3649
3650bool Isolate::IsWasmJSPIEnabled(DirectHandle<NativeContext> context) {
3651#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3652 return IsWasmJSPIRequested(context) &&
3653 context->is_wasm_jspi_installed() != Smi::zero();
3654#else
3655 return false;
3656#endif
3657}
3658
3659bool Isolate::IsWasmImportedStringsEnabled(
3660 DirectHandle<NativeContext> context) {
3661#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3662 v8::WasmImportedStringsEnabledCallback callback =
3663 wasm_imported_strings_enabled_callback();
3664 if (callback) {
3665 v8::Local<v8::Context> api_context = v8::Utils::ToLocal(context);
3666 if (callback(api_context)) return true;
3667 }
3668 return v8_flags.experimental_wasm_imported_strings;
3669#else
3670 return false;
3671#endif
3672}
3673
3674Handle<NativeContext> Isolate::GetIncumbentContextSlow() {
3675 JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(this);
3676
3677 // 1st candidate: most-recently-entered author function's context
3678 // if it's newer than the last Context::BackupIncumbentScope entry.
3679 //
3680 // NOTE: This code assumes that the stack grows downward.
3681 Address top_backup_incumbent =
3682 top_backup_incumbent_scope()
3683 ? top_backup_incumbent_scope()->JSStackComparableAddressPrivate()
3684 : 0;
3685 if (!it.done() &&
3686 (!top_backup_incumbent || it.frame()->sp() < top_backup_incumbent)) {
3687 Tagged<Context> context = Cast<Context>(it.frame()->context());
3688 // If the topmost_script_having_context is set then it must be correct.
3689 if (DEBUG_BOOL && !topmost_script_having_context().is_null()) {
3690 DCHECK_EQ(topmost_script_having_context()->native_context(),
3691 context->native_context());
3692 }
3693 return Handle<NativeContext>(context->native_context(), this);
3694 }
3695 DCHECK(topmost_script_having_context().is_null());
3696
3697 // 2nd candidate: the last Context::Scope's incumbent context if any.
3698 if (top_backup_incumbent_scope()) {
3699 v8::Local<v8::Context> incumbent_context =
3700 top_backup_incumbent_scope()->backup_incumbent_context_;
3701 return Utils::OpenHandle(*incumbent_context);
3702 }
3703
3704 // Last candidate: the entered context or microtask context.
3705 // Given that there is no other author function is running, there must be
3706 // no cross-context function running, then the incumbent realm must match
3707 // the entry realm.
3708 v8::Local<v8::Context> entered_context =
3709 reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this)->GetEnteredOrMicrotaskContext();
3710 return Utils::OpenHandle(*entered_context);
3711}
3712
3713char* Isolate::ArchiveThread(char* to) {
3714 MemCopy(to, reinterpret_cast<char*>(thread_local_top()),
3715 sizeof(ThreadLocalTop));
3716 return to + sizeof(ThreadLocalTop);
3717}
3718
3719char* Isolate::RestoreThread(char* from) {
3720 MemCopy(reinterpret_cast<char*>(thread_local_top()), from,
3721 sizeof(ThreadLocalTop));
3722 DCHECK(context().is_null() || IsContext(context()));
3723 return from + sizeof(ThreadLocalTop);
3724}
3725
3726void Isolate::ReleaseSharedPtrs() {
3727 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock(&managed_ptr_destructors_mutex_);
3728 while (managed_ptr_destructors_head_) {
3729 ManagedPtrDestructor* l = managed_ptr_destructors_head_;
3730 ManagedPtrDestructor* n = nullptr;
3731 managed_ptr_destructors_head_ = nullptr;
3732 for (; l != nullptr; l = n) {
3733 l->external_memory_accounter_.Decrease(
3734 reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this), l->estimated_size_);
3735 l->destructor_(l->shared_ptr_ptr_);
3736 n = l->next_;
3737 delete l;
3738 }
3739 }
3740}
3741
3742bool Isolate::IsBuiltinTableHandleLocation(Address* handle_location) {
3743 FullObjectSlot location(handle_location);
3744 FullObjectSlot first_root(builtin_table());
3745 FullObjectSlot last_root(first_root + Builtins::kBuiltinCount);
3746 if (location >= last_root) return false;
3747 if (location < first_root) return false;
3748 return true;
3749}
3750
3751void Isolate::RegisterManagedPtrDestructor(ManagedPtrDestructor* destructor) {
3752 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock(&managed_ptr_destructors_mutex_);
3753 DCHECK_NULL(destructor->prev_);
3754 DCHECK_NULL(destructor->next_);
3755 if (managed_ptr_destructors_head_) {
3756 managed_ptr_destructors_head_->prev_ = destructor;
3757 }
3758 destructor->next_ = managed_ptr_destructors_head_;
3759 managed_ptr_destructors_head_ = destructor;
3760}
3761
3762void Isolate::UnregisterManagedPtrDestructor(ManagedPtrDestructor* destructor) {
3763 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock(&managed_ptr_destructors_mutex_);
3764 if (destructor->prev_) {
3765 destructor->prev_->next_ = destructor->next_;
3766 } else {
3767 DCHECK_EQ(destructor, managed_ptr_destructors_head_);
3768 managed_ptr_destructors_head_ = destructor->next_;
3769 }
3770 if (destructor->next_) destructor->next_->prev_ = destructor->prev_;
3771 destructor->prev_ = nullptr;
3772 destructor->next_ = nullptr;
3773}
3774
3775#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3776bool Isolate::IsOnCentralStack(Address addr) {
3777 auto stack = SimulatorStack::GetCentralStackView(this);
3778 Address stack_top = reinterpret_cast<Address>(stack.begin());
3779 Address stack_base = reinterpret_cast<Address>(stack.end());
3780 return stack_top < addr && addr <= stack_base;
3781}
3782
3783bool Isolate::IsOnCentralStack() {
3784#if USE_SIMULATOR
3785 return IsOnCentralStack(Simulator::current(this)->get_sp());
3786#else
3787 return IsOnCentralStack(GetCurrentStackPosition());
3788#endif
3789}

3791void Isolate::AddSharedWasmMemory(
3792 DirectHandle<WasmMemoryObject> memory_object) {
3793 Handle<WeakArrayList> shared_wasm_memories =
3794 factory()->shared_wasm_memories();
3795 shared_wasm_memories = WeakArrayList::Append(
3796 this, shared_wasm_memories, MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(memory_object));
3797 heap()->set_shared_wasm_memories(*shared_wasm_memories);
3798}
3799
3800void Isolate::SyncStackLimit() {
3801 // Synchronize the stack limit with the active continuation for
3802 // stack-switching. This can be done before or after changing the stack
3803 // pointer itself, as long as we update both before the next stack check.
3804 // {StackGuard::SetStackLimitForStackSwitching} doesn't update the value of
3805 // the jslimit if it contains a sentinel value, and it is also thread-safe. So
3806 // if an interrupt is requested before, during or after this call, it will be
3807 // preserved and handled at the next stack check.
3808
3809 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3810 auto continuation =
3811 Cast<WasmContinuationObject>(root(RootIndex::kActiveContinuation));
3812 wasm::StackMemory* stack =
3813 reinterpret_cast<wasm::StackMemory*>(continuation->stack());
3814 if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_stack_switching) {
3815 PrintF("Switch to stack #%d\n", stack->id());
3816 }
3817 uintptr_t limit = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(stack->jmpbuf()->stack_limit);
3818 stack_guard()->SetStackLimitForStackSwitching(limit);
3819 UpdateCentralStackInfo();
3820}
3821
3822void Isolate::UpdateCentralStackInfo() {
3823 Tagged<Object> current = root(RootIndex::kActiveContinuation);
3824 DCHECK(!IsUndefined(current));
3825 wasm::StackMemory* wasm_stack = reinterpret_cast<wasm::StackMemory*>(
3826 Cast<WasmContinuationObject>(current)->stack());
3827 current = Cast<WasmContinuationObject>(current)->parent();
3828 thread_local_top()->is_on_central_stack_flag_ =
3829 IsOnCentralStack(wasm_stack->jmpbuf()->sp);
3830 // Update the central stack info on switch. Only consider the innermost stack
3831 bool updated_central_stack = false;
3832 // We don't need to add all inactive stacks. Only the ones in the active chain
3833 // may contain cpp heap pointers.
3834 while (!IsUndefined(current)) {
3835 auto cont = Cast<WasmContinuationObject>(current);
3836 auto* wasm_stack = reinterpret_cast<wasm::StackMemory*>(cont->stack());
3837 // On x64 and arm64 we don't need to record the stack segments for
3838 // conservative stack scanning. We switch to the central stack for foreign
3839 // calls, so secondary stacks only contain wasm frames which use the precise
3840 // GC.
3841 current = cont->parent();
3842 if (!updated_central_stack && IsOnCentralStack(wasm_stack->jmpbuf()->sp)) {
3843 // This is the most recent use of the central stack in the call chain.
3844 // Switch to this SP if we need to switch to the central stack in the
3845 // future.
3846 thread_local_top()->central_stack_sp_ = wasm_stack->jmpbuf()->sp;
3847 thread_local_top()->central_stack_limit_ =
3848 reinterpret_cast<Address>(wasm_stack->jmpbuf()->stack_limit);
3849 updated_central_stack = true;
3850 }
3851 }
3852}
3853
3854void Isolate::RetireWasmStack(wasm::StackMemory* stack) {
3855 stack->jmpbuf()->state = wasm::JumpBuffer::Retired;
3856 size_t index = stack->index();
3857 // We can only return from a stack that was still in the global list.
3858 DCHECK_LT(index, wasm_stacks().size());
3859 std::unique_ptr<wasm::StackMemory> stack_ptr =
3860 std::move(wasm_stacks()[index]);
3861 DCHECK_EQ(stack_ptr.get(), stack);
3862 if (index != wasm_stacks().size() - 1) {
3863 wasm_stacks()[index] = std::move(wasm_stacks().back());
3864 wasm_stacks()[index]->set_index(index);
3865 }
3866 wasm_stacks().pop_back();
3867 for (size_t i = 0; i < wasm_stacks().size(); ++i) {
3868 SLOW_DCHECK(wasm_stacks()[i]->index() == i);
3869 }
3870 stack_pool().Add(std::move(stack_ptr));
3871}
3872
3873wasm::WasmOrphanedGlobalHandle* Isolate::NewWasmOrphanedGlobalHandle() {
3874 return wasm::WasmEngine::NewOrphanedGlobalHandle(&wasm_orphaned_handle_);
3875}
3876
3877void Isolate::EnsureGenericJSToWasmWrapperParamBufferExists() {
3878 if (generic_js_to_wasm_wrapper_param_buffer_owner_) return;
3879
3880 generic_js_to_wasm_wrapper_param_buffer_owner_ =
3881 std::make_unique_for_overwrite<uint8_t[]>(
3882 wasm::kGenericJSToWasmWrapperParamBufferMaxSize);
3883 isolate_data_.generic_js_to_wasm_wrapper_param_buffer_ =
3884 generic_js_to_wasm_wrapper_param_buffer_owner_.get();
3885}

3905}

3910}
