3913 for (auto& x : table_) {
3914 delete x.second;
3915 }
3916 table_.clear();
3917}
3918
3919class TracingAccountingAllocator : public AccountingAllocator {
3920 public:
3921 explicit TracingAccountingAllocator(Isolate* isolate) : isolate_(isolate) {}
3922 ~TracingAccountingAllocator() = default;
3923
3924 protected:
3925 void TraceAllocateSegmentImpl(v8::internal::Segment* segment) override {
3926 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock(&mutex_);
3927 UpdateMemoryTrafficAndReportMemoryUsage(segment->total_size());
3928 }
3929
3930 void TraceZoneCreationImpl(const Zone* zone) override {
3931 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock(&mutex_);
3932 active_zones_.insert(zone);
3933 nesting_depth_++;
3934 }
3935
3936 void TraceZoneDestructionImpl(const Zone* zone) override {
3937 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock(&mutex_);
3938#ifdef V8_ENABLE_PRECISE_ZONE_STATS
3939 if (v8_flags.trace_zone_type_stats) {
3940 type_stats_.MergeWith(zone->type_stats());
3941 }
3942#endif
3943 UpdateMemoryTrafficAndReportMemoryUsage(zone->segment_bytes_allocated());
3944 active_zones_.erase(zone);
3945 nesting_depth_--;
3946
3947#ifdef V8_ENABLE_PRECISE_ZONE_STATS
3948 if (v8_flags.trace_zone_type_stats && active_zones_.empty()) {
3949 type_stats_.Dump();
3950 }
3951#endif
3952 }
3953
3954 private:
3955 void UpdateMemoryTrafficAndReportMemoryUsage(size_t memory_traffic_delta) {
3956 if (!v8_flags.trace_zone_stats &&
3957 !(TracingFlags::zone_stats.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) &
3958 v8::tracing::TracingCategoryObserver::ENABLED_BY_TRACING)) {
3959 // Don't print anything if the zone tracing was enabled only because of
3960 // v8_flags.trace_zone_type_stats.
3961 return;
3962 }
3963
3964 memory_traffic_since_last_report_ += memory_traffic_delta;
3965 if (memory_traffic_since_last_report_ < v8_flags.zone_stats_tolerance)
3966 return;
3967 memory_traffic_since_last_report_ = 0;
3968
3969 Dump(buffer_, true);
3970
3971 {
3972 std::string trace_str = buffer_.str();
3973
3974 if (v8_flags.trace_zone_stats) {
3975 PrintF(
3976 "{"
3977 "\"type\": \"v8-zone-trace\", "
3978 "\"stats\": %s"
3979 "}\n",
3980 trace_str.c_str());
3981 }
3982 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
3983 TracingFlags::zone_stats.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) &
3984 v8::tracing::TracingCategoryObserver::ENABLED_BY_TRACING)) {
3985 TRACE_EVENT_INSTANT1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.zone_stats"),
3986 "V8.Zone_Stats", TRACE_EVENT_SCOPE_THREAD, "stats",
3987 TRACE_STR_COPY(trace_str.c_str()));
3988 }
3989 }
3990
3991 // Clear the buffer.
3992 buffer_.str(std::string());
3993 }
3994
3995 void Dump(std::ostringstream& out, bool dump_details) {
3996 // Note: Neither isolate nor zones are locked, so be careful with accesses
3997 // as the allocator is potentially used on a concurrent thread.
3998 double time = isolate_->time_millis_since_init();
3999 out << "{" << "\"isolate\": \"" << reinterpret_cast<void*>(isolate_)
4000 << "\", " << "\"time\": " << time << ", ";
4001 size_t total_segment_bytes_allocated = 0;
4002 size_t total_zone_allocation_size = 0;
4003 size_t total_zone_freed_size = 0;
4004
4005 if (dump_details) {
4006 // Print detailed zone stats if memory usage changes direction.
4007 out << "\"zones\": [";
4008 bool first = true;
4009 for (const Zone* zone : active_zones_) {
4010 size_t zone_segment_bytes_allocated = zone->segment_bytes_allocated();
4011 size_t zone_allocation_size = zone->allocation_size_for_tracing();
4012 size_t freed_size = zone->freed_size_for_tracing();
4013 if (first) {
4014 first = false;
4015 } else {
4016 out << ", ";
4017 }
4018 out << "{" << "\"name\": \"" << zone->name() << "\", "
4019 << "\"allocated\": " << zone_segment_bytes_allocated << ", "
4020 << "\"used\": " << zone_allocation_size << ", "
4021 << "\"freed\": " << freed_size << "}";
4022 total_segment_bytes_allocated += zone_segment_bytes_allocated;
4023 total_zone_allocation_size += zone_allocation_size;
4024 total_zone_freed_size += freed_size;
4025 }
4026 out << "], ";
4027 } else {
4028 // Just calculate total allocated/used memory values.
4029 for (const Zone* zone : active_zones_) {
4030 total_segment_bytes_allocated += zone->segment_bytes_allocated();
4031 total_zone_allocation_size += zone->allocation_size_for_tracing();
4032 total_zone_freed_size += zone->freed_size_for_tracing();
4033 }
4034 }
4035 out << "\"allocated\": " << total_segment_bytes_allocated << ", "
4036 << "\"used\": " << total_zone_allocation_size << ", "
4037 << "\"freed\": " << total_zone_freed_size << "}";
4038 }
4039
4040 Isolate* const isolate_;
4041 std::atomic<size_t> nesting_depth_{0};
4042
4043 base::SpinningMutex mutex_;
4044 std::unordered_set<const Zone*> active_zones_;
4045#ifdef V8_ENABLE_PRECISE_ZONE_STATS
4046 TypeStats type_stats_;
4047#endif
4048 std::ostringstream buffer_;
4049 // This value is increased on both allocations and deallocations.
4050 size_t memory_traffic_since_last_report_ = 0;
4051};
4052
4053#ifdef DEBUG
4054std::atomic<size_t> Isolate::non_disposed_isolates_;
4055#endif // DEBUG
4056
4057// static
4058Isolate* Isolate::New() { return New(IsolateGroup::AcquireDefault()); }
4059
4060// static
4061Isolate* Isolate::New(IsolateGroup* group) { return Allocate(group); }
4062
4063// static
4064Isolate* Isolate::Allocate(IsolateGroup* group) {
4065 // v8::V8::Initialize() must be called before creating any isolates.
4066 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(V8::GetCurrentPlatform());
4067 // Allocate Isolate itself on C++ heap, ensuring page alignment.
4068 void* isolate_ptr = base::AlignedAlloc(sizeof(Isolate), kMinimumOSPageSize);
4069 // IsolateAllocator manages the virtual memory resources for the Isolate.
4070 Isolate* isolate = new (isolate_ptr) Isolate(group);
4071
4072#ifdef DEBUG
4073 non_disposed_isolates_++;
4074#endif // DEBUG
4075
4076 return isolate;
4077}
4078
4079// static
4080void Isolate::Delete(Isolate* isolate) {
4081 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate);
4082 // v8::V8::Dispose() must only be called after deleting all isolates.
4083 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(V8::GetCurrentPlatform());
4084 // Temporarily set this isolate as current so that various parts of
4085 // the isolate can access it in their destructors without having a
4086 // direct pointer. We don't use Enter/Exit here to avoid
4087 // initializing the thread data.
4088 PerIsolateThreadData* saved_data = isolate->CurrentPerIsolateThreadData();
4089 Isolate* saved_isolate = isolate->TryGetCurrent();
4090 SetIsolateThreadLocals(isolate, nullptr);
4091 isolate->set_thread_id(ThreadId::Current());
4092 isolate->heap()->SetStackStart();
4093
4094 isolate->Deinit();
4095
4096#ifdef DEBUG
4097 non_disposed_isolates_--;
4098#endif // DEBUG
4099
4100 IsolateGroup* group = isolate->isolate_group();
4101 isolate->~Isolate();
4102 // Only release the group once all other Isolate members have been destroyed.
4103 group->Release();
4104 // Free the isolate itself.
4105 base::AlignedFree(isolate);
4106
4107 // Restore the previous current isolate.
4108 SetIsolateThreadLocals(saved_isolate, saved_data);
4109}
4110
4111void Isolate::SetUpFromReadOnlyArtifacts(ReadOnlyArtifacts* artifacts) {
4112 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(artifacts);
4113 InitializeNextUniqueSfiId(artifacts->initial_next_unique_sfi_id());
4114 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(artifacts->read_only_heap());
4115 DCHECK_IMPLIES(read_only_heap_ != nullptr,
4116 read_only_heap_ == artifacts->read_only_heap());
4117 read_only_heap_ = artifacts->read_only_heap();
4118 heap_.SetUpFromReadOnlyHeap(read_only_heap_);
4119}
4120
4121v8::PageAllocator* Isolate::page_allocator() const {
4122 return isolate_group()->page_allocator();
4123}
4124
4125Isolate::Isolate(IsolateGroup* isolate_group)
4126 : isolate_data_(this, isolate_group),
4127 isolate_group_(isolate_group),
4128 id_(isolate_counter.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_relaxed)),
4129 allocator_(new TracingAccountingAllocator(this)),
4130 traced_handles_(this),
4131 builtins_(this),
4132#if defined(DEBUG) || defined(VERIFY_HEAP)
4133 num_active_deserializers_(0),
4134#endif
4135 logger_(new Logger()),
4136 detailed_source_positions_for_profiling_(v8_flags.detailed_line_info),
4137 persistent_handles_list_(new PersistentHandlesList()),
4138 jitless_(v8_flags.jitless),
4139 next_unique_sfi_id_(0),
4140 next_module_async_evaluation_ordinal_(
4141 SourceTextModule::kFirstAsyncEvaluationOrdinal),
4142 cancelable_task_manager_(new CancelableTaskManager())
4143#if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
4144 ,
4145 etw_tracing_enabled_(false),
4146 etw_trace_interpreted_frames_(v8_flags.interpreted_frames_native_stack)
4147#endif // V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING
4148{
4149 TRACE_ISOLATE(constructor);
4150 CheckIsolateLayout();
4151
4152 isolate_group->IncrementIsolateCount();
4153
4154 // ThreadManager is initialized early to support locking an isolate
4155 // before it is entered.
4156 thread_manager_ = new ThreadManager(this);
4157
4158 handle_scope_data()->Initialize();
4159
4160#define ISOLATE_INIT_EXECUTE(type, name, initial_value) \
4161 name##_ = (initial_value);
4162 ISOLATE_INIT_LIST(ISOLATE_INIT_EXECUTE)
4163#undef ISOLATE_INIT_EXECUTE
4164
4165#define ISOLATE_INIT_ARRAY_EXECUTE(type, name, length) \
4166 memset(name##_, 0, sizeof(type) * length);
4167 ISOLATE_INIT_ARRAY_LIST(ISOLATE_INIT_ARRAY_EXECUTE)
4168#undef ISOLATE_INIT_ARRAY_EXECUTE
4169
4170 InitializeLoggingAndCounters();
4171 debug_ = new Debug(this);
4172
4173 InitializeDefaultEmbeddedBlob();
4174
4175#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4176 // If we are in production V8 and not in mksnapshot we have to pass the
4177 // landing pad builtin to the WebAssembly TrapHandler.
4178 // TODO(ahaas): Isolate creation is the earliest point in time when builtins
4179 // are available, so we cannot set the landing pad earlier at the moment.
4180 // However, if builtins ever get loaded during process initialization time,
4181 // then the initialization of the trap handler landing pad should also go
4182 // there.
4183 // TODO(ahaas): The code of the landing pad does not have to be a builtin,
4184 // we could also just move it to the trap handler, and implement it e.g. with
4185 // inline assembly. It's not clear if that's worth it.
4186 if (Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobCodeSize()) {
4187 EmbeddedData embedded_data = EmbeddedData::FromBlob();
4188 Address landing_pad =
4189 embedded_data.InstructionStartOf(Builtin::kWasmTrapHandlerLandingPad);
4190 i::trap_handler::SetLandingPad(landing_pad);
4191 }
4192#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4193
4194 MicrotaskQueue::SetUpDefaultMicrotaskQueue(this);
4195}
4196
4197void Isolate::CheckIsolateLayout() {
4198#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4199 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(ExternalPointerTable, base_)),
4200 Internals::kExternalPointerTableBasePointerOffset);
4201 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(TrustedPointerTable, base_)),
4202 Internals::kTrustedPointerTableBasePointerOffset);
4203 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(sizeof(ExternalPointerTable)),
4204 Internals::kExternalPointerTableSize);
4205 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(sizeof(ExternalPointerTable)),
4206 ExternalPointerTable::kSize);
4207 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(sizeof(TrustedPointerTable)),
4208 Internals::kTrustedPointerTableSize);
4209 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(sizeof(TrustedPointerTable)),
4210 TrustedPointerTable::kSize);
4211#endif
4212
4213 CHECK_EQ(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_), 0);
4214 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.stack_guard_)),
4215 Internals::kIsolateStackGuardOffset);
4216 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.is_marking_flag_)),
4217 Internals::kVariousBooleanFlagsOffset);
4218 CHECK_EQ(
4219 static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.error_message_param_)),
4220 Internals::kErrorMessageParamOffset);
4221 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(
4222 OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.builtin_tier0_entry_table_)),
4223 Internals::kBuiltinTier0EntryTableOffset);
4224 CHECK_EQ(
4225 static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.builtin_tier0_table_)),
4226 Internals::kBuiltinTier0TableOffset);
4227 CHECK_EQ(
4228 static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.new_allocation_info_)),
4229 Internals::kNewAllocationInfoOffset);
4230 CHECK_EQ(
4231 static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.old_allocation_info_)),
4232 Internals::kOldAllocationInfoOffset);
4233 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(
4234 OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.fast_c_call_caller_fp_)),
4235 Internals::kIsolateFastCCallCallerFpOffset);
4236 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(
4237 OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.fast_c_call_caller_pc_)),
4238 Internals::kIsolateFastCCallCallerPcOffset);
4239 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.cage_base_)),
4240 Internals::kIsolateCageBaseOffset);
4241 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(
4242 OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.long_task_stats_counter_)),
4243 Internals::kIsolateLongTaskStatsCounterOffset);
4244 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.stack_guard_)),
4245 Internals::kIsolateStackGuardOffset);
4246
4247 CHECK_EQ(
4248 static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.thread_local_top_)),
4249 Internals::kIsolateThreadLocalTopOffset);
4250 CHECK_EQ(
4251 static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.handle_scope_data_)),
4252 Internals::kIsolateHandleScopeDataOffset);
4253 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.embedder_data_)),
4254 Internals::kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset);
4255#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
4256 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(
4257 OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.external_pointer_table_)),
4258 Internals::kIsolateExternalPointerTableOffset);
4259
4260 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(
4261 Isolate, isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_)),
4262 Internals::kIsolateSharedExternalPointerTableAddressOffset);
4263#endif
4264#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4265 CHECK_EQ(
4266 static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.trusted_cage_base_)),
4267 Internals::kIsolateTrustedCageBaseOffset);
4268
4269 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(
4270 OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.trusted_pointer_table_)),
4271 Internals::kIsolateTrustedPointerTableOffset);
4272
4273 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(
4274 OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_)),
4275 Internals::kIsolateSharedTrustedPointerTableAddressOffset);
4276#endif
4277 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(
4278 OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.api_callback_thunk_argument_)),
4279 Internals::kIsolateApiCallbackThunkArgumentOffset);
4280 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(
4281 Isolate, isolate_data_.continuation_preserved_embedder_data_)),
4282 Internals::kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset);
4283
4284 CHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.roots_table_)),
4285 Internals::kIsolateRootsOffset);
4286
4287 CHECK(IsAligned(reinterpret_cast<Address>(&isolate_data_),
4288 kIsolateDataAlignment));
4289
4290 static_assert(Internals::kStackGuardSize == sizeof(StackGuard));
4291 static_assert(Internals::kBuiltinTier0TableSize ==
4292 Builtins::kBuiltinTier0Count * kSystemPointerSize);
4293 static_assert(Internals::kBuiltinTier0EntryTableSize ==
4294 Builtins::kBuiltinTier0Count * kSystemPointerSize);
4295
4296 // Ensure that certain hot IsolateData fields fall into the same CPU cache
4297 // line.
4298 constexpr size_t kCacheLineSize = 64;
4299 static_assert(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_) == 0);
4300
4301 // Fields written on every CEntry/CallApiCallback/CallApiGetter call.
4302 // See MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame/LeaveExitFrame.
4303 constexpr size_t kCEntryFPCacheLine = RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4304 OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, thread_local_top_.c_entry_fp_));
4305 static_assert(kCEntryFPCacheLine ==
4306 RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4307 OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, thread_local_top_.c_function_)));
4308 static_assert(kCEntryFPCacheLine ==
4309 RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4310 OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, thread_local_top_.context_)));
4311 static_assert(
4312 kCEntryFPCacheLine ==
4313 RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(
4314 IsolateData, thread_local_top_.topmost_script_having_context_)));
4315 static_assert(kCEntryFPCacheLine ==
4316 RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4317 OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, thread_local_top_.last_api_entry_)));
4318
4319 // Fields written on every MacroAssembler::CallCFunction call.
4320 static_assert(RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4321 OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, fast_c_call_caller_fp_)) ==
4322 RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4323 OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, fast_c_call_caller_pc_)));
4324
4325 // LinearAllocationArea objects must not cross cache line boundary.
4326 static_assert(
4327 RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, new_allocation_info_)) ==
4328 RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, new_allocation_info_) +
4329 sizeof(LinearAllocationArea) - 1));
4330 static_assert(
4331 RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, old_allocation_info_)) ==
4332 RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, old_allocation_info_) +
4333 sizeof(LinearAllocationArea) - 1));
4334}

4336void Isolate::ClearSerializerData() {
4337 delete external_reference_map_;
4338 external_reference_map_ = nullptr;
4339}

4341// When profiling status changes, call this function to update the single bool
4342// cache.
4343void Isolate::UpdateLogObjectRelocation() {
4344 log_object_relocation_ = v8_flags.verify_predictable ||
4345 IsLoggingCodeCreation() ||
4346 v8_file_logger()->is_logging() ||
4347 (heap_profiler() != nullptr &&
4348 heap_profiler()->is_tracking_object_moves()) ||
4349 heap()->has_heap_object_allocation_tracker();

4351
4352void Isolate::Deinit() {
4353 TRACE_ISOLATE(deinit);
4354
4355#if defined(V8_USE_PERFETTO)
4356 PerfettoLogger::UnregisterIsolate(this);
4357#endif // defined(V8_USE_PERFETTO)
4358
4359 // All client isolates should already be detached when the shared heap isolate
4360 // tears down.
4361 if (is_shared_space_isolate()) {
4362 global_safepoint()->AssertNoClientsOnTearDown();
4363 }
4364
4365 if (has_shared_space() && !is_shared_space_isolate()) {
4366 IgnoreLocalGCRequests ignore_gc_requests(heap());
4367 main_thread_local_heap()->ExecuteMainThreadWhileParked([this]() {
4368 shared_space_isolate()->global_safepoint()->clients_mutex_.Lock();
4369 });
4370 }
4371
4372 // We start with the heap tear down so that releasing managed objects does
4373 // not cause a GC.
4374 heap_.StartTearDown();
4375
4376 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4377 IgnoreLocalGCRequests ignore_gc_requests(heap());
4378
4379#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY && V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
4380 if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
4381 wasm::WasmInterpreter::NotifyIsolateDisposal(this);
4382 } else if (v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms &&
4383 v8_flags.slow_histograms) {
4384 wasm_execution_timer_->Terminate();
4385 }
4386#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY && V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
4387
4388 tracing_cpu_profiler_.reset();
4389 if (v8_flags.stress_sampling_allocation_profiler > 0) {
4390 heap_profiler()->StopSamplingHeapProfiler();
4391 }
4392
4393 metrics_recorder_->NotifyIsolateDisposal();
4394 recorder_context_id_map_.clear();
4395
4396 FutexEmulation::IsolateDeinit(this);
4397 if (v8_flags.harmony_struct) {
4398 JSSynchronizationPrimitive::IsolateDeinit(this);
4399 } else {
4400 DCHECK(async_waiter_queue_nodes_.empty());
4401 }
4402
4403 debug()->Unload();
4404
4405#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4406 wasm::GetWasmEngine()->DeleteCompileJobsOnIsolate(this);
4407
4408 BackingStore::RemoveSharedWasmMemoryObjects(this);
4409#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4410
4411 if (concurrent_recompilation_enabled()) {
4412 optimizing_compile_dispatcher_->Stop();
4413 delete optimizing_compile_dispatcher_;
4414 optimizing_compile_dispatcher_ = nullptr;
4415 }
4416
4417 if (v8_flags.print_deopt_stress) {
4418 PrintF(stdout, "=== Stress deopt counter: %u\n", stress_deopt_count_);
4419 }
4420
4421 // We must stop the logger before we tear down other components.
4422 sampler::Sampler* sampler = v8_file_logger_->sampler();
4423 if (sampler && sampler->IsActive()) sampler->Stop();
4424 v8_file_logger_->StopProfilerThread();
4425
4426 FreeThreadResources();
4427
4428 // Stop concurrent tasks before destroying resources since they might still
4429 // use those.
4430 cancelable_task_manager()->CancelAndWait();
4431
4432 // Delete any remaining RegExpResultVector instances.
4433 for (int32_t* v : active_dynamic_regexp_result_vectors_) {
4434 delete[] v;
4435 }
4436 active_dynamic_regexp_result_vectors_.clear();
4437
4438 // Cancel all compiler tasks.
4439#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SPARKPLUG
4440 delete baseline_batch_compiler_;
4441 baseline_batch_compiler_ = nullptr;
4442#endif // V8_ENABLE_SPARKPLUG
4443
4444#ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
4445 delete maglev_concurrent_dispatcher_;
4446 maglev_concurrent_dispatcher_ = nullptr;
4447#endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
4448
4449 if (lazy_compile_dispatcher_) {
4450 lazy_compile_dispatcher_->AbortAll();
4451 lazy_compile_dispatcher_.reset();
4452 }
4453
4454 // At this point there are no more background threads left in this isolate.
4455 heap_.safepoint()->AssertMainThreadIsOnlyThread();
4456
4457 // Tear down data that requires the shared heap before detaching.
4458 heap_.TearDownWithSharedHeap();
4459 DumpAndResetBuiltinsProfileData();
4460
4461 // Detach from the shared heap isolate and then unlock the mutex.
4462 if (has_shared_space() && !is_shared_space_isolate()) {
4463 GlobalSafepoint* global_safepoint =
4464 this->shared_space_isolate()->global_safepoint();
4465 global_safepoint->RemoveClient(this);
4466 global_safepoint->clients_mutex_.Unlock();
4467 }
4468
4469 shared_space_isolate_.reset();
4470
4471 // Since there are no other threads left, we can lock this mutex without any
4472 // ceremony. This signals to the tear down code that we are in a safepoint.
4473 base::RecursiveMutexGuard safepoint(&heap_.safepoint()->local_heaps_mutex_);
4474
4475 ReleaseSharedPtrs();
4476
4477 builtins_.TearDown();
4478 bootstrapper_->TearDown();
4479
4480 if (tiering_manager_ != nullptr) {
4481 delete tiering_manager_;
4482 tiering_manager_ = nullptr;
4483 }
4484
4485 delete heap_profiler_;
4486 heap_profiler_ = nullptr;
4487
4488#if USE_SIMULATOR
4489 delete simulator_data_;
4490 simulator_data_ = nullptr;
4491#endif
4492
4493 // After all concurrent tasks are stopped, we know for sure that stats aren't
4494 // updated anymore.
4495 DumpAndResetStats();
4496
4497 heap_.TearDown();
4498 ReadOnlyHeap::TearDown(this);
4499
4500 delete inner_pointer_to_code_cache_;
4501 inner_pointer_to_code_cache_ = nullptr;
4502
4503 main_thread_local_isolate_.reset();
4504
4505 FILE* logfile = v8_file_logger_->TearDownAndGetLogFile();
4506 if (logfile != nullptr) base::Fclose(logfile);
4507
4508#if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
4509 if (v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking ||
4510 v8_flags.enable_etw_by_custom_filter_only) {
4511 ETWJITInterface::RemoveIsolate(this);
4512 }
4513#endif // defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
4514
4515#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4516 wasm::GetWasmEngine()->RemoveIsolate(this);
4517
4518 delete wasm_code_look_up_cache_;
4519 wasm_code_look_up_cache_ = nullptr;
4520#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4521
4522 TearDownEmbeddedBlob();
4523
4524 delete interpreter_;
4525 interpreter_ = nullptr;
4526
4527 delete ast_string_constants_;
4528 ast_string_constants_ = nullptr;
4529
4530 delete logger_;
4531 logger_ = nullptr;
4532
4533 delete root_index_map_;
4534 root_index_map_ = nullptr;
4535
4536 delete compiler_zone_;
4537 compiler_zone_ = nullptr;
4538 compiler_cache_ = nullptr;
4539
4540 SetCodePages(nullptr);
4541
4542 ClearSerializerData();
4543
4544 if (OwnsStringTables()) {
4545 string_forwarding_table()->TearDown();
4546 } else {
4547 DCHECK_NULL(string_table_.get());
4548 DCHECK_NULL(string_forwarding_table_.get());
4549 }
4550
4551 if (!is_shared_space_isolate()) {
4552 DCHECK_NULL(shared_struct_type_registry_.get());
4553 }
4554
4555#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
4556 external_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(
4557 heap()->young_external_pointer_space());
4558 external_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(heap()->old_external_pointer_space());
4559 external_pointer_table().DetachSpaceFromReadOnlySegment(
4560 heap()->read_only_external_pointer_space());
4561 external_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(
4562 heap()->read_only_external_pointer_space());
4563 external_pointer_table().TearDown();
4564 if (owns_shareable_data()) {
4565 shared_external_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(
4566 shared_external_pointer_space());
4567 shared_external_pointer_table().TearDown();
4568 delete isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_;
4569 isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_ = nullptr;
4570 delete shared_external_pointer_space_;
4571 shared_external_pointer_space_ = nullptr;
4572 }
4573 cpp_heap_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(heap()->cpp_heap_pointer_space());
4574 cpp_heap_pointer_table().TearDown();
4575#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
4576
4577#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4578 trusted_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(heap()->trusted_pointer_space());
4579 trusted_pointer_table().TearDown();
4580 if (owns_shareable_data()) {
4581 shared_trusted_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(
4582 shared_trusted_pointer_space());
4583 shared_trusted_pointer_table().TearDown();
4584 delete isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_;
4585 isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_ = nullptr;
4586 delete shared_trusted_pointer_space_;
4587 shared_trusted_pointer_space_ = nullptr;
4588 }
4589
4590 IsolateGroup::current()->code_pointer_table()->TearDownSpace(
4591 heap()->code_pointer_space());
4592#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4593#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4594 IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->TearDownSpace(
4595 heap()->js_dispatch_table_space());
4596#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4597
4598 {
4599 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&thread_data_table_mutex_);
4600 thread_data_table_.RemoveAllThreads();
4601 }
4602}

4604void Isolate::SetIsolateThreadLocals(Isolate* isolate,
4605 PerIsolateThreadData* data) {
4606 Isolate::SetCurrent(isolate);
4607 g_current_per_isolate_thread_data_ = data;
4608
4609#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_MULTIPLE_CAGES
4610 V8HeapCompressionScheme::InitBase(isolate ? isolate->cage_base()
4611 : kNullAddress);
4612 IsolateGroup::set_current(isolate ? isolate->isolate_group() : nullptr);
4613#ifdef V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
4614 ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::InitBase(isolate ? isolate->code_cage_base()
4615 : kNullAddress);
4616#endif
4617#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4618 Sandbox::set_current(isolate ? isolate->isolate_group()->sandbox() : nullptr);
4619#endif
4620#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_MULTIPLE_CAGES
4621
4622 if (isolate && isolate->main_thread_local_isolate()) {
4623 WriteBarrier::SetForThread(
4624 isolate->main_thread_local_heap()->marking_barrier());
4625 } else {
4626 WriteBarrier::SetForThread(nullptr);
4627 }
4628}

4716void Isolate::InitializeThreadLocal() {
4717 thread_local_top()->Initialize(this);
4718#ifdef DEBUG
4719 // This method might be called on a thread that's not bound to any Isolate
4720 // and thus pointer compression schemes might have cage base value unset.
4721 // Read-only roots accessors contain type DCHECKs which require access to
4722 // V8 heap in order to check the object type. So, allow heap access here
4723 // to let the checks work.
4724 i::PtrComprCageAccessScope ptr_compr_cage_access_scope(this);
4725#endif // DEBUG
4726 clear_exception();
4727 clear_pending_message();
4728}
4729
4730void Isolate::SetTerminationOnExternalTryCatch() {
4731 DCHECK_IMPLIES(v8_flags.strict_termination_checks,
4732 is_execution_terminating());
4733 if (try_catch_handler() == nullptr) return;
4734 try_catch_handler()->can_continue_ = false;
4735 try_catch_handler()->exception_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(
4736 ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).termination_exception().ptr());
4737}
4738
4739bool Isolate::PropagateExceptionToExternalTryCatch(
4740 ExceptionHandlerType top_handler) {
4741 Tagged<Object> exception = this->exception();
4742
4743 if (top_handler == ExceptionHandlerType::kJavaScriptHandler) return false;
4744 if (top_handler == ExceptionHandlerType::kNone) return true;
4745
4746 DCHECK_EQ(ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch, top_handler);
4747 if (!is_catchable_by_javascript(exception)) {
4748 SetTerminationOnExternalTryCatch();
4749 } else {
4750 v8::TryCatch* handler = try_catch_handler();
4751 DCHECK(IsJSMessageObject(pending_message()) ||
4752 IsTheHole(pending_message(), this));
4753 handler->can_continue_ = true;
4754 handler->exception_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(exception.ptr());
4755 // Propagate to the external try-catch only if we got an actual message.
4756 if (!has_pending_message()) return true;
4757 handler->message_obj_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(pending_message().ptr());
4758 }
4759 return true;
4760}
4761
4762namespace {
4763
4764inline Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> GetTargetFunctionTemplateInfo(
4765 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
4766 Tagged<Object> target = FunctionCallbackArguments::GetTarget(info);
4767 if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(target)) {
4768 return Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(target);
4769 }
4770 CHECK(Is<JSFunction>(target));
4771 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = Cast<JSFunction>(target)->shared();
4772 return shared_info->api_func_data();
4773}
4774
4775} // namespace
4776
4777void Isolate::NotifyExceptionPropagationCallback() {
4778 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(exception_propagation_callback_);
4779
4780 // Try to figure out whether the exception was thrown directly from an
4781 // Api callback and if it's the case then call the
4782 // |exception_propagation_callback_| with relevant data.
4783
4784 ExternalCallbackScope* ext_callback_scope = external_callback_scope();
4785 StackFrameIterator it(this);
4786
4787 if (it.done() && !ext_callback_scope) {
4788 // The exception was thrown directly by embedder code without crossing
4789 // "C++ -> JS" or "C++ -> Api callback" boundary.
4790 return;
4791 }
4792 if (it.done() ||
4793 (ext_callback_scope &&
4794 ext_callback_scope->JSStackComparableAddress() < it.frame()->fp())) {
4795 // There were no crossings of "C++ -> JS" boundary at all or they happened
4796 // earlier than the last crossing of the "C++ -> Api callback" boundary.
4797 // In this case all the data about Api callback is available in the
4798 // |ext_callback_scope| object.
4799 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(ext_callback_scope);
4800 v8::ExceptionContext kind = ext_callback_scope->exception_context();
4801 switch (kind) {
4802 case v8::ExceptionContext::kConstructor:
4803 case v8::ExceptionContext::kOperation: {
4804 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(ext_callback_scope->callback_info());
4805 auto callback_info =
4806 reinterpret_cast<const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>*>(
4807 ext_callback_scope->callback_info());
4808
4809 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver =
4810 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*callback_info->This());
4811 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info(
4812 GetTargetFunctionTemplateInfo(*callback_info), this);
4813 ReportExceptionFunctionCallback(receiver, function_template_info, kind);
4814 return;
4815 }
4816 case v8::ExceptionContext::kAttributeGet:
4817 case v8::ExceptionContext::kAttributeSet:
4818 case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedQuery:
4819 case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedGetter:
4820 case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedDescriptor:
4821 case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedSetter:
4822 case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedDefiner:
4823 case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedDeleter:
4824 case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedQuery:
4825 case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedGetter:
4826 case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedDescriptor:
4827 case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedSetter:
4828 case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedDefiner:
4829 case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedDeleter:
4830 case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedEnumerator: {
4831 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(ext_callback_scope->callback_info());
4832 auto callback_info =
4833 reinterpret_cast<const v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>*>(
4834 ext_callback_scope->callback_info());
4835
4836 // Allow usages of v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<T>::Holder() for now.
4837 // TODO(https://crbug.com/333672197): remove.
4838 START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
4839
4840 DirectHandle<Object> holder =
4841 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*callback_info->Holder());
4842 Handle<Object> maybe_name =
4843 PropertyCallbackArguments::GetPropertyKeyHandle(*callback_info);
4844 Handle<Name> name =
4845 IsSmi(*maybe_name)
4846 ? factory()->SizeToString(
4847 PropertyCallbackArguments::GetPropertyIndex(
4848 *callback_info))
4849 : Cast<Name>(maybe_name);
4850 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*holder));
4851
4852 // Allow usages of v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<T>::Holder() for now.
4853 // TODO(https://crbug.com/333672197): remove.
4854 END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
4855
4856 // Currently we call only ApiGetters from JS code.
4857 ReportExceptionPropertyCallback(Cast<JSReceiver>(holder), name, kind);
4858 return;
4859 }
4860
4861 case v8::ExceptionContext::kUnknown:
4862 DCHECK_WITH_MSG(kind != v8::ExceptionContext::kUnknown,
4863 "ExternalCallbackScope should not use "
4864 "v8::ExceptionContext::kUnknown exception context");
4865 return;
4866 }
4867 UNREACHABLE();
4868 }
4869
4870 // There were no crossings of "C++ -> Api callback" bondary or they
4871 // happened before crossing the "C++ -> JS" boundary.
4872 // In this case all the data about Api callback is available in the
4873 // topmost "JS -> Api callback" frame (ApiCallbackExitFrame or
4874 // ApiAccessorExitFrame).
4875 DCHECK(!it.done());
4876 StackFrame::Type frame_type = it.frame()->type();
4877 switch (frame_type) {
4878 case StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT: {
4879 ApiCallbackExitFrame* frame = ApiCallbackExitFrame::cast(it.frame());
4880 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver(Cast<JSReceiver>(frame->receiver()),
4881 this);
4882 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info =
4883 frame->GetFunctionTemplateInfo();
4884
4885 v8::ExceptionContext callback_kind =
4886 frame->IsConstructor() ? v8::ExceptionContext::kConstructor
4887 : v8::ExceptionContext::kOperation;
4888 ReportExceptionFunctionCallback(receiver, function_template_info,
4889 callback_kind);
4890 return;
4891 }
4892 case StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT: {
4893 ApiAccessorExitFrame* frame = ApiAccessorExitFrame::cast(it.frame());
4894
4895 DirectHandle<Object> holder(frame->holder(), this);
4896 Handle<Name> name(frame->property_name(), this);
4897 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*holder));
4898
4899 // Currently we call only ApiGetters from JS code.
4900 ReportExceptionPropertyCallback(Cast<JSReceiver>(holder), name,
4901 v8::ExceptionContext::kAttributeGet);
4902 return;
4903 }
4904 case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS:
4905 // This must be a fast Api call.
4906 CHECK(it.frame()->InFastCCall());
4907 // TODO(ishell): support fast Api calls.
4908 return;
4909 case StackFrame::EXIT:
4910 case StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT:
4911 // This is a regular runtime function or C++ builtin.
4912 return;
4913#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4914 case StackFrame::WASM:
4915 case StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START:
4916 // No more info.
4917 return;
4918#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4919 default:
4920 // Other types are not expected, so just hard-crash.
4921 CHECK_NE(frame_type, frame_type);
4922 }
4923}
4924
4925void Isolate::ReportExceptionFunctionCallback(
4926 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
4927 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function,
4928 v8::ExceptionContext exception_context) {
4929 DCHECK(exception_context == v8::ExceptionContext::kConstructor ||
4930 exception_context == v8::ExceptionContext::kOperation);
4931 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(exception_propagation_callback_);
4932
4933 // Ignore exceptions that we can't extend.
4934 if (!IsJSReceiver(this->exception())) return;
4935 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> exception(Cast<JSReceiver>(this->exception()), this);
4936
4937 DirectHandle<Object> maybe_message(pending_message(), this);
4938
4939 DirectHandle<String> property_name =
4940 IsUndefined(function->class_name(), this)
4941 ? factory()->empty_string()
4942 : Handle<String>(Cast<String>(function->class_name()), this);
4943 DirectHandle<String> interface_name =
4944 IsUndefined(function->interface_name(), this)
4945 ? factory()->empty_string()
4946 : Handle<String>(Cast<String>(function->interface_name()), this);
4947 if (exception_context != ExceptionContext::kConstructor) {
4948 exception_context =
4949 static_cast<ExceptionContext>(function->exception_context());
4950 }
4951
4952 {
4953 v8::Isolate* v8_isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this);
4954 // Ignore any exceptions thrown inside the callback and rethrow the
4955 // original exception/message.
4956 TryCatch try_catch(v8_isolate);
4957
4958 exception_propagation_callback_(v8::ExceptionPropagationMessage(
4959 v8_isolate, v8::Utils::ToLocal(exception),
4960 v8::Utils::ToLocal(interface_name), v8::Utils::ToLocal(property_name),
4961 exception_context));
4962
4963 try_catch.Reset();
4964 }
4965 ReThrow(*exception, *maybe_message);
4966}
4967
4968void Isolate::ReportExceptionPropertyCallback(
4969 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> holder, Handle<Name> name,
4970 v8::ExceptionContext exception_context) {
4971 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(exception_propagation_callback_);
4972
4973 if (!IsJSReceiver(this->exception())) return;
4974 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> exception(Cast<JSReceiver>(this->exception()), this);
4975
4976 DirectHandle<Object> maybe_message(pending_message(), this);
4977
4978 DirectHandle<String> property_name;
4979 std::ignore = Name::ToFunctionName(this, name).ToHandle(&property_name);
4980 DirectHandle<String> interface_name =
4981 JSReceiver::GetConstructorName(this, holder);
4982
4983 {
4984 v8::Isolate* v8_isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this);
4985 // Ignore any exceptions thrown inside the callback and rethrow the
4986 // original exception/message.
4987 TryCatch try_catch(v8_isolate);
4988
4989 exception_propagation_callback_(v8::ExceptionPropagationMessage(
4990 v8_isolate, v8::Utils::ToLocal(exception),
4991 v8::Utils::ToLocal(interface_name), v8::Utils::ToLocal(property_name),
4992 exception_context));
4993
4994 try_catch.Reset();
4995 }
4996 ReThrow(*exception, *maybe_message);
4997}
4998
4999void Isolate::SetExceptionPropagationCallback(
5000 ExceptionPropagationCallback callback) {
5001 exception_propagation_callback_ = callback;
5002}

5017namespace {
5018
5019void FinalizeBuiltinCodeObjects(Isolate* isolate) {
5020 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate->embedded_blob_code());
5021 DCHECK_NE(0, isolate->embedded_blob_code_size());
5022 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate->embedded_blob_data());
5023 DCHECK_NE(0, isolate->embedded_blob_data_size());
5024
5025 EmbeddedData d = EmbeddedData::FromBlob(isolate);
5026 HandleScope scope(isolate);
5027 static_assert(Builtins::kAllBuiltinsAreIsolateIndependent);
5028 for (Builtin builtin = Builtins::kFirst; builtin <= Builtins::kLast;
5029 ++builtin) {
5030 DirectHandle<Code> old_code = isolate->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
5031 // Note that `old_code.instruction_start` might point to `old_code`'s
5032 // InstructionStream which might be GCed once we replace the old code
5033 // with the new code.
5034 Address instruction_start = d.InstructionStartOf(builtin);
5035 DirectHandle<Code> new_code =
5036 isolate->factory()->NewCodeObjectForEmbeddedBuiltin(old_code,
5037 instruction_start);
5038
5039 // From this point onwards, the old builtin code object is unreachable and
5040 // will be collected by the next GC.
5041 isolate->builtins()->set_code(builtin, *new_code);
5042 }
5043}
5044
5045#ifdef DEBUG
5046bool IsolateIsCompatibleWithEmbeddedBlob(Isolate* isolate) {
5047 EmbeddedData d = EmbeddedData::FromBlob(isolate);
5048 return (d.IsolateHash() == isolate->HashIsolateForEmbeddedBlob());
5049}
5050#endif // DEBUG
5051
5052} // namespace
5053
5054void Isolate::InitializeDefaultEmbeddedBlob() {
5055 const uint8_t* code = DefaultEmbeddedBlobCode();
5056 uint32_t code_size = DefaultEmbeddedBlobCodeSize();
5057 const uint8_t* data = DefaultEmbeddedBlobData();
5058 uint32_t data_size = DefaultEmbeddedBlobDataSize();
5059
5060 if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() != nullptr) {
5061 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(
5062 current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
5063 // Check again now that we hold the lock.
5064 if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() != nullptr) {
5065 code = StickyEmbeddedBlobCode();
5066 code_size = StickyEmbeddedBlobCodeSize();
5067 data = StickyEmbeddedBlobData();
5068 data_size = StickyEmbeddedBlobDataSize();
5069 current_embedded_blob_refs_++;
5070 }
5071 }
5072
5073 if (code_size == 0) {
5074 CHECK_EQ(0, data_size);
5075 } else {
5076 SetEmbeddedBlob(code, code_size, data, data_size);
5077 }
5078}
5079
5080void Isolate::CreateAndSetEmbeddedBlob() {
5081 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(
5082 current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
5083
5084 PrepareBuiltinSourcePositionMap();
5085
5086 // If a sticky blob has been set, we reuse it.
5087 if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() != nullptr) {
5088 CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_code(), StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
5089 CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_data(), StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
5090 CHECK_EQ(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode(), StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
5091 CHECK_EQ(CurrentEmbeddedBlobData(), StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
5092 } else {
5093 // Create and set a new embedded blob.
5094 uint8_t* code;
5095 uint32_t code_size;
5096 uint8_t* data;
5097 uint32_t data_size;
5098 OffHeapInstructionStream::CreateOffHeapOffHeapInstructionStream(
5099 this, &code, &code_size, &data, &data_size);
5100
5101 CHECK_EQ(0, current_embedded_blob_refs_);
5102 const uint8_t* const_code = const_cast<const uint8_t*>(code);
5103 const uint8_t* const_data = const_cast<const uint8_t*>(data);
5104 SetEmbeddedBlob(const_code, code_size, const_data, data_size);
5105 current_embedded_blob_refs_++;
5106
5107 SetStickyEmbeddedBlob(code, code_size, data, data_size);
5108 }
5109
5110 MaybeRemapEmbeddedBuiltinsIntoCodeRange();
5111 FinalizeBuiltinCodeObjects(this);
5112}
5113
5114void Isolate::InitializeIsShortBuiltinCallsEnabled() {
5115 if (V8_SHORT_BUILTIN_CALLS_BOOL && v8_flags.short_builtin_calls) {
5116#if defined(V8_OS_ANDROID)
5117 // On Android, the check is not operative to detect memory, and re-embedded
5118 // builtins don't have a memory cost.
5119 is_short_builtin_calls_enabled_ = true;
5120#else
5121 // Check if the system has more than 4GB of physical memory by comparing the
5122 // old space size with respective threshold value.
5123 is_short_builtin_calls_enabled_ = (heap_.MaxOldGenerationSize() >=
5124 kShortBuiltinCallsOldSpaceSizeThreshold);
5125#endif // defined(V8_OS_ANDROID)
5126 // Additionally, enable if there is already a process-wide CodeRange that
5127 // has re-embedded builtins.
5128 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
5129 CodeRange* code_range = isolate_group()->GetCodeRange();
5130 if (code_range && code_range->embedded_blob_code_copy() != nullptr) {
5131 is_short_builtin_calls_enabled_ = true;
5132 }
5133 }
5134 if (V8_ENABLE_NEAR_CODE_RANGE_BOOL) {
5135 // The short builtin calls could still be enabled if allocated code range
5136 // is close enough to embedded builtins so that the latter could be
5137 // reached using pc-relative (short) calls/jumps.
5138 is_short_builtin_calls_enabled_ |=
5139 GetShortBuiltinsCallRegion().contains(heap_.code_region());
5140 }
5141 }
5142}
5143
5144void Isolate::MaybeRemapEmbeddedBuiltinsIntoCodeRange() {
5145 if (!is_short_builtin_calls_enabled() || !RequiresCodeRange()) {
5146 return;
5147 }
5148 if (V8_ENABLE_NEAR_CODE_RANGE_BOOL &&
5149 GetShortBuiltinsCallRegion().contains(heap_.code_region())) {
5150 // The embedded builtins are within the pc-relative reach from the code
5151 // range, so there's no need to remap embedded builtins.
5152 return;
5153 }
5154
5155 CHECK_NOT_NULL(embedded_blob_code_);
5156 CHECK_NE(embedded_blob_code_size_, 0);
5157
5158 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(heap_.code_range_);
5159 embedded_blob_code_ = heap_.code_range_->RemapEmbeddedBuiltins(
5160 this, embedded_blob_code_, embedded_blob_code_size_);
5161 CHECK_NOT_NULL(embedded_blob_code_);
5162 // The un-embedded code blob is already a part of the registered code range
5163 // so it's not necessary to register it again.
5164}
5165
5166void Isolate::TearDownEmbeddedBlob() {
5167 // Nothing to do in case the blob is embedded into the binary or unset.
5168 if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() == nullptr) return;
5169
5170 if (!is_short_builtin_calls_enabled()) {
5171 CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_code(), StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
5172 CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_data(), StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
5173 }
5174 CHECK_EQ(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode(), StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
5175 CHECK_EQ(CurrentEmbeddedBlobData(), StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
5176
5177 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(
5178 current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
5179 current_embedded_blob_refs_--;
5180 if (current_embedded_blob_refs_ == 0 && enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_) {
5181 // We own the embedded blob and are the last holder. Free it.
5182 OffHeapInstructionStream::FreeOffHeapOffHeapInstructionStream(
5183 const_cast<uint8_t*>(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode()),
5184 embedded_blob_code_size(),
5185 const_cast<uint8_t*>(CurrentEmbeddedBlobData()),
5186 embedded_blob_data_size());
5187 ClearEmbeddedBlob();
5188 }
5189}

5206namespace {
5207static std::string ToHexString(uintptr_t address) {
5208 std::stringstream stream_address;
5209 stream_address << "0x" << std::hex << address;
5210 return stream_address.str();
5211}
5212} // namespace
5213
5214void Isolate::AddCrashKeysForIsolateAndHeapPointers() {
5215 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(add_crash_key_callback_);
5216
5217 const uintptr_t isolate_address = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(this);
5218 add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kIsolateAddress,
5219 ToHexString(isolate_address));
5220
5221 const uintptr_t ro_space_firstpage_address =
5222 heap()->read_only_space()->FirstPageAddress();
5223 add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kReadonlySpaceFirstPageAddress,
5224 ToHexString(ro_space_firstpage_address));
5225
5226 const uintptr_t old_space_firstpage_address =
5227 heap()->old_space()->FirstPageAddress();
5228 add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kOldSpaceFirstPageAddress,
5229 ToHexString(old_space_firstpage_address));
5230
5231 if (heap()->code_range_base()) {
5232 const uintptr_t code_range_base_address = heap()->code_range_base();
5233 add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kCodeRangeBaseAddress,
5234 ToHexString(code_range_base_address));
5235 }
5236
5237 if (heap()->code_space()->first_page()) {
5238 const uintptr_t code_space_firstpage_address =
5239 heap()->code_space()->FirstPageAddress();
5240 add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kCodeSpaceFirstPageAddress,
5241 ToHexString(code_space_firstpage_address));
5242 }
5243 const v8::StartupData* data = Snapshot::DefaultSnapshotBlob();
5244 // TODO(cbruni): Implement strategy to infrequently collect this.
5245 const uint32_t v8_snapshot_checksum_calculated = 0;
5246 add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kSnapshotChecksumCalculated,
5247 ToHexString(v8_snapshot_checksum_calculated));
5248 const uint32_t v8_snapshot_checksum_expected =
5249 Snapshot::GetExpectedChecksum(data);
5250 add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kSnapshotChecksumExpected,
5251 ToHexString(v8_snapshot_checksum_expected));
5252}

5265// This global counter contains number of stack loads/stores per optimized/wasm
5266// function.
5267using MapOfLoadsAndStoresPerFunction =
5268 std::map<std::string /* function_name */,
5269 std::pair<uint64_t /* loads */, uint64_t /* stores */>>;
5270MapOfLoadsAndStoresPerFunction* stack_access_count_map = nullptr;

5294
5295void Isolate::VerifyStaticRoots() {
5296#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
5297#define STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG \
5298 "Read-only heap layout changed. Run `tools/dev/gen-static-roots.py` to " \
5299 "update static-roots.h."
5300 static_assert(static_cast<int>(RootIndex::kReadOnlyRootsCount) ==
5301 StaticReadOnlyRootsPointerTable.size(),
5302 STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG);
5303 auto& roots = roots_table();
5304 RootIndex idx = RootIndex::kFirstReadOnlyRoot;
5305 for (Tagged_t cmp_ptr : StaticReadOnlyRootsPointerTable) {
5306 Address the_root = roots[idx];
5307 Address ptr =
5308 V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(cage_base(), cmp_ptr);
5309 CHECK_WITH_MSG(the_root == ptr, STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG);
5310 ++idx;
5311 }
5312
5313 idx = RootIndex::kFirstReadOnlyRoot;
5314#define CHECK_NAME(_1, _2, CamelName) \
5315 CHECK_WITH_MSG(StaticReadOnlyRoot::k##CamelName == \
5316 V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(roots[idx]), \
5317 STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG); \
5318 ++idx;
5319 STRONG_READ_ONLY_ROOT_LIST(CHECK_NAME)
5320#undef CHECK_NAME
5321
5322 // Check if instance types to map range mappings are still valid.
5323 //
5324 // Is##type(map) may be computed by checking if the map pointer lies in a
5325 // statically known range of addresses, whereas Is##type(instance_type) is the
5326 // definitive source of truth. If they disagree it means that a particular
5327 // entry in InstanceTypeChecker::kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRangeList is out
5328 // of date. This can also happen if an instance type is starting to be used by
5329 // more maps.
5330 //
5331 // If this check fails either re-arrange allocations in the read-only heap
5332 // such that the static map range is restored (consult static-roots.h for a
5333 // sorted list of addresses) or remove the offending entry from the list.
5334 for (auto idx = RootIndex::kFirstRoot; idx <= RootIndex::kLastRoot; ++idx) {
5335 Tagged<Object> obj = roots_table().slot(idx).load(this);
5336 if (obj.ptr() == kNullAddress || !IsMap(obj)) continue;
5337 Tagged<Map> map = Cast<Map>(obj);
5338
5339#define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_SINGLE(type, _) \
5340 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::Is##type(map), \
5341 InstanceTypeChecker::Is##type(map->instance_type()));
5342 INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS_SINGLE(INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_SINGLE)
5343#undef INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_SINGLE
5344
5345#define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE(type, _1, _2) \
5346 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::Is##type(map), \
5347 InstanceTypeChecker::Is##type(map->instance_type()));
5348 INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS_RANGE(INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE)
5349#undef INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE
5350
5351 // This limit is used in various places as a fast IsJSReceiver check.
5352 CHECK_IMPLIES(
5353 InstanceTypeChecker::IsPrimitiveHeapObject(map->instance_type()),
5354 V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(map.ptr()) <
5355 InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit);
5356 CHECK_IMPLIES(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(map->instance_type()),
5357 V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(map.ptr()) >=
5358 InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit);
5359 CHECK(InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit <
5360 read_only_heap()->read_only_space()->Size());
5361
5362 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(map->instance_type())) {
5363 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(map),
5364 InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(map->instance_type()));
5365 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsSeqString(map),
5366 InstanceTypeChecker::IsSeqString(map->instance_type()));
5367 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsExternalString(map),
5368 InstanceTypeChecker::IsExternalString(map->instance_type()));
5369 CHECK_EQ(
5370 InstanceTypeChecker::IsUncachedExternalString(map),
5371 InstanceTypeChecker::IsUncachedExternalString(map->instance_type()));
5372 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsInternalizedString(map),
5373 InstanceTypeChecker::IsInternalizedString(map->instance_type()));
5374 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsConsString(map),
5375 InstanceTypeChecker::IsConsString(map->instance_type()));
5376 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsSlicedString(map),
5377 InstanceTypeChecker::IsSlicedString(map->instance_type()));
5378 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsThinString(map),
5379 InstanceTypeChecker::IsThinString(map->instance_type()));
5380 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsOneByteString(map),
5381 InstanceTypeChecker::IsOneByteString(map->instance_type()));
5382 CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsTwoByteString(map),
5383 InstanceTypeChecker::IsTwoByteString(map->instance_type()));
5384 }
5385 }
5386
5387 // Sanity check the API
5388 CHECK_EQ(
5389 v8::internal::Internals::GetRoot(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this),
5390 static_cast<int>(RootIndex::kNullValue)),
5391 ReadOnlyRoots(this).null_value().ptr());
5392#undef STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG
5393#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
5394}
5395
5396bool Isolate::Init(SnapshotData* startup_snapshot_data,
5397 SnapshotData* read_only_snapshot_data,
5398 SnapshotData* shared_heap_snapshot_data, bool can_rehash) {
5399 TRACE_ISOLATE(init);
5400
5401#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_SHARED_CAGE
5402 CHECK_EQ(V8HeapCompressionScheme::base(), cage_base());
5403#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_SHARED_CAGE
5404
5405 const bool create_heap_objects = (shared_heap_snapshot_data == nullptr);
5406 // We either have both or none.
5407 DCHECK_EQ(create_heap_objects, startup_snapshot_data == nullptr);
5408 DCHECK_EQ(create_heap_objects, read_only_snapshot_data == nullptr);
5409
5410 EnableRoAllocationForSnapshotScope enable_ro_allocation(this);
5411
5412 base::ElapsedTimer timer;
5413 if (create_heap_objects && v8_flags.profile_deserialization) timer.Start();
5414
5415 time_millis_at_init_ = heap_.MonotonicallyIncreasingTimeInMs();
5416
5417 Isolate* use_shared_space_isolate = nullptr;
5418
5419 if (v8_flags.shared_heap) {
5420 if (isolate_group_->has_shared_space_isolate()) {
5421 owns_shareable_data_ = false;
5422 use_shared_space_isolate = isolate_group_->shared_space_isolate();
5423 } else {
5424 isolate_group_->init_shared_space_isolate(this);
5425 use_shared_space_isolate = isolate_group_->shared_space_isolate();
5426 is_shared_space_isolate_ = true;
5427 DCHECK(owns_shareable_data_);
5428 }
5429 }
5430
5431 CHECK_IMPLIES(is_shared_space_isolate_, V8_CAN_CREATE_SHARED_HEAP_BOOL);
5432
5433 stress_deopt_count_ = v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times;
5434 force_slow_path_ = v8_flags.force_slow_path;
5435
5436 has_fatal_error_ = false;
5437
5438 // The initialization process does not handle memory exhaustion.
5439 AlwaysAllocateScope always_allocate(heap());
5440
5441#define ASSIGN_ELEMENT(CamelName, hacker_name) \
5442 isolate_addresses_[IsolateAddressId::k##CamelName##Address] = \
5443 reinterpret_cast<Address>(hacker_name##_address());
5444 FOR_EACH_ISOLATE_ADDRESS_NAME(ASSIGN_ELEMENT)
5445#undef ASSIGN_ELEMENT
5446
5447 // We need to initialize code_pages_ before any on-heap code is allocated to
5448 // make sure we record all code allocations.
5449 InitializeCodeRanges();
5450
5451 compilation_cache_ = new CompilationCache(this);
5452 descriptor_lookup_cache_ = new DescriptorLookupCache();
5453 global_handles_ = new GlobalHandles(this);
5454 eternal_handles_ = new EternalHandles();
5455 bootstrapper_ = new Bootstrapper(this);
5456 handle_scope_implementer_ = new HandleScopeImplementer(this);
5457 load_stub_cache_ = new StubCache(this);
5458 store_stub_cache_ = new StubCache(this);
5459 define_own_stub_cache_ = new StubCache(this);
5460 materialized_object_store_ = new MaterializedObjectStore(this);
5461 regexp_stack_ = new RegExpStack();
5462 isolate_data()->set_regexp_static_result_offsets_vector(
5463 jsregexp_static_offsets_vector());
5464 date_cache_ = new DateCache();
5465 heap_profiler_ = new HeapProfiler(heap());
5466 interpreter_ = new interpreter::Interpreter(this);
5467 bigint_processor_ = bigint::Processor::New(new BigIntPlatform(this));
5468
5469 if (is_shared_space_isolate_) {
5470 global_safepoint_ = std::make_unique<GlobalSafepoint>(this);
5471 }
5472
5473 if (v8_flags.lazy_compile_dispatcher) {
5474 lazy_compile_dispatcher_ = std::make_unique<LazyCompileDispatcher>(
5475 this, V8::GetCurrentPlatform(), v8_flags.stack_size);
5476 }
5477#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SPARKPLUG
5478 baseline_batch_compiler_ = new baseline::BaselineBatchCompiler(this);
5479#endif // V8_ENABLE_SPARKPLUG
5480#ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
5481 maglev_concurrent_dispatcher_ = new maglev::MaglevConcurrentDispatcher(this);
5482#endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
5483
5484#if USE_SIMULATOR
5485 simulator_data_ = new SimulatorData;
5486#endif
5487
5488 // Enable logging before setting up the heap
5489 v8_file_logger_->SetUp(this);
5490
5491 metrics_recorder_ = std::make_shared<metrics::Recorder>();
5492
5493 {
5494 // Ensure that the thread has a valid stack guard. The v8::Locker object
5495 // will ensure this too, but we don't have to use lockers if we are only
5496 // using one thread.
5497 ExecutionAccess lock(this);
5498 stack_guard()->InitThread(lock);
5499 }
5500
5501 // Create LocalIsolate/LocalHeap for the main thread and set state to Running.
5502 main_thread_local_isolate_.reset(new LocalIsolate(this, ThreadKind::kMain));
5503
5504 {
5505 IgnoreLocalGCRequests ignore_gc_requests(heap());
5506 main_thread_local_heap()->Unpark();
5507 }
5508
5509 // Requires a LocalHeap to be set up to register a GC epilogue callback.
5510 inner_pointer_to_code_cache_ = new InnerPointerToCodeCache(this);
5511
5512#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5513 wasm_code_look_up_cache_ = new wasm::WasmCodeLookupCache;
5514#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5515
5516 // Lock clients_mutex_ in order to prevent shared GCs from other clients
5517 // during deserialization.
5518 std::optional<base::RecursiveMutexGuard> clients_guard;
5519
5520 if (use_shared_space_isolate && !is_shared_space_isolate()) {
5521 clients_guard.emplace(
5522 &use_shared_space_isolate->global_safepoint()->clients_mutex_);
5523 use_shared_space_isolate->global_safepoint()->AppendClient(this);
5524 }
5525
5526 shared_space_isolate_ = use_shared_space_isolate;
5527
5528 isolate_data_.is_shared_space_isolate_flag_ = is_shared_space_isolate();
5529 isolate_data_.uses_shared_heap_flag_ = has_shared_space();
5530
5531 if (use_shared_space_isolate && !is_shared_space_isolate() &&
5532 use_shared_space_isolate->heap()
5533 ->incremental_marking()
5534 ->IsMajorMarking()) {
5535 heap_.SetIsMarkingFlag(true);
5536 }
5537
5538 // Set up the object heap.
5539 DCHECK(!heap_.HasBeenSetUp());
5540 heap_.SetUp(main_thread_local_heap());
5541 InitializeIsShortBuiltinCallsEnabled();
5542 if (!create_heap_objects) {
5543 // Must be done before deserializing RO space, since RO space may contain
5544 // builtin Code objects which point into the (potentially remapped)
5545 // embedded blob.
5546 MaybeRemapEmbeddedBuiltinsIntoCodeRange();
5547 }
5548 {
5549 // Must be done before deserializing RO space since the deserialization
5550 // process refers to these data structures.
5551 isolate_data_.external_reference_table()->InitIsolateIndependent(
5552 isolate_group()->external_ref_table());
5553#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5554 external_pointer_table().Initialize();
5555 external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5556 heap()->read_only_external_pointer_space());
5557 external_pointer_table().AttachSpaceToReadOnlySegment(
5558 heap()->read_only_external_pointer_space());
5559 external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5560 heap()->young_external_pointer_space());
5561 external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5562 heap()->old_external_pointer_space());
5563 cpp_heap_pointer_table().Initialize();
5564 cpp_heap_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(heap()->cpp_heap_pointer_space());
5565#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5566
5567#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5568 trusted_pointer_table().Initialize();
5569 trusted_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(heap()->trusted_pointer_space());
5570#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5571 }
5572 ReadOnlyHeap::SetUp(this, read_only_snapshot_data, can_rehash);
5573 heap_.SetUpSpaces(isolate_data_.new_allocation_info_,
5574 isolate_data_.old_allocation_info_);
5575
5576 DCHECK_EQ(this, Isolate::Current());
5577 PerIsolateThreadData* const current_data = CurrentPerIsolateThreadData();
5578 DCHECK_EQ(current_data->isolate(), this);
5579 SetIsolateThreadLocals(this, current_data);
5580
5581 if (OwnsStringTables()) {
5582 string_table_ = std::make_unique<StringTable>(this);
5583 string_forwarding_table_ = std::make_unique<StringForwardingTable>(this);
5584 } else {
5585 // Only refer to shared string table after attaching to the shared isolate.
5586 DCHECK(has_shared_space());
5587 DCHECK(!is_shared_space_isolate());
5588 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(string_table());
5589 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(string_forwarding_table());
5590 }
5591
5592#ifdef V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
5593 {
5594 VirtualMemoryCage* code_cage;
5595 if (heap_.code_range()) {
5596 code_cage = heap_.code_range();
5597 } else {
5598 CHECK(jitless_);
5599 // In jitless mode the code space pages will be allocated in the main
5600 // pointer compression cage.
5601 code_cage = isolate_group_->GetPtrComprCage();
5602 }
5603 code_cage_base_ = ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::PrepareCageBaseAddress(
5604 code_cage->base());
5605 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_MULTIPLE_CAGES_BOOL) {
5606 // .. now that it's available, initialize the thread-local base.
5607 ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::InitBase(code_cage_base_);
5608 }
5609 CHECK_EQ(ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::base(), code_cage_base_);
5610
5611 // Ensure that ExternalCodeCompressionScheme is applicable to all objects
5612 // stored in the code cage.
5613 using ComprScheme = ExternalCodeCompressionScheme;
5614 Address base = code_cage->base();
5615 Address last = base + code_cage->size() - 1;
5616 PtrComprCageBase code_cage_base{code_cage_base_};
5617 CHECK_EQ(base, ComprScheme::DecompressTagged(
5618 code_cage_base, ComprScheme::CompressObject(base)));
5619 CHECK_EQ(last, ComprScheme::DecompressTagged(
5620 code_cage_base, ComprScheme::CompressObject(last)));
5621 }
5622#endif // V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
5623
5624 isolate_data_.external_reference_table()->Init(this);
5625
5626#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5627 if (owns_shareable_data()) {
5628 isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_ = new ExternalPointerTable();
5629 shared_external_pointer_space_ = new ExternalPointerTable::Space();
5630 shared_external_pointer_table().Initialize();
5631 shared_external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5632 shared_external_pointer_space());
5633 } else {
5634 DCHECK(has_shared_space());
5635 isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_ =
5636 shared_space_isolate()->isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_;
5637 shared_external_pointer_space_ =
5638 shared_space_isolate()->shared_external_pointer_space_;
5639 }
5640#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5641
5642#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5643 IsolateGroup::current()->code_pointer_table()->InitializeSpace(
5644 heap()->code_pointer_space());
5645 if (owns_shareable_data()) {
5646 isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_ = new TrustedPointerTable();
5647 shared_trusted_pointer_space_ = new TrustedPointerTable::Space();
5648 shared_trusted_pointer_table().Initialize();
5649 shared_trusted_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5650 shared_trusted_pointer_space());
5651 } else {
5652 DCHECK(has_shared_space());
5653 isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_ =
5654 shared_space_isolate()->isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_;
5655 shared_trusted_pointer_space_ =
5656 shared_space_isolate()->shared_trusted_pointer_space_;
5657 }
5658
5659#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5660#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5661 IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->InitializeSpace(
5662 heap()->js_dispatch_table_space());
5663#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5664
5665#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5666 wasm::GetWasmEngine()->AddIsolate(this);
5667#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5668
5669#if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5670 if (v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking ||
5671 v8_flags.enable_etw_by_custom_filter_only) {
5672 ETWJITInterface::AddIsolate(this);
5673 }
5674#endif // defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5675
5676 if (setup_delegate_ == nullptr) {
5677 setup_delegate_ = new SetupIsolateDelegate;
5678 }
5679
5680 if (!v8_flags.inline_new) heap_.DisableInlineAllocation();
5681
5682 if (!setup_delegate_->SetupHeap(this, create_heap_objects)) {
5683 V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(this, "heap object creation");
5684 }
5685
5686 if (create_heap_objects) {
5687 // Terminate the startup and shared heap object caches so we can iterate.
5688 startup_object_cache_.push_back(ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
5689 shared_heap_object_cache_.push_back(ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
5690 }
5691
5692 InitializeThreadLocal();
5693
5694 // Profiler has to be created after ThreadLocal is initialized
5695 // because it makes use of interrupts.
5696 tracing_cpu_profiler_.reset(new TracingCpuProfilerImpl(this));
5697
5698 bootstrapper_->Initialize(create_heap_objects);
5699
5700 if (create_heap_objects) {
5701 builtins_constants_table_builder_ = new BuiltinsConstantsTableBuilder(this);
5702
5703 if (v8_flags.concurrent_builtin_generation) {
5704 optimizing_compile_dispatcher_ = new OptimizingCompileDispatcher(this);
5705 optimizing_compile_dispatcher_->set_finalize(false);
5706 }
5707
5708 setup_delegate_->SetupBuiltins(this, true);
5709
5710 if (v8_flags.concurrent_builtin_generation) {
5711 delete optimizing_compile_dispatcher_;
5712 optimizing_compile_dispatcher_ = nullptr;
5713 }
5714
5715 builtins_constants_table_builder_->Finalize();
5716 delete builtins_constants_table_builder_;
5717 builtins_constants_table_builder_ = nullptr;
5718
5719 CreateAndSetEmbeddedBlob();
5720 } else {
5721 setup_delegate_->SetupBuiltins(this, false);
5722 }
5723
5724 // Initialize custom memcopy and memmove functions (must happen after
5725 // embedded blob setup).
5726 init_memcopy_functions();
5727
5728 if (v8_flags.trace_turbo || v8_flags.trace_turbo_graph ||
5729 v8_flags.turbo_profiling) {
5730 PrintF("Concurrent recompilation has been disabled for tracing.\n");
5731 } else if (OptimizingCompileDispatcher::Enabled()) {
5732 optimizing_compile_dispatcher_ = new OptimizingCompileDispatcher(this);
5733 }
5734
5735 // Initialize before deserialization since collections may occur,
5736 // clearing/updating ICs (and thus affecting tiering decisions).
5737 tiering_manager_ = new TieringManager(this);
5738
5739 if (!create_heap_objects) {
5740 // If we are deserializing, read the state into the now-empty heap.
5741 SharedHeapDeserializer shared_heap_deserializer(
5742 this, shared_heap_snapshot_data, can_rehash);
5743 shared_heap_deserializer.DeserializeIntoIsolate();
5744
5745 StartupDeserializer startup_deserializer(this, startup_snapshot_data,
5746 can_rehash);
5747 startup_deserializer.DeserializeIntoIsolate();
5748 }
5749 InitializeBuiltinJSDispatchTable();
5750 if (DEBUG_BOOL) VerifyStaticRoots();
5751 load_stub_cache_->Initialize();
5752 store_stub_cache_->Initialize();
5753 define_own_stub_cache_->Initialize();
5754 interpreter_->Initialize();
5755 heap_.NotifyDeserializationComplete();
5756
5757 delete setup_delegate_;
5758 setup_delegate_ = nullptr;
5759
5760 Builtins::InitializeIsolateDataTables(this);
5761
5762 // Extra steps in the logger after the heap has been set up.
5763 v8_file_logger_->LateSetup(this);
5764
5765#ifdef DEBUG
5766 // Verify that the current heap state (usually deserialized from the snapshot)
5767 // is compatible with the embedded blob. If this DCHECK fails, we've likely
5768 // loaded a snapshot generated by a different V8 version or build-time
5769 // configuration.
5770 if (!IsolateIsCompatibleWithEmbeddedBlob(this)) {
5771 FATAL(
5772 "The Isolate is incompatible with the embedded blob. This is usually "
5773 "caused by incorrect usage of mksnapshot. When generating custom "
5774 "snapshots, embedders must ensure they pass the same flags as during "
5775 "the V8 build process (e.g.: --turbo-instruction-scheduling).");
5776 }
5777#endif // DEBUG
5778
5779 if (v8_flags.print_builtin_code) builtins()->PrintBuiltinCode();
5780 if (v8_flags.print_builtin_size) builtins()->PrintBuiltinSize();
5781
5782 // Finish initialization of ThreadLocal after deserialization is done.
5783 clear_exception();
5784 clear_pending_message();
5785
5786 // Quiet the heap NaN if needed on target platform.
5787 if (!create_heap_objects)
5788 Assembler::QuietNaN(ReadOnlyRoots(this).nan_value());
5789
5790 if (v8_flags.trace_turbo) {
5791 // Create an empty file.
5792 std::ofstream(GetTurboCfgFileName(this).c_str(), std::ios_base::trunc);
5793 }
5794
5795 isolate_data_.continuation_preserved_embedder_data_ =
5796 *factory()->undefined_value();
5797
5798 {
5799 HandleScope scope(this);
5800 ast_string_constants_ = new AstStringConstants(this, HashSeed(this));
5801 }
5802
5803 initialized_from_snapshot_ = !create_heap_objects;
5804
5805 if (v8_flags.stress_sampling_allocation_profiler > 0) {
5806 uint64_t sample_interval = v8_flags.stress_sampling_allocation_profiler;
5807 int stack_depth = 128;
5808 v8::HeapProfiler::SamplingFlags sampling_flags =
5809 v8::HeapProfiler::SamplingFlags::kSamplingForceGC;
5810 heap_profiler()->StartSamplingHeapProfiler(sample_interval, stack_depth,
5811 sampling_flags);
5812 }
5813
5814 if (create_heap_objects && v8_flags.profile_deserialization) {
5815 double ms = timer.Elapsed().InMillisecondsF();
5816 PrintF("[Initializing isolate from scratch took %0.3f ms]\n", ms);
5817 }
5818
5819 if (initialized_from_snapshot_) {
5820 SLOW_DCHECK(SharedFunctionInfo::UniqueIdsAreUnique(this));
5821 }
5822
5823 if (v8_flags.harmony_struct) {
5824 // Initialize or get the struct type registry shared by all isolates.
5825 if (is_shared_space_isolate()) {
5826 shared_struct_type_registry_ =
5827 std::make_unique<SharedStructTypeRegistry>();
5828 } else {
5829 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(shared_struct_type_registry());
5830 }
5831 }
5832
5833#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5834#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
5835 // Protect the payload of wasm null.
5836 if (!page_allocator()->DecommitPages(
5837 reinterpret_cast<void*>(factory()->wasm_null()->payload()),
5838 WasmNull::kSize - kTaggedSize)) {
5839 V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(this, "decommitting WasmNull payload");
5840 }
5841#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
5842#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5843
5844 // Isolate initialization allocates long living objects that should be
5845 // pretenured to old space.
5846 DCHECK_IMPLIES(heap()->new_space(), heap()->new_space()->Size() == 0);
5847 DCHECK_IMPLIES(heap()->new_lo_space(), heap()->new_lo_space()->Size() == 0);
5848 DCHECK_EQ(heap()->gc_count(), 0);
5849
5850#if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5851 if (v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking ||
5852 v8_flags.enable_etw_by_custom_filter_only) {
5853 ETWJITInterface::MaybeSetHandlerNow(this);
5854 }
5855#endif // defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5856
5857#if defined(V8_USE_PERFETTO)
5858 PerfettoLogger::RegisterIsolate(this);
5859#endif // defined(V8_USE_PERFETTO)
5860
5861 initialized_ = true;
5862
5863 return true;
5864}
5865
5866void Isolate::Enter() {
5867 Isolate* current_isolate = nullptr;
5868 PerIsolateThreadData* current_data = CurrentPerIsolateThreadData();
5869
5870#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
5871 // No different thread must have entered the isolate. Allow re-entering.
5872 ThreadId thread_id = ThreadId::Current();
5873 if (current_thread_id_.IsValid()) {
5874 CHECK_EQ(current_thread_id_, thread_id);
5875 } else {
5876 CHECK_EQ(0, current_thread_counter_);
5877 current_thread_id_ = thread_id;
5878 }
5879 current_thread_counter_++;
5880#endif
5881
5882 // Set the stack start for the main thread that enters the isolate.
5883 heap()->SetStackStart();
5884
5885 if (current_data != nullptr) {
5886 current_isolate = current_data->isolate_;
5887 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_isolate);
5888 if (current_isolate == this) {
5889 DCHECK(Current() == this);
5890 auto entry_stack = entry_stack_.load();
5891 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(entry_stack);
5892 DCHECK(entry_stack->previous_thread_data == nullptr ||
5893 entry_stack->previous_thread_data->thread_id() ==
5894 ThreadId::Current());
5895 // Same thread re-enters the isolate, no need to re-init anything.
5896 entry_stack->entry_count++;
5897 return;
5898 }
5899 }
5900
5901 PerIsolateThreadData* data = FindOrAllocatePerThreadDataForThisThread();
5902 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(data);
5903 DCHECK(data->isolate_ == this);
5904
5905 EntryStackItem* item =
5906 new EntryStackItem(current_data, current_isolate, entry_stack_);
5907 entry_stack_ = item;
5908
5909 SetIsolateThreadLocals(this, data);
5910
5911 // In case it's the first time some thread enters the isolate.
5912 set_thread_id(data->thread_id());
5913}
5914
5915void Isolate::Exit() {
5916 auto current_entry_stack = entry_stack_.load();
5917 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_entry_stack);
5918 DCHECK(current_entry_stack->previous_thread_data == nullptr ||
5919 current_entry_stack->previous_thread_data->thread_id() ==
5920 ThreadId::Current());
5921
5922#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
5923 // The current thread must have entered the isolate.
5924 CHECK_EQ(current_thread_id_, ThreadId::Current());
5925 if (--current_thread_counter_ == 0) current_thread_id_ = ThreadId::Invalid();
5926#endif
5927
5928 if (--current_entry_stack->entry_count > 0) return;
5929
5930 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(CurrentPerIsolateThreadData());
5931 DCHECK(CurrentPerIsolateThreadData()->isolate_ == this);
5932
5933 // Pop the stack.
5934 entry_stack_ = current_entry_stack->previous_item;
5935
5936 PerIsolateThreadData* previous_thread_data =
5937 current_entry_stack->previous_thread_data;
5938 Isolate* previous_isolate = current_entry_stack->previous_isolate;
5939
5940 delete current_entry_stack;
5941
5942 // Reinit the current thread for the isolate it was running before this one.
5943 SetIsolateThreadLocals(previous_isolate, previous_thread_data);
5944}
5945
5946std::unique_ptr<PersistentHandles> Isolate::NewPersistentHandles() {
5947 return std::make_unique<PersistentHandles>(this);
5948}
5949
5950void Isolate::DumpAndResetStats() {
5951 if (v8_flags.trace_turbo_stack_accesses) {
5952 StdoutStream os;
5953 uint64_t total_loads = 0;
5954 uint64_t total_stores = 0;
5955 os << "=== Stack access counters === " << std::endl;
5956 if (!stack_access_count_map) {
5957 os << "No stack accesses in optimized/wasm functions found.";
5958 } else {
5959 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(stack_access_count_map);
5960 os << "Number of optimized/wasm stack-access functions: "
5961 << stack_access_count_map->size() << std::endl;
5962 for (auto it = stack_access_count_map->cbegin();
5963 it != stack_access_count_map->cend(); it++) {
5964 std::string function_name((*it).first);
5965 std::pair<uint64_t, uint64_t> per_func_count = (*it).second;
5966 os << "Name: " << function_name << ", Loads: " << per_func_count.first
5967 << ", Stores: " << per_func_count.second << std::endl;
5968 total_loads += per_func_count.first;
5969 total_stores += per_func_count.second;
5970 }
5971 os << "Total Loads: " << total_loads << ", Total Stores: " << total_stores
5972 << std::endl;
5973 stack_access_count_map = nullptr;
5974 }
5975 }
5976 if (turbo_statistics_ != nullptr) {
5977 DCHECK(v8_flags.turbo_stats || v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp);
5978 StdoutStream os;
5979 if (v8_flags.turbo_stats) {
5980 AsPrintableStatistics ps = {"Turbofan", *turbo_statistics_, false};
5981 os << ps << std::endl;
5982 }
5983 if (v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp) {
5984 AsPrintableStatistics ps = {"Turbofan", *turbo_statistics_, true};
5985 os << ps << std::endl;
5986 }
5987 turbo_statistics_.reset();
5988 }
5989
5990#ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
5991 if (maglev_statistics_ != nullptr) {
5992 DCHECK(v8_flags.maglev_stats || v8_flags.maglev_stats_nvp);
5993 StdoutStream os;
5994 if (v8_flags.maglev_stats) {
5995 AsPrintableStatistics ps = {"Maglev", *maglev_statistics_, false};
5996 os << ps << std::endl;
5997 }
5998 if (v8_flags.maglev_stats_nvp) {
5999 AsPrintableStatistics ps = {"Maglev", *maglev_statistics_, true};
6000 os << ps << std::endl;
6001 }
6002 maglev_statistics_.reset();
6003 }
6004#endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
6005
6006#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6007 // TODO(7424): There is no public API for the {WasmEngine} yet. So for now we
6008 // just dump and reset the engines statistics together with the Isolate.
6009 if (v8_flags.turbo_stats_wasm) {
6010 wasm::GetWasmEngine()->DumpAndResetTurboStatistics();
6011 }
6012#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6013#if V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6014 if (V8_UNLIKELY(TracingFlags::runtime_stats.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) ==
6015 v8::tracing::TracingCategoryObserver::ENABLED_BY_NATIVE)) {
6016 counters()->worker_thread_runtime_call_stats()->AddToMainTable(
6017 counters()->runtime_call_stats());
6018 counters()->runtime_call_stats()->Print();
6019 counters()->runtime_call_stats()->Reset();
6020 }
6021#endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6022}
6023
6024void Isolate::DumpAndResetBuiltinsProfileData() {
6025 if (BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->HasData(this)) {
6026 if (v8_flags.turbo_profiling_output) {
6027 FILE* f = std::fopen(v8_flags.turbo_profiling_output, "w");
6028 if (f == nullptr) {
6029 FATAL("Unable to open file \"%s\" for writing.\n",
6030 v8_flags.turbo_profiling_output.value());
6031 }
6032 OFStream pgo_stream(f);
6033 BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->Log(this, pgo_stream);
6034 } else {
6035 StdoutStream out;
6036 BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->Print(this, out);
6037 }
6038 BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->ResetCounts(this);
6039 } else {
6040 // Only log builtins PGO data if v8 was built with
6041 // v8_enable_builtins_profiling=true
6042 CHECK_NULL(v8_flags.turbo_profiling_output);
6043 }
6044}

6105 return v8_file_logger()->is_listening_to_code_events() || is_profiling() ||
6106 v8_flags.log_function_events ||
6107 logger()->is_listening_to_code_events();

6113
6114bool Isolate::NeedsSourcePositions() const {
6115 return
6116 // Static conditions.
6117 v8_flags.trace_deopt || v8_flags.trace_turbo ||
6118 v8_flags.trace_turbo_graph || v8_flags.turbo_profiling ||
6119 v8_flags.print_maglev_code || v8_flags.perf_prof || v8_flags.log_maps ||
6120 v8_flags.log_ic || v8_flags.log_function_events ||
6121 v8_flags.heap_snapshot_on_oom ||
6122 // Dynamic conditions; changing any of these conditions triggers source
6123 // position collection for the entire heap
6124 // (CollectSourcePositionsForAllBytecodeArrays).
6125 is_profiling() || debug_->is_active() || v8_file_logger_->is_logging();
6126}
6127
6128void Isolate::SetFeedbackVectorsForProfilingTools(Tagged<Object> value) {
6129 DCHECK(IsUndefined(value, this) || IsArrayList(value));
6130 heap()->set_feedback_vectors_for_profiling_tools(value);
6131}
6132
6133void Isolate::MaybeInitializeVectorListFromHeap() {
6134 if (!IsUndefined(heap()->feedback_vectors_for_profiling_tools(), this)) {
6135 // Already initialized, return early.
6136 DCHECK(IsArrayList(heap()->feedback_vectors_for_profiling_tools()));
6137 return;
6138 }
6139
6140 // Collect existing feedback vectors.
6141 DirectHandleVector<FeedbackVector> vectors(this);
6142
6143 {
6144 HeapObjectIterator heap_iterator(heap());
6145 for (Tagged<HeapObject> current_obj = heap_iterator.Next();
6146 !current_obj.is_null(); current_obj = heap_iterator.Next()) {
6147 if (!IsFeedbackVector(current_obj)) continue;
6148
6149 Tagged<FeedbackVector> vector = Cast<FeedbackVector>(current_obj);
6150 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = vector->shared_function_info();
6151
6152 // No need to preserve the feedback vector for non-user-visible functions.
6153 if (!shared->IsSubjectToDebugging()) continue;
6154
6155 vectors.emplace_back(vector, this);
6156 }
6157 }
6158
6159 // Add collected feedback vectors to the root list lest we lose them to GC.
6160 Handle<ArrayList> list =
6161 ArrayList::New(this, static_cast<int>(vectors.size()));
6162 for (const auto& vector : vectors) list = ArrayList::Add(this, list, vector);
6163 SetFeedbackVectorsForProfilingTools(*list);
6164}
