6166void Isolate::set_date_cache(DateCache* date_cache) {
6167 if (date_cache != date_cache_) {
6168 delete date_cache_;
6169 }
6170 date_cache_ = date_cache;
6171}
6172
6173Isolate::KnownPrototype Isolate::IsArrayOrObjectOrStringPrototype(
6174 Tagged<JSObject> object) {
6175 Tagged<Map> metamap = object->map(this)->map(this);
6176 Tagged<NativeContext> native_context = metamap->native_context();
6177 if (native_context->initial_object_prototype() == object) {
6178 return KnownPrototype::kObject;
6179 } else if (native_context->initial_array_prototype() == object) {
6180 return KnownPrototype::kArray;
6181 } else if (native_context->initial_string_prototype() == object) {
6182 return KnownPrototype::kString;
6183 }
6184 return KnownPrototype::kNone;
6185}
6186
6187bool Isolate::IsInCreationContext(Tagged<JSObject> object, uint32_t index) {
6188 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6189 Tagged<Map> metamap = object->map(this)->map(this);
6190 // Filter out native-context independent objects.
6191 if (metamap == ReadOnlyRoots(this).meta_map()) return false;
6192 Tagged<NativeContext> native_context = metamap->native_context();
6193 return native_context->get(index) == object;
6194}
6195
6196void Isolate::UpdateNoElementsProtectorOnSetElement(
6197 DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
6198 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6199 if (!object->map()->is_prototype_map()) return;
6200 if (!Protectors::IsNoElementsIntact(this)) return;
6201 KnownPrototype obj_type = IsArrayOrObjectOrStringPrototype(*object);
6202 if (obj_type == KnownPrototype::kNone) return;
6203 if (obj_type == KnownPrototype::kObject) {
6204 this->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kObjectPrototypeHasElements);
6205 } else if (obj_type == KnownPrototype::kArray) {
6206 this->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kArrayPrototypeHasElements);
6207 }
6208 Protectors::InvalidateNoElements(this);
6209}
6210
6211void Isolate::UpdateProtectorsOnSetPrototype(
6212 DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<Object> new_prototype) {
6213 UpdateNoElementsProtectorOnSetPrototype(object);
6214 UpdateTypedArraySpeciesLookupChainProtectorOnSetPrototype(object);
6215 UpdateNumberStringNotRegexpLikeProtectorOnSetPrototype(object);
6216 UpdateStringWrapperToPrimitiveProtectorOnSetPrototype(object, new_prototype);
6217}
6218
6219void Isolate::UpdateTypedArraySpeciesLookupChainProtectorOnSetPrototype(
6220 DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
6221 // Setting the __proto__ of TypedArray constructor could change TypedArray's
6222 // @@species. So we need to invalidate the @@species protector.
6223 if (IsTypedArrayConstructor(*object) &&
6224 Protectors::IsTypedArraySpeciesLookupChainIntact(this)) {
6225 Protectors::InvalidateTypedArraySpeciesLookupChain(this);
6226 }
6227}
6228
6229void Isolate::UpdateNumberStringNotRegexpLikeProtectorOnSetPrototype(
6230 DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
6231 if (!Protectors::IsNumberStringNotRegexpLikeIntact(this)) {
6232 return;
6233 }
6234 // We need to protect the prototype chain of `Number.prototype` and
6235 // `String.prototype`.
6236 // Since `Object.prototype.__proto__` is not writable, we can assume it
6237 // doesn't occur here. We detect `Number.prototype` and `String.prototype` by
6238 // checking for a prototype that is a JSPrimitiveWrapper. This is a safe
6239 // approximation. Using JSPrimitiveWrapper as prototype should be
6240 // sufficiently rare.
6241 DCHECK(!IsJSObjectPrototype(*object));
6242 if (object->map()->is_prototype_map() && (IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*object))) {
6243 Protectors::InvalidateNumberStringNotRegexpLike(this);
6244 }
6245}
6246
6247void Isolate::UpdateStringWrapperToPrimitiveProtectorOnSetPrototype(
6248 DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<Object> new_prototype) {
6249 if (!Protectors::IsStringWrapperToPrimitiveIntact(this)) {
6250 return;
6251 }
6252
6253 // We can have a custom @@toPrimitive on a string wrapper also if we subclass
6254 // String and the subclass (or one of its subclasses) defines its own
6255 // @@toPrimive. Thus we invalidate the protector whenever we detect
6256 // subclassing String - it should be reasonably rare.
6257 if (IsStringWrapper(*object) || IsStringWrapper(*new_prototype)) {
6258 Protectors::InvalidateStringWrapperToPrimitive(this);
6259 }
6260}
6261
6262static base::RandomNumberGenerator* ensure_rng_exists(
6263 base::RandomNumberGenerator** rng, int seed) {
6264 if (*rng == nullptr) {
6265 if (seed != 0) {
6266 *rng = new base::RandomNumberGenerator(seed);
6267 } else {
6268 *rng = new base::RandomNumberGenerator();
6269 }
6270 }
6271 return *rng;
6272}
6273
6274base::RandomNumberGenerator* Isolate::random_number_generator() {
6275 // TODO(bmeurer) Initialized lazily because it depends on flags; can
6276 // be fixed once the default isolate cleanup is done.
6277 return ensure_rng_exists(&random_number_generator_, v8_flags.random_seed);
6278}
6279
6280base::RandomNumberGenerator* Isolate::fuzzer_rng() {
6281 if (fuzzer_rng_ == nullptr) {
6282 int64_t seed = v8_flags.fuzzer_random_seed;
6283 if (seed == 0) {
6284 seed = random_number_generator()->initial_seed();
6285 }
6286
6287 fuzzer_rng_ = new base::RandomNumberGenerator(seed);
6288 }
6289
6290 return fuzzer_rng_;
6291}
6292
6293int Isolate::GenerateIdentityHash(uint32_t mask) {
6294 int hash;
6295 int attempts = 0;
6296 do {
6297 hash = random_number_generator()->NextInt() & mask;
6298 } while (hash == 0 && attempts++ < 30);
6299 return hash != 0 ? hash : 1;
6300}

6302#ifdef DEBUG

6304 const intptr_t Isolate::name##_debug_offset_ = OFFSET_OF(Isolate, name##_);
6305ISOLATE_INIT_LIST(ISOLATE_FIELD_OFFSET)
6306ISOLATE_INIT_ARRAY_LIST(ISOLATE_FIELD_OFFSET)
6307#undef ISOLATE_FIELD_OFFSET
6308#endif
6309
6310Handle<Symbol> Isolate::SymbolFor(RootIndex dictionary_index,
6311 Handle<String> name, bool private_symbol) {
6312 DirectHandle<String> key = factory()->InternalizeString(name);
6313 Handle<RegisteredSymbolTable> dictionary =
6314 Cast<RegisteredSymbolTable>(root_handle(dictionary_index));
6315 InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(this, key);
6316 Handle<Symbol> symbol;
6317 if (entry.is_not_found()) {
6318 symbol =
6319 private_symbol ? factory()->NewPrivateSymbol() : factory()->NewSymbol();
6320 symbol->set_description(*key);
6321 dictionary = RegisteredSymbolTable::Add(this, dictionary, key, symbol);
6322
6323 switch (dictionary_index) {
6324 case RootIndex::kPublicSymbolTable:
6325 symbol->set_is_in_public_symbol_table(true);
6326 heap()->set_public_symbol_table(*dictionary);
6327 break;
6328 case RootIndex::kApiSymbolTable:
6329 heap()->set_api_symbol_table(*dictionary);
6330 break;
6331 case RootIndex::kApiPrivateSymbolTable:
6332 heap()->set_api_private_symbol_table(*dictionary);
6333 break;
6334 default:
6335 UNREACHABLE();
6336 }
6337 } else {
6338 symbol = Handle<Symbol>(Cast<Symbol>(dictionary->ValueAt(entry)), this);
6339 }
6340 return symbol;
6341}
6342
6343void Isolate::AddBeforeCallEnteredCallback(BeforeCallEnteredCallback callback) {
6344 auto pos = std::find(before_call_entered_callbacks_.begin(),
6345 before_call_entered_callbacks_.end(), callback);
6346 if (pos != before_call_entered_callbacks_.end()) return;
6347 before_call_entered_callbacks_.push_back(callback);
6348}
6349
6350void Isolate::RemoveBeforeCallEnteredCallback(
6351 BeforeCallEnteredCallback callback) {
6352 auto pos = std::find(before_call_entered_callbacks_.begin(),
6353 before_call_entered_callbacks_.end(), callback);
6354 if (pos == before_call_entered_callbacks_.end()) return;
6355 before_call_entered_callbacks_.erase(pos);
6356}
6357
6358void Isolate::AddCallCompletedCallback(CallCompletedCallback callback) {
6359 auto pos = std::find(call_completed_callbacks_.begin(),
6360 call_completed_callbacks_.end(), callback);
6361 if (pos != call_completed_callbacks_.end()) return;
6362 call_completed_callbacks_.push_back(callback);
6363}
6364
6365void Isolate::RemoveCallCompletedCallback(CallCompletedCallback callback) {
6366 auto pos = std::find(call_completed_callbacks_.begin(),
6367 call_completed_callbacks_.end(), callback);
6368 if (pos == call_completed_callbacks_.end()) return;
6369 call_completed_callbacks_.erase(pos);
6370}
6371
6372void Isolate::FireCallCompletedCallbackInternal(
6373 MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6374 DCHECK(thread_local_top()->CallDepthIsZero());
6375
6376 bool perform_checkpoint =
6377 microtask_queue &&
6378 microtask_queue->microtasks_policy() == v8::MicrotasksPolicy::kAuto &&
6379 !is_execution_terminating();
6380
6381 v8::Isolate* isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this);
6382 if (perform_checkpoint) microtask_queue->PerformCheckpoint(isolate);
6383
6384 if (call_completed_callbacks_.empty()) return;
6385 // Fire callbacks. Increase call depth to prevent recursive callbacks.
6386 v8::Isolate::SuppressMicrotaskExecutionScope suppress(isolate);
6387 std::vector<CallCompletedCallback> callbacks(call_completed_callbacks_);
6388 for (auto& callback : callbacks) {
6389 callback(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this));
6390 }
6391}

6393#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6394void Isolate::WasmInitJSPIFeature() {
6395 if (IsUndefined(root(RootIndex::kActiveContinuation))) {
6396 wasm::StackMemory* stack(wasm::StackMemory::GetCentralStackView(this));
6397 this->wasm_stacks().emplace_back(stack);
6398 stack->set_index(0);
6399 if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_stack_switching) {
6400 PrintF("Set up native stack object (limit: %p, base: %p)\n",
6401 stack->jslimit(), reinterpret_cast<void*>(stack->base()));
6402 }
6403 HandleScope scope(this);
6404 DirectHandle<WasmContinuationObject> continuation =
6405 WasmContinuationObject::New(this, stack, wasm::JumpBuffer::Active,
6406 AllocationType::kOld);
6407 heap()
6408 ->roots_table()
6409 .slot(RootIndex::kActiveContinuation)
6410 .store(*continuation);
6411 }
6412}
6413#endif

6415void Isolate::UpdatePromiseHookProtector() {
6416 if (Protectors::IsPromiseHookIntact(this)) {
6417 HandleScope scope(this);
6418 Protectors::InvalidatePromiseHook(this);
6419 }
6420}
6421
6422void Isolate::PromiseHookStateUpdated() {
6423 promise_hook_flags_ =
6424 (promise_hook_flags_ & PromiseHookFields::HasContextPromiseHook::kMask) |
6425 PromiseHookFields::HasIsolatePromiseHook::encode(promise_hook_) |
6426 PromiseHookFields::HasAsyncEventDelegate::encode(async_event_delegate_) |
6427 PromiseHookFields::IsDebugActive::encode(debug()->is_active());
6428
6429 if (promise_hook_flags_ != 0) {
6430 UpdatePromiseHookProtector();
6431 }
6432}

6434namespace {
6435
6436MaybeHandle<JSPromise> NewRejectedPromise(Isolate* isolate,
6437 v8::Local<v8::Context> api_context,
6438 DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
6439 v8::Local<v8::Promise::Resolver> resolver;
6440 API_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, resolver,
6441 v8::Promise::Resolver::New(api_context),
6442 MaybeHandle<JSPromise>());
6443
6444 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6445 isolate, resolver->Reject(api_context, v8::Utils::ToLocal(exception)),
6446 MaybeHandle<JSPromise>());
6447
6448 v8::Local<v8::Promise> promise = resolver->GetPromise();
6449 return v8::Utils::OpenHandle(*promise);
6450}
6451
6452} // namespace
6453
6454MaybeHandle<JSPromise> Isolate::RunHostImportModuleDynamicallyCallback(
6455 MaybeDirectHandle<Script> maybe_referrer, Handle<Object> specifier,
6456 ModuleImportPhase phase,
6457 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> maybe_import_options_argument) {
6458 DCHECK(!is_execution_terminating());
6459 v8::Local<v8::Context> api_context = v8::Utils::ToLocal(native_context());
6460 if (host_import_module_dynamically_callback_ == nullptr) {
6461 DirectHandle<Object> exception =
6462 factory()->NewError(error_function(), MessageTemplate::kUnsupported);
6463 return NewRejectedPromise(this, api_context, exception);
6464 }
6465
6466 DirectHandle<String> specifier_str;
6467 MaybeDirectHandle<String> maybe_specifier = Object::ToString(this, specifier);
6468 if (!maybe_specifier.ToHandle(&specifier_str)) {
6469 if (is_execution_terminating()) {
6470 return MaybeHandle<JSPromise>();
6471 }
6472 DirectHandle<Object> exception(this->exception(), this);
6473 clear_exception();
6474 return NewRejectedPromise(this, api_context, exception);
6475 }
6476 DCHECK(!has_exception());
6477
6478 v8::Local<v8::Promise> promise;
6479 DirectHandle<FixedArray> import_attributes_array;
6480 if (!GetImportAttributesFromArgument(maybe_import_options_argument)
6481 .ToHandle(&import_attributes_array)) {
6482 if (is_execution_terminating()) {
6483 return MaybeHandle<JSPromise>();
6484 }
6485 DirectHandle<Object> exception(this->exception(), this);
6486 clear_exception();
6487 return NewRejectedPromise(this, api_context, exception);
6488 }
6489 DirectHandle<FixedArray> host_defined_options;
6490 DirectHandle<Object> resource_name;
6491 if (maybe_referrer.is_null()) {
6492 host_defined_options = factory()->empty_fixed_array();
6493 resource_name = factory()->null_value();
6494 } else {
6495 DirectHandle<Script> referrer = maybe_referrer.ToHandleChecked();
6496 host_defined_options =
6497 direct_handle(referrer->host_defined_options(), this);
6498 resource_name = direct_handle(referrer->name(), this);
6499 }
6500
6501 switch (phase) {
6502 case ModuleImportPhase::kEvaluation:
6503 // TODO(42204365): Deprecate HostImportModuleDynamicallyCallback once
6504 // HostImportModuleWithPhaseDynamicallyCallback is stable.
6505 API_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6506 this, promise,
6507 host_import_module_dynamically_callback_(
6508 api_context, v8::Utils::ToLocal(host_defined_options),
6509 v8::Utils::ToLocal(resource_name),
6510 v8::Utils::ToLocal(specifier_str),
6511 ToApiHandle<v8::FixedArray>(import_attributes_array)),
6512 MaybeHandle<JSPromise>());
6513 break;
6514 case ModuleImportPhase::kSource:
6515 CHECK(v8_flags.js_source_phase_imports);
6516 CHECK_NOT_NULL(host_import_module_with_phase_dynamically_callback_);
6517 API_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6518 this, promise,
6519 host_import_module_with_phase_dynamically_callback_(
6520 api_context, v8::Utils::ToLocal(host_defined_options),
6521 v8::Utils::ToLocal(resource_name),
6522 v8::Utils::ToLocal(specifier_str), phase,
6523 ToApiHandle<v8::FixedArray>(import_attributes_array)),
6524 MaybeHandle<JSPromise>());
6525 break;
6526 default:
6527 UNREACHABLE();
6528 }
6529
6530 return v8::Utils::OpenHandle(*promise);
6531}
6532
6533MaybeHandle<FixedArray> Isolate::GetImportAttributesFromArgument(
6534 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> maybe_import_options_argument) {
6535 Handle<FixedArray> import_attributes_array = factory()->empty_fixed_array();
6536 DirectHandle<Object> import_options_argument;
6537 if (!maybe_import_options_argument.ToHandle(&import_options_argument) ||
6538 IsUndefined(*import_options_argument)) {
6539 return import_attributes_array;
6540 }
6541
6542 // The parser shouldn't have allowed the second argument to import() if
6543 // the flag wasn't enabled.
6544 DCHECK(v8_flags.harmony_import_attributes);
6545
6546 if (!IsJSReceiver(*import_options_argument)) {
6547 this->Throw(
6548 *factory()->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonObjectImportArgument));
6549 return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
6550 }
6551
6552 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> import_options_argument_receiver =
6553 Cast<JSReceiver>(import_options_argument);
6554
6555 DirectHandle<Object> import_attributes_object;
6556
6557 if (v8_flags.harmony_import_attributes) {
6558 DirectHandle<Name> with_key = factory()->with_string();
6559 if (!JSReceiver::GetProperty(this, import_options_argument_receiver,
6560 with_key)
6561 .ToHandle(&import_attributes_object)) {
6562 // This can happen if the property has a getter function that throws
6563 // an error.
6564 return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
6565 }
6566 }
6567
6568 // If there is no 'with' option in the options bag, it's not an error. Just do
6569 // the import() as if no attributes were provided.
6570 if (IsUndefined(*import_attributes_object)) return import_attributes_array;
6571
6572 if (!IsJSReceiver(*import_attributes_object)) {
6573 this->Throw(
6574 *factory()->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonObjectAttributesOption));
6575 return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
6576 }
6577
6578 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> import_attributes_object_receiver =
6579 Cast<JSReceiver>(import_attributes_object);
6580
6581 DirectHandle<FixedArray> attribute_keys;
6582 if (!KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(this, import_attributes_object_receiver,
6583 KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly, ENUMERABLE_STRINGS,
6584 GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString)
6585 .ToHandle(&attribute_keys)) {
6586 // This happens if the attributes object is a Proxy whose ownKeys() or
6587 // getOwnPropertyDescriptor() trap throws.
6588 return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
6589 }
6590
6591 bool has_non_string_attribute = false;
6592
6593 // The attributes will be passed to the host in the form: [key1,
6594 // value1, key2, value2, ...].
6595 constexpr size_t kAttributeEntrySizeForDynamicImport = 2;
6596 import_attributes_array = factory()->NewFixedArray(static_cast<int>(
6597 attribute_keys->length() * kAttributeEntrySizeForDynamicImport));
6598 for (int i = 0; i < attribute_keys->length(); i++) {
6599 DirectHandle<String> attribute_key(Cast<String>(attribute_keys->get(i)),
6600 this);
6601 DirectHandle<Object> attribute_value;
6602 if (!Object::GetPropertyOrElement(this, import_attributes_object_receiver,
6603 attribute_key)
6604 .ToHandle(&attribute_value)) {
6605 // This can happen if the property has a getter function that throws
6606 // an error.
6607 return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
6608 }
6609
6610 if (!IsString(*attribute_value)) {
6611 has_non_string_attribute = true;
6612 }
6613
6614 import_attributes_array->set((i * kAttributeEntrySizeForDynamicImport),
6615 *attribute_key);
6616 import_attributes_array->set((i * kAttributeEntrySizeForDynamicImport) + 1,
6617 *attribute_value);
6618 }
6619
6620 if (has_non_string_attribute) {
6621 this->Throw(*factory()->NewTypeError(
6622 MessageTemplate::kNonStringImportAttributeValue));
6623 return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
6624 }
6625
6626 return import_attributes_array;
6627}
6628

6641MaybeHandle<JSObject> Isolate::RunHostInitializeImportMetaObjectCallback(

6664
6665MaybeHandle<NativeContext> Isolate::RunHostCreateShadowRealmContextCallback() {
6666 if (host_create_shadow_realm_context_callback_ == nullptr) {
6667 DirectHandle<Object> exception =
6668 factory()->NewError(error_function(), MessageTemplate::kUnsupported);
6669 Throw(*exception);
6670 return kNullMaybeHandle;
6671 }
6672
6673 v8::Local<v8::Context> api_context = v8::Utils::ToLocal(native_context());
6674 v8::Local<v8::Context> shadow_realm_context;
6675 API_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6676 this, shadow_realm_context,
6677 host_create_shadow_realm_context_callback_(api_context),
6678 MaybeHandle<NativeContext>());
6679 Handle<Context> shadow_realm_context_handle =
6680 v8::Utils::OpenHandle(*shadow_realm_context);
6681 DCHECK(IsNativeContext(*shadow_realm_context_handle));
6682 shadow_realm_context_handle->set_scope_info(
6683 ReadOnlyRoots(this).shadow_realm_scope_info());
6684 return Cast<NativeContext>(shadow_realm_context_handle);
6685}

6781 // tracing of interpreter stack frames.

6819
6820void Isolate::RunAllPromiseHooks(PromiseHookType type,
6821 DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
6822 DirectHandle<Object> parent) {
6823#ifdef V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
6824 if (HasContextPromiseHooks()) {
6825 native_context()->RunPromiseHook(type, promise, parent);
6826 }
6827#endif
6828 if (HasIsolatePromiseHooks() || HasAsyncEventDelegate()) {
6829 RunPromiseHook(type, promise, parent);
6830 }
6831}
6832
6833void Isolate::RunPromiseHook(PromiseHookType type,
6834 DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
6835 DirectHandle<Object> parent) {
6836 if (!HasIsolatePromiseHooks()) return;
6837 DCHECK(promise_hook_ != nullptr);
6838 promise_hook_(type, v8::Utils::PromiseToLocal(promise),
6839 v8::Utils::ToLocal(parent));
6840}
6841
6842void Isolate::OnAsyncFunctionSuspended(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
6843 DirectHandle<JSPromise> parent) {
6844 DCHECK(!promise->has_async_task_id());
6845 RunAllPromiseHooks(PromiseHookType::kInit, promise, parent);
6846 if (HasAsyncEventDelegate()) {
6847 DCHECK_NE(nullptr, async_event_delegate_);
6848 current_async_task_id_ =
6849 JSPromise::GetNextAsyncTaskId(current_async_task_id_);
6850 promise->set_async_task_id(current_async_task_id_);
6851 async_event_delegate_->AsyncEventOccurred(debug::kDebugAwait,
6852 promise->async_task_id(), false);
6853 }
6854}
6855
6856void Isolate::OnPromiseThen(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise) {
6857 if (!HasAsyncEventDelegate()) return;
6858 Maybe<debug::DebugAsyncActionType> action_type =
6859 Nothing<debug::DebugAsyncActionType>();
6860 for (JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(this); !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
6861 std::vector<Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>> infos;
6862 it.frame()->GetFunctions(&infos);
6863 for (auto it = infos.rbegin(); it != infos.rend(); ++it) {
6864 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info = *it;
6865 if (info->HasBuiltinId()) {
6866 // We should not report PromiseThen and PromiseCatch which is called
6867 // indirectly, e.g. Promise.all calls Promise.then internally.
6868 switch (info->builtin_id()) {
6869 case Builtin::kPromisePrototypeCatch:
6870 action_type = Just(debug::kDebugPromiseCatch);
6871 continue;
6872 case Builtin::kPromisePrototypeFinally:
6873 action_type = Just(debug::kDebugPromiseFinally);
6874 continue;
6875 case Builtin::kPromisePrototypeThen:
6876 action_type = Just(debug::kDebugPromiseThen);
6877 continue;
6878 default:
6879 return;
6880 }
6881 }
6882 if (info->IsUserJavaScript() && action_type.IsJust()) {
6883 DCHECK(!promise->has_async_task_id());
6884 current_async_task_id_ =
6885 JSPromise::GetNextAsyncTaskId(current_async_task_id_);
6886 promise->set_async_task_id(current_async_task_id_);
6887 async_event_delegate_->AsyncEventOccurred(action_type.FromJust(),
6888 promise->async_task_id(),
6889 debug()->IsBlackboxed(info));
6890 }
6891 return;
6892 }
6893 }
6894}
6895
6896void Isolate::OnPromiseBefore(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise) {
6897 RunPromiseHook(PromiseHookType::kBefore, promise,
6898 factory()->undefined_value());
6899 if (HasAsyncEventDelegate()) {
6900 if (promise->has_async_task_id()) {
6901 async_event_delegate_->AsyncEventOccurred(
6902 debug::kDebugWillHandle, promise->async_task_id(), false);
6903 }
6904 }
6905}
6906
6907void Isolate::OnPromiseAfter(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise) {
6908 RunPromiseHook(PromiseHookType::kAfter, promise,
6909 factory()->undefined_value());
6910 if (HasAsyncEventDelegate()) {
6911 if (promise->has_async_task_id()) {
6912 async_event_delegate_->AsyncEventOccurred(
6913 debug::kDebugDidHandle, promise->async_task_id(), false);
6914 }
6915 }
6916}
6917
6918void Isolate::OnStackTraceCaptured(DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace) {
6919 if (HasAsyncEventDelegate()) {
6920 async_event_delegate_->AsyncEventOccurred(debug::kDebugStackTraceCaptured,
6921 stack_trace->id(), false);
6922 }
6923}
6924
6925void Isolate::OnTerminationDuringRunMicrotasks() {
6926 DCHECK(is_execution_terminating());
6927 // This performs cleanup for when RunMicrotasks (in
6928 // builtins-microtask-queue-gen.cc) is aborted via a termination exception.
6929 // This has to be kept in sync with the code in said file. Currently this
6930 // includes:
6931 //
6932 // (1) Resetting the |current_microtask| slot on the Isolate to avoid leaking
6933 // memory (and also to keep |current_microtask| not being undefined as an
6934 // indicator that we're currently pumping the microtask queue).
6935 // (2) Empty the promise stack to avoid leaking memory.
6936 // (3) If the |current_microtask| is a promise reaction or resolve thenable
6937 // job task, then signal the async event delegate and debugger that the
6938 // microtask finished running.
6939 //
6940
6941 // Reset the |current_microtask| global slot.
6942 DirectHandle<Microtask> current_microtask(
6943 Cast<Microtask>(heap()->current_microtask()), this);
6944 heap()->set_current_microtask(ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
6945
6946 if (IsPromiseReactionJobTask(*current_microtask)) {
6947 auto promise_reaction_job_task =
6948 Cast<PromiseReactionJobTask>(current_microtask);
6949 DirectHandle<HeapObject> promise_or_capability(
6950 promise_reaction_job_task->promise_or_capability(), this);
6951 if (IsPromiseCapability(*promise_or_capability)) {
6952 promise_or_capability = direct_handle(
6953 Cast<PromiseCapability>(promise_or_capability)->promise(), this);
6954 }
6955 if (IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
6956 OnPromiseAfter(Cast<JSPromise>(promise_or_capability));
6957 }
6958 } else if (IsPromiseResolveThenableJobTask(*current_microtask)) {
6959 auto promise_resolve_thenable_job_task =
6960 Cast<PromiseResolveThenableJobTask>(current_microtask);
6961 DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise_to_resolve(
6962 promise_resolve_thenable_job_task->promise_to_resolve(), this);
6963 OnPromiseAfter(promise_to_resolve);
6964 }
6965
6966 SetTerminationOnExternalTryCatch();
6967}

6985
6986void Isolate::CountUsage(v8::Isolate::UseCounterFeature feature) {
6987 CountUsage(base::VectorOf({feature}));
6988}
6989
6990void Isolate::CountUsage(
6991 base::Vector<const v8::Isolate::UseCounterFeature> features) {
6992 // The counter callback
6993 // - may cause the embedder to call into V8, which is not generally possible
6994 // during GC.
6995 // - requires a current native context, which may not always exist.
6996 // TODO(jgruber): Consider either removing the native context requirement in
6997 // blink, or passing it to the callback explicitly.
6998 if (heap_.gc_state() == Heap::NOT_IN_GC && !context().is_null()) {
6999 DCHECK(IsContext(context()));
7000 DCHECK(IsNativeContext(context()->native_context()));
7001 if (use_counter_callback_) {
7002 HandleScope handle_scope(this);
7003 for (auto feature : features) {
7004 use_counter_callback_(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this), feature);
7005 }
7006 }
7007 } else {
7008 heap_.IncrementDeferredCounts(features);
7009 }
7010}

7014// static
7015std::string Isolate::GetTurboCfgFileName(Isolate* isolate) {
7016 if (const char* filename = v8_flags.trace_turbo_cfg_file) return filename;
7017 std::ostringstream os;
7018 os << "turbo-" << base::OS::GetCurrentProcessId() << "-";
7019 if (isolate != nullptr) {
7020 os << isolate->id();
7021 } else {
7022 os << "any";
7023 }
7024 os << ".cfg";
7025 return os.str();
7026}
7027
7028// Heap::detached_contexts tracks detached contexts as pairs
7029// (the context, number of GC since the context was detached).
7030void Isolate::AddDetachedContext(DirectHandle<Context> context) {
7031 HandleScope scope(this);
7032 Handle<WeakArrayList> detached_contexts = factory()->detached_contexts();
7033 detached_contexts = WeakArrayList::AddToEnd(
7034 this, detached_contexts, MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(context),
7035 Smi::zero());
7036 heap()->set_detached_contexts(*detached_contexts);
7037}
7038
7039void Isolate::CheckDetachedContextsAfterGC() {
7040 HandleScope scope(this);
7041 DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> detached_contexts =
7042 factory()->detached_contexts();
7043 int length = detached_contexts->length();
7044 if (length == 0) return;
7045 int new_length = 0;
7046 for (int i = 0; i < length; i += 2) {
7047 Tagged<MaybeObject> context = detached_contexts->Get(i);
7048 DCHECK(context.IsWeakOrCleared());
7049 if (!context.IsCleared()) {
7050 int mark_sweeps = detached_contexts->Get(i + 1).ToSmi().value();
7051 detached_contexts->Set(new_length, context);
7052 detached_contexts->Set(new_length + 1, Smi::FromInt(mark_sweeps + 1));
7053 new_length += 2;
7054 }
7055 }
7056 detached_contexts->set_length(new_length);
7057 while (new_length < length) {
7058 detached_contexts->Set(new_length, Smi::zero());
7059 ++new_length;
7060 }
7061
7062 if (v8_flags.trace_detached_contexts) {
7063 PrintF("%d detached contexts are collected out of %d\n",
7064 length - new_length, length);
7065 for (int i = 0; i < new_length; i += 2) {
7066 Tagged<MaybeObject> context = detached_contexts->Get(i);
7067 int mark_sweeps = detached_contexts->Get(i + 1).ToSmi().value();
7068 DCHECK(context.IsWeakOrCleared());
7069 if (mark_sweeps > 3) {
7070 PrintF("detached context %p\n survived %d GCs (leak?)\n",
7071 reinterpret_cast<void*>(context.ptr()), mark_sweeps);
7072 }
7073 }
7074 }
7075}
7076
7077void Isolate::DetachGlobal(DirectHandle<Context> env) {
7078 counters()->errors_thrown_per_context()->AddSample(
7079 env->native_context()->GetErrorsThrown());
7080
7081 ReadOnlyRoots roots(this);
7082 DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy(env->global_proxy(), this);
7083 // NOTE: Turbofan's JSNativeContextSpecialization and Maglev depend on
7084 // DetachGlobal causing a map change.
7085 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(this, global_proxy, factory()->null_value());
7086 // Detach the global object from the native context by making its map
7087 // contextless (use the global metamap instead of the contextful one).
7088 global_proxy->map()->set_map(this, roots.meta_map());
7089 global_proxy->map()->set_constructor_or_back_pointer(roots.null_value(),
7090 kRelaxedStore);
7091 if (v8_flags.track_detached_contexts) AddDetachedContext(env);
7092 DCHECK(global_proxy->IsDetached());
7093
7094 env->native_context()->set_microtask_queue(this, nullptr);
7095}
7096
7097void Isolate::SetIsLoading(bool is_loading) {
7098 if (is_loading) {
7099 heap()->NotifyLoadingStarted();
7100 } else {
7101 heap()->NotifyLoadingEnded();
7102 }
7103 if (v8_flags.trace_rail) {
7104 // TODO(crbug.com/373688984): Switch to a trace flag for loading state.
7105 PrintIsolate(this, "RAIL mode: %s\n", is_loading ? "LOAD" : "ANIMATION");
7106 }
7107}

7109void Isolate::SetPriority(v8::Isolate::Priority priority) {
7110 priority_ = priority;
7111 heap()->tracer()->UpdateCurrentEventPriority(priority_);
7112 if (priority_ == v8::Isolate::Priority::kBestEffort) {
7113 heap()->ActivateMemoryReducerIfNeeded();
7114 }
7115}

7117void Isolate::PrintWithTimestamp(const char* format, ...) {
7118 base::OS::Print("[%d:%p] %8.0f ms: ", base::OS::GetCurrentProcessId(),
7119 static_cast<void*>(this), time_millis_since_init());
7120 va_list arguments;
7121 va_start(arguments, format);
7122 base::OS::VPrint(format, arguments);
7123 va_end(arguments);
7124}
7125
7126void Isolate::SetIdle(bool is_idle) {
7127 StateTag state = current_vm_state();
7128 if (js_entry_sp() != kNullAddress) return;
7129 DCHECK(state == EXTERNAL || state == IDLE);
7130 if (is_idle) {
7131 set_current_vm_state(IDLE);
7132 } else if (state == IDLE) {
7133 set_current_vm_state(EXTERNAL);
7134 }
7135}
7136
7137void Isolate::CollectSourcePositionsForAllBytecodeArrays() {
7138 if (!initialized_) return;
7139
7140 HandleScope scope(this);
7141 std::vector<Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>> sfis;
7142 {
7143 HeapObjectIterator iterator(heap());
7144 for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj = iterator.Next(); !obj.is_null();
7145 obj = iterator.Next()) {
7146 if (!IsSharedFunctionInfo(obj)) continue;
7147 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(obj);
7148 // If the script is a Smi, then the SharedFunctionInfo is in
7149 // the process of being deserialized.
7150 Tagged<Object> script = sfi->raw_script(kAcquireLoad);
7151 if (IsSmi(script)) {
7152 DCHECK_EQ(script, Smi::uninitialized_deserialization_value());
7153 continue;
7154 }
7155 if (!sfi->CanCollectSourcePosition(this)) continue;
7156 sfis.push_back(Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>(sfi, this));
7157 }
7158 }
7159 for (auto sfi : sfis) {
7160 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(this, sfi);
7161 }
7162}

7166namespace {

7168std::string GetStringFromLocales(Isolate* isolate,
7169 DirectHandle<Object> locales) {
7170 if (IsUndefined(*locales, isolate)) return "";
7171 return std::string(Cast<String>(*locales)->ToCString().get());
7172}
7173
7174bool StringEqualsLocales(Isolate* isolate, const std::string& str,
7175 DirectHandle<Object> locales) {
7176 if (IsUndefined(*locales, isolate)) return str.empty();
7177 return Cast<String>(locales)->IsEqualTo(
7178 base::VectorOf(str.c_str(), str.length()));
7179}

7181} // namespace
7182
7183const std::string& Isolate::DefaultLocale() {
7184 if (default_locale_.empty()) {
7185 icu::Locale default_locale;
7186 // Translate ICU's fallback locale to a well-known locale.
7187 if (strcmp(default_locale.getName(), "en_US_POSIX") == 0 ||
7188 strcmp(default_locale.getName(), "c") == 0) {
7189 set_default_locale("en-US");
7190 } else {
7191 // Set the locale
7192 set_default_locale(default_locale.isBogus()
7193 ? "und"
7194 : Intl::ToLanguageTag(default_locale).FromJust());
7195 }
7196 DCHECK(!default_locale_.empty());
7197 }
7198 return default_locale_;
7199}
7200
7201void Isolate::ResetDefaultLocale() {
7202 default_locale_.clear();
7203 clear_cached_icu_objects();
7204 // We inline fast paths assuming certain locales. Since this path is rarely
7205 // taken, we deoptimize everything to keep things simple.
7206 Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeAll(this);
7207}

7209icu::UMemory* Isolate::get_cached_icu_object(ICUObjectCacheType cache_type,
7210 DirectHandle<Object> locales) {
7211 const ICUObjectCacheEntry& entry =
7212 icu_object_cache_[static_cast<int>(cache_type)];
7213 return StringEqualsLocales(this, entry.locales, locales) ? entry.obj.get()
7214 : nullptr;
7215}

7217void Isolate::set_icu_object_in_cache(ICUObjectCacheType cache_type,

7235
7236bool StackLimitCheck::HandleStackOverflowAndTerminationRequest() {
7237 DCHECK(InterruptRequested());
7238 if (V8_UNLIKELY(HasOverflowed())) {
7239 isolate_->StackOverflow();
7240 return true;
7241 }
7242 if (V8_UNLIKELY(isolate_->stack_guard()->HasTerminationRequest())) {
7243 isolate_->TerminateExecution();
7244 return true;
7245 }
7246 return false;
7247}
7248
7249bool StackLimitCheck::JsHasOverflowed(uintptr_t gap) const {
7250 StackGuard* stack_guard = isolate_->stack_guard();
7251#ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
7252 // The simulator uses a separate JS stack.
7253 Address jssp_address = Simulator::current(isolate_)->get_sp();
7254 uintptr_t jssp = static_cast<uintptr_t>(jssp_address);
7255 if (jssp - gap < stack_guard->real_jslimit()) return true;
7256#endif // USE_SIMULATOR
7257 return GetCurrentStackPosition() - gap < stack_guard->real_climit();
7258}
7259
7260bool StackLimitCheck::WasmHasOverflowed(uintptr_t gap) const {
7261 StackGuard* stack_guard = isolate_->stack_guard();
7262 auto sp = isolate_->thread_local_top()->secondary_stack_sp_;
7263 auto limit = isolate_->thread_local_top()->secondary_stack_limit_;
7264 if (sp == 0) {
7265#ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
7266 // The simulator uses a separate JS stack.
7267 // Use it if code is executed on the central stack.
7268 Address jssp_address = Simulator::current(isolate_)->get_sp();
7269 uintptr_t jssp = static_cast<uintptr_t>(jssp_address);
7270 if (jssp - gap < stack_guard->real_jslimit()) return true;
7271#endif // USE_SIMULATOR
7272 sp = GetCurrentStackPosition();
7273 limit = stack_guard->real_climit();
7274 }
7275 return sp - gap < limit;
7276}

7310
7311bool Overlapping(const MemoryRange& a, const MemoryRange& b) {
7312 uintptr_t a1 = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(a.start);
7313 uintptr_t a2 = a1 + a.length_in_bytes;
7314 uintptr_t b1 = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(b.start);
7315 uintptr_t b2 = b1 + b.length_in_bytes;
7316 // Either b1 or b2 are in the [a1, a2) range.
7317 return (a1 <= b1 && b1 < a2) || (a1 <= b2 && b2 < a2);
7318}
7319
7320} // anonymous namespace
7321
7322#endif // DEBUG
7323
7324void Isolate::AddCodeMemoryRange(MemoryRange range) {
7325 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(&code_pages_mutex_);
7326 std::vector<MemoryRange>* old_code_pages = GetCodePages();
7327 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(old_code_pages);
7328#ifdef DEBUG
7329 auto overlapping = [range](const MemoryRange& a) {
7330 return Overlapping(range, a);
7331 };
7332 DCHECK_EQ(old_code_pages->end(),
7333 std::find_if(old_code_pages->begin(), old_code_pages->end(),
7334 overlapping));
7335#endif
7336
7337 std::vector<MemoryRange>* new_code_pages;
7338 if (old_code_pages == &code_pages_buffer1_) {
7339 new_code_pages = &code_pages_buffer2_;
7340 } else {
7341 new_code_pages = &code_pages_buffer1_;
7342 }
7343
7344 // Copy all existing data from the old vector to the new vector and insert the
7345 // new page.
7346 new_code_pages->clear();
7347 new_code_pages->reserve(old_code_pages->size() + 1);
7348 std::merge(old_code_pages->begin(), old_code_pages->end(), &range, &range + 1,
7349 std::back_inserter(*new_code_pages),
7350 [](const MemoryRange& a, const MemoryRange& b) {
7351 return a.start < b.start;
7352 });
7353
7354 // Atomically switch out the pointer
7355 SetCodePages(new_code_pages);
7356}
7357
7358// |chunk| is either a Page or an executable LargePage.
7359void Isolate::AddCodeMemoryChunk(MutablePageMetadata* chunk) {
7360 // We only keep track of individual code pages/allocations if we are on arm32,
7361 // because on x64 and arm64 we have a code range which makes this unnecessary.
7362#if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
7363 void* new_page_start = reinterpret_cast<void*>(chunk->area_start());
7364 size_t new_page_size = chunk->area_size();
7365
7366 MemoryRange new_range{new_page_start, new_page_size};
7367
7368 AddCodeMemoryRange(new_range);
7369#endif // !defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
7370}
7371
7372void Isolate::AddCodeRange(Address begin, size_t length_in_bytes) {
7373 AddCodeMemoryRange(
7374 MemoryRange{reinterpret_cast<void*>(begin), length_in_bytes});
7375}

7377bool Isolate::RequiresCodeRange() const {
7378 return kPlatformRequiresCodeRange && !jitless_;
7379}
7380
7381v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId Isolate::GetOrRegisterRecorderContextId(
7382 DirectHandle<NativeContext> context) {
7383 if (serializer_enabled_) return v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId::Empty();
7384 i::Tagged<i::Object> id = context->recorder_context_id();
7385 if (IsNullOrUndefined(id)) {
7386 CHECK_LT(last_recorder_context_id_, i::Smi::kMaxValue);
7387 context->set_recorder_context_id(
7388 i::Smi::FromIntptr(++last_recorder_context_id_));
7389 v8::HandleScope handle_scope(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this));
7390 auto result = recorder_context_id_map_.emplace(
7391 std::piecewise_construct,
7392 std::forward_as_tuple(last_recorder_context_id_),
7393 std::forward_as_tuple(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this),
7394 ToApiHandle<v8::Context>(context)));
7395 result.first->second.SetWeak(
7396 reinterpret_cast<void*>(last_recorder_context_id_),
7397 RemoveContextIdCallback, v8::WeakCallbackType::kParameter);
7398 return v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId(last_recorder_context_id_);
7399 } else {
7400 DCHECK(IsSmi(id));
7401 return v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId(
7402 static_cast<uintptr_t>(i::Smi::ToInt(id)));
7403 }
7404}
7405
7406MaybeLocal<v8::Context> Isolate::GetContextFromRecorderContextId(
7407 v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId id) {
7408 auto result = recorder_context_id_map_.find(id.id_);
7409 if (result == recorder_context_id_map_.end() || result->second.IsEmpty())
7410 return MaybeLocal<v8::Context>();
7411 return result->second.Get(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this));
7412}

7426void Isolate::RemoveContextIdCallback(const v8::WeakCallbackInfo<void>& data) {

7442
7443// |chunk| is either a Page or an executable LargePage.
7444void Isolate::RemoveCodeMemoryChunk(MutablePageMetadata* chunk) {
7445 // We only keep track of individual code pages/allocations if we are on arm32,
7446 // because on x64 and arm64 we have a code range which makes this unnecessary.
7447#if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
7448 void* removed_page_start = reinterpret_cast<void*>(chunk->area_start());
7449 std::vector<MemoryRange>* old_code_pages = GetCodePages();
7450 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(old_code_pages);
7451
7452 std::vector<MemoryRange>* new_code_pages;
7453 if (old_code_pages == &code_pages_buffer1_) {
7454 new_code_pages = &code_pages_buffer2_;
7455 } else {
7456 new_code_pages = &code_pages_buffer1_;
7457 }
7458
7459 // Copy all existing data from the old vector to the new vector except the
7460 // removed page.
7461 new_code_pages->clear();
7462 new_code_pages->reserve(old_code_pages->size() - 1);
7463 std::remove_copy_if(old_code_pages->begin(), old_code_pages->end(),
7464 std::back_inserter(*new_code_pages),
7465 [removed_page_start](const MemoryRange& range) {
7466 return range.start == removed_page_start;
7467 });
7468 DCHECK_EQ(old_code_pages->size(), new_code_pages->size() + 1);
7469 // Atomically switch out the pointer
7470 SetCodePages(new_code_pages);
7471#endif // !defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
7472}

7485// static
7486Address Isolate::load_from_stack_count_address(const char* function_name) {
7487 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(function_name);
7488 if (!stack_access_count_map) {
7489 stack_access_count_map = new MapOfLoadsAndStoresPerFunction{};
7490 }
7491 auto& map = *stack_access_count_map;
7492 std::string name(function_name);
7493 // It is safe to return the address of std::map values.
7494 // Only iterators and references to the erased elements are invalidated.
7495 return reinterpret_cast<Address>(&map[name].first);
7496}
7497
7498// static
7499Address Isolate::store_to_stack_count_address(const char* function_name) {
7500 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(function_name);
7501 if (!stack_access_count_map) {
7502 stack_access_count_map = new MapOfLoadsAndStoresPerFunction{};
7503 }
7504 auto& map = *stack_access_count_map;
7505 std::string name(function_name);
7506 // It is safe to return the address of std::map values.
7507 // Only iterators and references to the erased elements are invalidated.
7508 return reinterpret_cast<Address>(&map[name].second);
7509}
7510
7511void Isolate::LocalsBlockListCacheSet(
7512 DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> scope_info,
7513 DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> outer_scope_info,
7514 DirectHandle<StringSet> locals_blocklist) {
7515 Handle<EphemeronHashTable> cache;
7516 if (IsEphemeronHashTable(heap()->locals_block_list_cache())) {
7517 cache = handle(Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(heap()->locals_block_list_cache()),
7518 this);
7519 } else {
7520 CHECK(IsUndefined(heap()->locals_block_list_cache()));
7521 constexpr int kInitialCapacity = 8;
7522 cache = EphemeronHashTable::New(this, kInitialCapacity);
7523 }
7524 DCHECK(IsEphemeronHashTable(*cache));
7525
7526 DirectHandle<Object> value;
7527 if (!outer_scope_info.is_null()) {
7528 value = factory()->NewTuple2(outer_scope_info, locals_blocklist,
7529 AllocationType::kYoung);
7530 } else {
7531 value = locals_blocklist;
7532 }
7533
7534 CHECK(!value.is_null());
7535 cache = EphemeronHashTable::Put(cache, scope_info, value);
7536 heap()->set_locals_block_list_cache(*cache);
7537}
7538
7539Tagged<Object> Isolate::LocalsBlockListCacheGet(
7540 DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> scope_info) {
7541 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
7542
7543 if (!IsEphemeronHashTable(heap()->locals_block_list_cache())) {
7544 return ReadOnlyRoots(this).the_hole_value();
7545 }
7546
7547 Tagged<Object> maybe_value =
7548 Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(heap()->locals_block_list_cache())
7549 ->Lookup(scope_info);
7550 if (IsTuple2(maybe_value)) return Cast<Tuple2>(maybe_value)->value2();
7551
7552 CHECK(IsStringSet(maybe_value) || IsTheHole(maybe_value));
7553 return maybe_value;
7554}

7560
7561void DefaultWasmAsyncResolvePromiseCallback(
7562 v8::Isolate* isolate, v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
7563 v8::Local<v8::Promise::Resolver> resolver, v8::Local<v8::Value> result,
7564 WasmAsyncSuccess success) {
7565 MicrotasksScope microtasks_scope(context,
7566 MicrotasksScope::kDoNotRunMicrotasks);
7567
7568 Maybe<bool> ret = success == WasmAsyncSuccess::kSuccess
7569 ? resolver->Resolve(context, result)
7570 : resolver->Reject(context, result);
7571 // It's guaranteed that no exceptions will be thrown by these
7572 // operations, but execution might be terminating.
7573 CHECK(ret.IsJust() ? ret.FromJust() : isolate->IsExecutionTerminating());
7574}
7575
7576// Mutex used to ensure that the dispatch table entries for builtins are only
7577// initialized once.
7578base::LazySpinningMutex read_only_dispatch_entries_mutex_ =
7579 LAZY_SELFISH_MUTEX_INITIALIZER;
7580
7581void Isolate::InitializeBuiltinJSDispatchTable() {
7582#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7583 // Ideally these entries would be created when the read only heap is
7584 // initialized. However, since builtins are deserialized later, we need to
7585 // patch it up here. Also, we need a mutex so the shared read only heaps space
7586 // is not initialized multiple times. This must be blocking as no isolate
7587 // should be allowed to proceed until the table is initialized.
7588 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(read_only_dispatch_entries_mutex_.Pointer());
7589 JSDispatchTable* jdt = IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table();
7590
7591 bool needs_initialization =
7592 !V8_STATIC_DISPATCH_HANDLES_BOOL ||
7593 jdt->PreAllocatedEntryNeedsInitialization(
7594 read_only_heap_->js_dispatch_table_space(),
7595 builtin_dispatch_handle(JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::Idx::kFirst));
7596
7597 if (needs_initialization) {
7598 std::optional<JSDispatchTable::UnsealReadOnlySegmentScope> unseal_scope;
7599 if (V8_STATIC_DISPATCH_HANDLES_BOOL) {
7600 unseal_scope.emplace(jdt);
7601 }
7602 for (JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::Idx idx =
7603 JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::kFirst;
7604 idx < JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::kCount;
7605 idx = static_cast<JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::Idx>(
7606 static_cast<int>(idx) + 1)) {
7607 Builtin builtin = JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::to_builtin(idx);
7608 DCHECK(Builtins::IsIsolateIndependent(builtin));
7609 Tagged<Code> code = builtins_.code(builtin);
7610 DCHECK(code->entrypoint_tag() == CodeEntrypointTag::kJSEntrypointTag);
7611 // TODO(olivf, 40931165): It might be more robust to get the static
7612 // parameter count of this builtin.
7613 int parameter_count = code->parameter_count();
7614#if V8_STATIC_DISPATCH_HANDLES_BOOL
7615 JSDispatchHandle handle = builtin_dispatch_handle(builtin);
7616 jdt->InitializePreAllocatedEntry(
7617 read_only_heap_->js_dispatch_table_space(), handle, code,
7618 parameter_count);
7619#else
7620 CHECK_LT(idx, JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::kTableSize);
7621 isolate_data_.builtin_dispatch_table()[idx] =
7622 jdt->AllocateAndInitializeEntry(
7623 read_only_heap_->js_dispatch_table_space(), parameter_count,
7624 code);
7625#endif // V8_STATIC_DISPATCH_HANDLES_BOOL
7626 }
7627 }
7628#endif
7629}
